Paneer Malai Tikka if u r sick of gravy. Best dish was the cauliflower üëçüèº', "Butter chicken is really good, and the rest of the buffet is worth it, the strawberry margarita is too sweet so I don't recommend it, but besides that it was all good.", 'Great food and very good service. Dare and try some of the spicy Indian dishes. The bread Roti is excellent too!', 'Western style restaurant with Indian and Chinese food and good choice of alcohol. Everything is quite spicy as usual.']

name: Peshawri
address: Taj Ganj Itc Mughal, ƒÄgra 282001, Uttar Pradesh
reviews: ["Peshawri is the same as Bukhara in Delhi (and slightly less expensive). We did both but would have tried something else in Delhi if we'd known", 'Cool vibe, friendly staff, good food, and interesting drinks', 'Probably the best Indian food I‚Äôve had to date', 'Delicious! Loving the lamb!', 'Restaurante en el hotel ITC    Mughal de comida india del norte. Gemelo del Bukhara de Delhi, no ha cambiado su menu desde hace 30 a√±os.']

name: Hummingbird Amsterdam BV
reviews: ['Great! Recommended. "V60 Ethiopian" was amazing. One of the best coffee roasters in Amsterdam. Sure worth to try. "Carrot Cake" was acceptable. Staff is extremely friendly.', 'The place is so cozy, it feels like you‚Äôre at a friend‚Äôs house. The decoration is really beautiful. Tried the flat white and the oatmeal cookies and both were nice.', 'I would recommend this cafe to anyone who is in Spui. The decoration of the cafe is beautiful. I also met the sweetest barista in my life.', 'Love the vibe here, small but clean and cosy! Staff is super nice and have their own blend of beans - oh and ask about their high end coffee machine that thing is next level!', 'Modern interior, friendly staff, good coffee. Appreciate the magazines by the window! A cute small cafe to hide from the rain.', 'Cozy vibes and their flat white is great  ü§ç', 'Excelent specialty coffee! Maybe the best flat white in Amsterdam. Homemade cakes are also delicious', 'The place is nice and cosy and the coffee itself is balanced one of the best coffees I tried in Europe', 'Great coffee, they have their own blend. Highly recommended.', 'Amazing cappuccino and very tasty cookies üòã']

name: Proeflokaal Arendsnest
reviews: ['Really the best beer bar that I know so far in Amsterdam. Regarding the choice: of course La Trappe, De Molen and Skuumkoppe. Also order the old cheese as a side dish and finish with a shot of jenever', 'Only Dutch craft beer, 30 on tap and around 100 bottled. Great selection of beers from Brouwerij De Molen. Go check the blackboards and make your choice. Beers on tap also served in 15cl tasters.', "In this amazing bar you'll always find one, if not ten, surprising new beer to try. All beers being Dutch, it is the place to discover Holland's newly found brewing pride!", 'Best pub on the Herengracht Canal, also one of the priciest, but worth it. Incredible selection of local Dutch microbrews, great location in Jordaan with outdoor seating and nice evening crowd.', 'While this bar may be more filled with tourists than locals, I think it has possibly the most complete list of Dutch Craft Beers in the city. Highly recommend if you want to get a feel for the scene.', 'The 24-page beer menu provides not only prices but also short bios of each beer including the history, location and alcohol percentage. The strongest beer available are Bombs and Grenades (15.2% abv).', 'One of the best beer places in Amsterdam. 30 beers from draft. All Dutch! Staff have very good knowledge. True recommendation for both tourist as locals', '‚ÄúGrej‚Äù bear(sweet and strong)and also ‚ÄúTop of morning‚Äù (dark with the taste of chocolate) are amazing!', 'Enormous selection of beers on tap. But also ask the bartender to recommend some genevers. They shouldn‚Äôt be missed either.', 'Various choices of beer, cosy atmosphere and delicious gouda Perfect stop for an afternoon break']

name: Scheltema
reviews: ['What a fantastic bookstore! Lots of books, plenty of space to walk around or sit and relax, a cafe, a space for author talks, and we noticed a cooking class. A bit of everything, plus friendly staff!', 'Best book shop in Amsterdam, moved to this newlocation a few years ago. Multiple floors, each with a wide selection of topics. Also organizes events with famous authors, like Donna Hay.', 'With this 5 stories high book store, there is something for anyone. They have a caf√© inside in case you need a break. From wednesday to saturday you can offer them your own books for sale.', 'Super nice bookstore with 5 floors filled with a great selection of books. There is a nice reading caf√© included on the first floor.', 'Classic, stylish, lotsnod books and very friendly staff', 'This new location is amazing! Beautiful building, great location, well designed, great collection. They have everything! I can be there for hours!', 'Nice big bookstore. Has a good selection of books in English and also some other languages.', 'Lots of interesting themed books and magazines and you can also go for a drink.', 'They have a floor with discounted books and books in English, French and other foreign languages. Children‚Äôs department is very nice.', 'Beautiful bookshop with nice areas to sit and browse.']

name: Ashoka
reviews: ['Yummy authentic Indian cuisine . The place is Cozy , waiters and service are excellent and the food is So GOod ! A must try üëçüèº', 'Perfect for vegans and vegetarians! We ordered something mild spicy and it was OK for non-indiansüòä', "One of few restaurants with proper Nepalese dhal baat on the menu. Don't overestimate yourself when the waiter asks for your preferred level of spiciness.", 'Unbelievable! Amazing Indian restaurant. Worth the hype. "Butter Chicken" + "Samosa" + "Lamb Biryani" all were delicious. "Chicken Tikka Tandoori" was in average. Don‚Äôt forget "Chicken Momo" it isüëåüèª', 'One of the best Indian restaurants in Amsterdam. We ordered Lamb Baryiani, Butter Chicken, Cheese Naan, and Tandoori; all of them were just excellent. Would definitely repeat the visit.', 'Great food, beautiful atmosphere and welcoming staff. Ordered Butter chicken was so yummy, naan bread and bashawri was delicious. Don‚Äôt recommend the lamb dishes it was not really tender. Overall üëçüèª', 'Lovely staff, great interior, food was delicious as always. However, we thought the rice was a bit undercooked. Overall a great experience, would definitely recommend üëçüèª', 'Samosa, prawn masala, butter chicken, lamp masala, vegi biryani and nan. Amazing food a must in Amsterdam ‚úÖ nice staff.']

name: P.G.C. Hajenius
reviews: ["Smoking a cigar at the shop's lounge was a whole different experience. One of my favorite places in the city. Staff were nice.", 'Buy something from the massive walk in humidor, and enjoy it in the lounge in the back.', 'The cigar lounge is a very nice place to escape the hectic inner city.', "Cigar aficionado's must visit -place in Amsterdam!", 'One of the best cigars shop I have ever seen  (but not as good as Pierre cigars club in Seoul)', 'Big variety of cigars, very rude and unfriendly personnel, I was willing to spend a good amount of money, didn‚Äôt leave penny! Good job guys!!!ü§Æ', "Excellent selection of Cuban cigars. Don't miss the smoking lounge in the back.", 'The best cigar shop in Amsterdam by a mile!', 'Try the Don Thomas, my favorite, and mind you, not from Cuba.', 'I love this place, the atmosphere is so old school golden era Dutch.']

name: The American Book Center
reviews: ["The name should be changed to 'The Amazing Book Center'. Definitely worth a visit, even if its just to have a cup of coffee (upstairs).", 'I love stopping by at american book store when I go to Spui, one of my favorite straats in Amsterdam. Cozy place, you can spent hours reading and buying staff', 'Enormous selection of travel books (also of Amsterdam and The Netherlands), science fiction and Fantasy. Plus a hidden corner with board, card and role playing games.', 'If you like books (and magazines, games, etc), the American Book Center is (together with close by Waterstones) definitely worth visiting.', 'You can find any book, magazines and guides in here. Huge store with great atmosphere. They have this "blind date with a book" thing which i thing really exciting.', 'Chaotic organization of books and categories, but I like it. The shop has some nice corridors with shelves filled with books up to the ceiling. Even the stairs are flanked by bookshelves!', "Honestly the best looking book store I've ever come across with a beautiful collection of books, graphic novels etc. I think I want to live here.", "Easily the best bookstore in Amsterdam. Bargains and the massive graphic novel & manga sections are definitely worth checking out. Don't forget to show your student card at checkout!", 'Four floors of various literature in English! As a fan of Star Wars I found several editions of storyboards for the entire Saga, albums about such renowned artists as Ralph McQuarrie and much more.', 'Huge selection. Check out the mystery books on the top floor. You never know what you will get! Provide your student ID from anywhere in the world and get a discount!']

name: Oude Kerk
reviews: ['Very nice and cozy place to have a cup of coffee and piece of amazing cake in the centre of A‚Äôdam. Highly recommend peanut butter chocolate cake which is my new addiction. Gezzellig! ‚ù§Ô∏è', 'Freshly made apple pie thru out the day. Good coffee. Nice terrace in the church garden.A very cozy little oasis in the middle of the red light district.', 'By far one of the best spots to have a nice coffee or healthy drink. Cozy and stylish inside and a beautiful front yard. The smell of the freshly baked cakes is amazing.', 'Perfect place for coffee lovers in Amsterdam. Comfortable to the eyes for outdoor seats. Filter coffee was excellent. "Apple pie" was met the expectations. Sure worth to try.', 'Still my favorite place in Amsterdam, every coffee and cake is fantastic and the staff is always kind and helpful.', 'Very cozy place with enough private space for everyone. Own terrace with a living fence, as well as additional corners on the first and especially second floor. Nice desserts and tasty coffee!', 'Very cozy and authentic place in a flowery church garden. Delicious cakes and quality coffee served. It has also has a second floor which you can also work / study quietly.', 'WHY THERE: coffee, desserts, vintage, interior. COFFEE: lovely. DESSERTS: crazy piers. STAFF: decent and friendly. LOCATION: mainstream (convenient) PRICES: average (reasonable)', 'A place you can spend hours without noticing.. so homey with garden and a room full of light..coffee is the best in town since there using bocca beans.', 'Cozy place with amazing atmosphere and friendly staff.. Very good location, fine coffee and excelent apple pie! Thums up :)']

name: Winkel 43
reviews: ['Like all the others, the apple pie is a must recommend! This is a cute bar/cafe   and with great charm. Evening menu starts at 6 and is yummy. I recommend the pork with chorizo+cheese, it was great.', "An Amsterdam classic, and you can't go wrong. Start in the early afternoon with a cup of tea or coffee with classic dutch apple-pie, served to perfection. Continue the day with a few beers and snacks", "We were told numerous times ‚Äî Winkel 43 served the 'best apple pie in Amsterdam‚Ä¶' ‚Äî They didn't disappoint. You will probably have to wait for a table and be prepared to queue ‚Äî but it's so worth it.", 'The apple pie is delicious without a doubt! Hard to find a place to sit & the que to order is always petty long, but it moves fast. Is it a must? No, I think its so crowded coz somehow it got famous.', 'The best apple pie in town! Very friendly service , atmosphere and good vibe. Latte is very smooth and sweet. Highly recommended place to try the pie with coffee here!', 'Seriously the apple cake is the best thing I‚Äôve ever eaten. It was so amazing. The spiced apple and sweet crust took my breath awayüëèüèª', 'Best apple pie in the world even if you do not like apple pie, you will love this one. Whipped cream makes it delicious. Coffee and mint tea are also great. Crowded and there is line at the enterance.', 'Family managed extremely popular place - be aware you will have to wait. Apple pie is incredible!! Coffee is good as well! Cold and warm snacks are available', "If you haven't tried this apple pie you probably have missed one of the most wonderful things in Amsterdam. I keep trying different apple pies here in Amsterdam so far none can beat this!", "Apple pie at its best: are you hungry? Get one. Are you not? Doesn't matter, just get the damn pie. It is heavenly delicious. And the hot chocolate is also good. But GET THE PIE."]

name: Toastable
reviews: ['Tried Caprese, I liked it, the tomato tastes strong (sun-dried tomato) which I loved since I really love tomatoes. The only downside is the mozzarella cheese tastes good but they put a lot, too cheesy', 'They have mastered the old-aged art of toasting! One toast = one brunch, no discussion. Give tip', 'High quality food!cozy placeüå∏üö≤Very nice coffee, tasty toasts and the brownie with salted caramel....wow it was so amazing üëèüèªüôåüèΩ so recommend it‚ò∫Ô∏èüôãüèº\u200d‚ôÄÔ∏è‚ô•Ô∏èüòãüòã', 'Good atmosphere, tasty sandwitch (Legend on the pic), even better green juice. Good coffee.', 'Overnight oat is good, toastable (triple!) sandwiches are delicious! Cozy interior and nice staff. They use compostable saucers. We would like to eat here again!', 'Lived up to the Foursquare hype! Best sandwiches in town!', 'Creative sandwich combinations not just for breakfast but for the whole day. Trust the ‚ÄûSandwich of the Month‚Äú recommendation!', 'Great service, toasty with pulled pork and bbq sauce is simply the best. Lemonade and coffee tasty also. Highly recommend!', 'Such great breakfast. Try the Crosti. It‚Äôs a fresh baked croissant, with toppings of egg, bacon, avocado, cheese, or whatever other goodness you want.']

name: D&A Hummus Bistro
reviews: ["I felt in love with this place ! One of the best hummus in Amsterdam, creamy not to much oily. The homemade pita bread is wonderful ( white and brown). Try the watermelon and gets, it's delicious !", "Incredible food! I love when it's healthy and tasty in the same time and this food is perfect to sharing like tapas with your partner ! Special mention for the open kitchen, watching chef cooking!", "Everything is sooo good here. It's all made fresh with such a perfect combination of hearty flavors. We tried the hummus with roasted veggies and the lamb dish. Both highly recommended!", 'Great value! (I do not agree with the review that says this place is expensive.) Shakshuka is great and staff is really friendly. Their playlists are perfect during diner. Must visit!', 'one of my favorites in Amsterdam for lunch. apart from their yummy hummus try their extremely delicious baked eggplant', 'The hummus has different toppings to choose from, and comes with fluffy pitas. I recommend the one with chicken and the other one with pulled pork. The eggplant was disappointing. It's generally a bit pricey but totally worth it!", 'Get the A Little Bit of This & A Little Bit of That so you can try a bunch of things. The chicken hummus was smooth and flavorful and the falafel was crunchy and light.', "Took 'a bit of this'n'that' as couldn't choose. Everything was great and the Home made Ice tea crowned the set. I drank three of those Ice teas. Strongly recommend the place!", "Falafel hummus is fantastic. Can be crowded since it's a fairly tight space but casual enough to eat solo or with a plus one. Hummus is very creamy and filling."]

reviews: ['Do not miss it!! reviews: ['It is mandatory: once in Athens, you HAVE to visit this place. Arrive early, as it gets crowded real quick. Greek food, organic local wine and traditional environment.', 'Cappadocian - Karamanli pastirma or "Karamanlidikos pastirmas", an exquisite handmade delicacy, accompanies traditional distilled Greek beverages as ouzo & tsipouro. Enjoy!', 'If you would like to impress your female companion or if you just want to have a great meal you should eat at this place.The cheese and meat plateau for two persona with a glass of red wine is perfect', 'Bio eggs with pastirma & sudjuk, salad with paskitan, tsipouro. One of our fave haunts in Athens. Gluten-free hams & cold-cuts, red & white wine collection, cheese. http://whyathens.com/karamanlidika/', 'The best place we‚Äôve eaten after a week in Greece hands down. Loved everything - pastrami, chick peas, dolmas, bulgar salad. There‚Äôs even a cute outdoor patio. Good beer menu. Maybe best food ever.', 'One of the best dishes that I have ever had ‚ù§Ô∏è the best place to eat in Athens', 'A cool place in Athens! Try red wine & taste Greek delicacies in small plates! Enjoy delicious local pastrami, prosciutto, sausages, turkey, pastirma & soutzouki. Discover authentic, aged, PGI cheese.', 'An eggs & cheese paradise. Also top feta, prosciutto, pastrami, gluten-free cold-cuts. Nice collection of Greek red & white wine. Near Varvakeios Market free wifi. Dinner reservations +30210 325 4184.', 'This place was life-changing and I‚Äôm not even joking. The smoked cheese and the kavournas were our favourites, along with the baklava. Lots of love for the Spanish lady heading the place‚ÄîI‚Äôll be back!', 'Delicious food, very inexpensive, with plenty of vegetarian options (yes, really!) and the staff is super nice. We only wished we had found it sooner, best place in Athens!']

name: Temple of Athena Nike (ŒùŒ±œåœÇ œÑŒ∑œÇ ŒëŒ∏Œ∑ŒΩŒ¨œÇ ŒùŒØŒ∫Œ∑œÇ)
reviews: ['Built in 420BC and is the earliest Ionic temple on the Acropolis.', 'Beautiful, more delicate; dedicated to the goddesses of ancient Greek. Make a full walk around, back sidebis different than front.', 'The Temple of the Athena Victory (Wingless Victory), was built circa 420 BC in commemoration of the victory of the Greeks against the Persians.', 'One of my favorite temples cause its connected with Nike. Know the meaning behind the Nike symbol', 'The best time to visit is the early morning.', 'Greeks used to pour libations and to deposit primitive figurines of the deities worshiped to the temple of Athena Nike.', 'Just like all the sites in Athens, it‚Äôs ruined and visually unimpressive. Some sort of guide highly recommended to make it more interesting.', 'Great views amazing history', 'Amazing views , great history', 'Amazing view!']

name: Herod Atticus Odeon (Œ©Œ¥ŒµŒØŒø ŒóœÅœéŒ¥ŒøœÖ ŒëœÑœÑŒπŒ∫Œøœç)
address: Œ†ŒµŒ∂œåŒ¥œÅŒøŒºŒøœÇ ŒîŒπŒøŒΩ. ŒëœÅŒµŒøœÄŒ±Œ≥ŒØœÑŒøœÖ (ŒùœåœÑŒπŒ± Œ∫ŒªŒπœÑœçœÇ ŒëŒ∫œÅŒøœÄœåŒªŒµœâœÇ), 10555 ŒëŒ∏ŒÆŒΩŒ±, ŒëœÑœÑŒπŒ∫ŒÆ
reviews: ['Herod Atticus built this roofed Odeon (in 161 B.C.) for music concerts in honor of his wife Regilla, after her death. Its magic and beauty, can only be understood when walking on the way to Acropolis.', 'a stone theatre structure located on the south slope of the Acropolis of Athens. It was built in 161 AD by the Athenian magnate Herodes Atticus in memory of his wife, Aspasia Annia Regilla.', 'An ancient theater from the Roman era, very well preserved just below Acropolis. Must visit!!!!', 'Ancient theater built on the slope of the Acropolis that is nowadays the main venue of the Athens Greek festival. Try to attend a live concert or an ancient tragedy, unforgettable experience.', 'A bit hard on your bottom and your back, can be very hot sometimes, but it is worth every minute of your time and every cent of your money to be here for a concert, ballet, play or whatever.', 'Imagine the excitement when not only you visit a monument of thousands years old but you participate in an event that is similar to the use of this monument thousands of years ago..feeling privileged!', 'Museum and Acropolis tickets also give access to the temple of Zeus', "You should definitely go at least once in your life! If you are a tourist try to book something that it might suit you, you won't regret it!", 'Built in 161AD by Herodes Atticus in memory of his wife. Had a capacity of 5000. Lasted just over 100 years until destroyed by the Heruli in 267AD.', "A place to visit for sure if you're coming in summer during Athens Art Festival! An amphitheater on the base of the Acropolis rock."]

name: Parthenon (Œ†Œ±œÅŒ∏ŒµŒΩœéŒΩŒ±œÇ)
reviews: ["Despite the scaffolding and enormous crane, this is a site you can't miss in Athens. Enjoy the climb up the hill and admire the beauty.", 'Gorgeous! Get there early as the tours start arriving around 9am (it opens at 8am). The side entrance (near the museum) is much less busy than the main entrance.', 'The Parthenon  is a temple on the Athenian Acropolis, Greece, dedicated to the Greek goddess Athena.Its construction began in 447 BCIt is the most important surviving building of Classical Greece.', 'What can you say but Wow! Beautiful architecture and history. Get there early to beat the heat and the crowds. Buy tickets ahead of time to skip the lines. Great vistas from everywhere.', "Worth going at sunset - it feels a lot cooler up there at that time of day in the summer and it's truly wonderful to watch the sun sink down over Athens from this view point.", 'Beautiful ancient Greek architecture. Some construction and renovation is still going on. So difficult to take proper photo without anything at the background. Number 1 must-see tourist attraction.', 'As an Egyptian, these sites tend to be not so impressive. Bit of a hike, but a must see. Gorgeous views.', "One of Western civilisation's most important sites lives up to its reputation! Awe-inspiring architecture, stunning views and the centre-piece of a wonderful city!", 'Save a min of 2 hours 4 this sight. U need 2 b ready wz appropriate shoes as lots of areas are slippery & u will walk up & down z entire visit. Great view from top so be ready for loads of selfies.', 'this place is amazing, worth visiting. With just one ticket you visit all the monuments.']

name: Acropolis of Athens (ŒëŒ∫œÅœåœÄŒøŒªŒ∑ ŒëŒ∏Œ∑ŒΩœéŒΩ)
reviews: ['Try a weekday with clear weather to enjoy the great views. Your senses will be eternally grateful and you will commit the visit to memory for the rest of your life! Stop reading and book your ticket!', 'The place where civilization was born, one of the 7 wonders, overlooking one of the most ancient cities in the world, stands one of the most must seen places in Athens.', 'The Acropolis of Athens! The greatest and finest sanctuary of ancient Athens. The imposing Parthenon is the most magnificent creation of Athenian democracy at the height of its power.', "The greatest masterpiece of classical Greek art can be seen as symbolizing the idea of world heritage.When words can't describe the beauty. #lifetime_experience", 'One of the most amazing sites in the world. Often overlooked nearby are the south flank of the Acropolis (separate entrance) and the nearby Pnyx hill where democracy was born.', 'A bucket list must see. The entire Acropolis offers so much history and not just about the Parthenon structure. Various temples on other buildings are on top as well.Bring some water as it can get hot', 'Best tip to avoid queue: buy a 30‚Ç¨ combination ticket at one of the other six archeological sites which are far less crowded. If you do this you can skip the line at Acropolis. Take eastern entrance.', 'Such an amazing site !! One of the 7 wonders of the world !! What an honor to have climbed to the top and viewed modern Athens !! So proud to be Greek !!!', 'Beautiful view and gorgeous buildings of the antic greek empire. But the floors were really slippery, everyone fell at least two times. I even saw a man getting injured... There must be a solution!', 'Since 1987\xa0UNESCO World\xa0Heritage, the Acropolis is a place where probably Europe was founded. The view over the city is breathtaking, we enjoyed every second on this historical place.']

name: Acropolis Museum (ŒúŒøœÖœÉŒµŒØŒø ŒëŒ∫œÅœåœÄŒøŒªŒ∑œÇ)
reviews: ['one of the best places on planet Earth... the best collection of artifacts in the world (some missing :(  ) the best view Acropolis of Athens and Parthenon, under the Athenian blue sky, 11 out of 10', "British Museum should give the rest back. Some claim they are best kept there in London. Come on! This Museum is a symbol of greeks' capability of taking care of their own history. This is beautiful!", 'Entry: 5 euros. Bag check: free. Indoor/outdoor seating in restaurant. I liked the films in the museum, that helped me learn more without hiring a guide. I spent about 2 hours here.', 'I cannot appreciate this museum enough! One of the most modern and polished museums I‚Äôve ever been to! The art collection is just mesmerizing. Definitely a must see after going to the Acropolis!', 'Absolutely incredible museum. Definitely come here before hiking to the top of the Acropolis--it will enrich your experience! Have lunch at the second floor caf√©. The view of the Acropolis is awesome!', 'Nice location, quite central, easy to access on foot. It may take easily 2hrs, to walk around the exibits and read about them. Better to come to museum before climbing up the Acropolis. Cafe available', 'Went on a Friday night since the museum is open until 22 or 10pm. Was not busy at all. Learned a lot about Acropolis. Loved the setup of the museum. Cool to see original pieces from Parthenon.', 'Start at the top floor to see the friezes and pediments set to the original scale, then wander down to see the rest of the exhibition arranged chronologically. So awe-inspiring, with great views!', 'A very modern building where you can see some of the best  examples that the ancient Greek civilization has to offer, located in one of the most beautiful streets of Athens.', "The Acropolis was very cool to see in real life there was a lot to take in so make sure you block out the whole day. Once you're done with the sites and museum make sure to check out the neighborhood."]

name: Auckland Domain
reviews: ["Don't forget to visit the Winter Garden. Most of the people go to the Domain to visit the Museum, but don't know about the fantastic gardens, just 1 minute walking from the museum.", 'A great place to visit any time of the year. There you will find the Auckland Museum and the Winter Garden. Both worth visiting!', 'Best place for taking a walk and chilling!', 'Truck decks for sale nz, Best Truck Liners, Durapro NZ - We are the supply and installers of best truck Liners Auckland New Zealand. Moreover, we supply Oiler Bearings and Durapro Truck Liners too.', 'If you are the kind of person that likes exploring and getting lost, this is a great place to be.', 'Calm and quite place in the city. One of the best places to enjoy the summer', 'Beautiful park and perfect Lantern Festival location.', 'Kids love tree', 'Winter gardens is a wonderful place and very few tourists find it', 'We play football every Tuesday and Thursday at 12pm. Great spot.']

name: Mount Eden - Maungawhau
reviews: ["The road to the top is out of commission.  Walk up to the top from the car barrier.  It's a pleasant walk and the view is special", 'Climb and have some amazing scenery and experience the in-active volcano.', 'off leash area for dogs up on the hill. If keen for a power walk, try walking to the summit. A nice area overall. One of my favourites', 'Gotta top out and check out the views. Awesome photo of the crater back towards town.', 'Loved the climb to the summit and the views. I did not remember how deep the crater hole was near the summit', 'Easy hike and awesome views', 'One of the volcanic cones in Auckland. Great view of the city!', 'Not a bad walk from CBD. Bring a picnic for the sunset', 'A melhor vista de Auckland! Best view in Auckland', 'Nice crater. Also check out one tree hill!']

name: Mt Eden Summit
reviews: ['A must-visit locale for stunning 360 degree views over Auckland.', "Cool park and pretty cool view on the city and the Auckland area, especially for the sunset when it's (kinda) clear.", 'Short hike to the top. The crater is pretty cool!', 'The best view is actually up a side hill on the west side of the summit', 'Drive here instead of hiking! Great 360 view of Auckland and beyond.', 'You have a 360 view of Auckland...awesome !', 'Watch out! Plenty of lover birds in their cars about! :-D', 'Mount Eden in Auckland', 'Take a panoramic.', 'In the bottom of the crater dwells a Taniwha, so beware.']

name: Albert Park
reviews: ["If you love fountains then I think you'll like this one, it's really pretty.", 'Stupid beautiful and it has FREE wifi throughout. Definitely a gem hidden inside Aucklands bustling city', 'So peaceful! Sit on one of the benches and watch the birds or lay on the grass for a quick sunny nap', 'Good for relaxing, breathing fresh air and lovely flowers for the eyes.', 'Nice park, a few benches around to chill and pretty gardens.', 'Good place to go for some peace and quiet in the heart of the city', 'Wow you can do drugs and drink without worrying about the police at night', 'A good place to build your route through. Especially in the morning. Love oaks!', 'Very well lit and safe to walk through at night.', "Sit back and relax. It feels like you're high above the city in this park."]

name: Tony's Original Steak & Seafood Restaurant
reviews: ['Superb steak, superb wine, superb service...', 'Pacific steak really good and the eye beef meat really melt in my mouth. Really recommended.', 'The original Tony‚Äôs steak just so so compare to the pacific steak', 'Perfectly cooked Medium-rare Rump Steak', 'The Calamari just so so and over peice', "Get the 'Localist' steak and drink special. $20.", 'Great steak!', 'Choose their steaks and house wines. Nice!', "It's a steak house, get the steak.", 'Mega feines Filet, einfach der Hammer']

name: Auckland Art Gallery
reviews: ['Beautifully designed gallery featuring Kauri throughout. Well organized with good NZ Art selections as well as guest features.', 'Very informative staff, giving us a great introduction to Maori art and culture. Lots of classic and contemporary work on display.', 'Very small museum but worth the free entry. The building is gorgeous. My favorite was the Maori portraits - obviously unique to New Zealand.', "There's no permanent collection, and exhibitions change regularly. Gottfried Lindauer's portraits of important Maori figures are amazing.", 'Wide-ranging collection with the hoped-for emphasis on New Zealand artists. Free admission. Cool cafe, with Steampunk coffee maker.', 'The cafe has amazing toasted sandwiches, and the lovely balcony will be glorious to sit on in summer. Welcome to the new Auckland Art Gallery!', 'A really nice place to visit and know more about NZ art. Really nice!', 'Loved it! Louise Henderson‚Äôs trajectory and story was my favorite. Take the free tour!', 'Great cubist exhibit. Major works by New Zealand artists.', 'Right place to check some maori artwork, and also the great architecture of the gallery.']

name: Remedy Coffee
reviews: ['Lovely coffee place with beautiful open windows to watch the crowd on the street. The salads were exquisite and totally worth the little wait, as they came with big chunks of bread and warm chorizo!', 'Decent piccolo latte with sour undertones. They should however use good quality full cream milk (organic) to make it perfect. Red Rabbit Coffee beans are used for espresso based drinks.', "Breakfast bagels are a great option here. Although you'll probably fall in love with the kitschy ambience which is definitely a geek's paradise.", 'Cappuccino and almond croissant cost NZD 10.5 and were both delicious. It is really small but the atmosphere is great.', 'Had the carb free breakfast and it was really delicious plus their (delicious) coffees come with the cutest little spoons', 'Cozy interior, tasty desserts, great coffee and the staff always friendly ! absolutely lovely place !', 'Cool local cafe vibe! Very good coffee and a small range of good pastries. Funky furniture. Loved it.', 'Awesome intimate little cafe with great coffee and cozy surroundings. The banana cake is great.', 'Cosy little cafe almost in the heart of the city. Liked my chai latte even more cz it was served with a smile:)', 'Fabulous place, very friendly staff and lovely food. Coffee is a piece of art. Will definitely be back!']

name: Depot Eatery & Oyster Bar
reviews: ['Excellent food but not very friendly service.', "Order Mahurangi Oysters, Snapper Sliders, Bone Marrow, Lamb Ribs and Tuatua Clams! All fresh and yummy! They have wine on tap, not bad. Love the atmosphere there. Better reserve a table, it's packed!", 'We left our order to our waitress and she nailed every single order. Clams and oysters well shucked. The craydog gave me mouthfuls of orgasmic pleasure. Great beer list too!', "It's worth getting a little adventurous - stranger dishes (like popcorn duck tongues) are a surprising delight (as is everything). Excellent show case of pacific rim cooking and NZ produce.", "Squid in linguini with clams and chorizo ! If you like seafood you won't regret this pick, but really can't go wrong at deposit with any of the items on their menu!", "Depot never disappoints! Super friendly staff, lively atmosphere, decent prices for the quality of food on offer - what's not to love? Must try: Hapuka sliders, Fergus‚Äô bone marrow & Brussels sprouts.", "Omg! I've fall in love with this place. Oysters are big , delicious and not expensive and the service is great. You should spend your Friday night at here , order oysters and drink wine.", 'Bone marrow was fab, but the charred broccoli w/labneh date and almond was better and the halibut sliders were worth traveling from U.K. for. Thank you!', 'Al Brown‚Äôs temple to dude food is the buzziest spot in town. Inside, it‚Äôs all about the seasonal small plates: lamb with mini Yorkshire puddings and snapper sliders with a killer lemon mayo.', 'Super hip and super delish. Long waits so go early. Right next to the Skytower. This photo is of the Turbot slider. Wow. So nom!']

name: That's Amore Pizza
reviews: ["Best pizza in Auckland! Sooo delicious and super cute, a rare gem in Auckland's CBD", 'Pizza should be your go to...enjoy what you like.', "One of Auckland's best places, hope it stays there forever.", 'Amazing Margherita pizza', 'Pizza here is always good. Try a calzone.', "Friendly service. Lots to choose from. You can't go wrong.", "The first time I'm here I ordered DUCA. I was impressive, trust me, it's DELICIOUS !", 'The best pizzas in Auckland.', 'Pretty good pizza, very friendly staff', 'Fast at bringing out the pizza!']

name: Campuhan Ridge Walk
reviews: ['Best time to visit: late afternoons or evenings when the weather is cooler and lighting for photos is perfect, especially with the changing colours of the skyline. A must visit for those visiting Ubud', 'Go for a walk 30 minutes or so before sunset and enjoy it at Kasa Cafe (see my tip there). It could get a little dark after so ask for a taxi in the surroundings.', 'Enjoyable walk through paved pathways. The actual ridge walk is around 1.5 km, the rest of the walk go through villages and some ricefields.', 'Lovely walk in nature. Stop at a warung for lunch or walk all the way to the end and find Bamboo kitchen for awesome views.', 'The swing on the way is the cheapest in Bali. Just 50 k! In other places it varies between 100 and 200 k! The road is like a path in paradise!', '2km each way, a lovely walk along the ridge, filled with small local businesses and warungs to stop and grab a cuppa or a meal on the way.', 'Wanna go jogging while seeing nice green view. Come to this place. Really refreshing!', 'Come for sunset! It‚Äôs not too busy and will be less hot.', 'Beautiful walk on the ridge, worth taking it in the morning or late afternoon, when the Sun is not so strong.', 'June 2024 - It‚Äôs essentially a paved walk through overgrown foliage. There are no views.']

name: Sweet Orange Warung
address: Jalan Kajeng Ubud Kecamatan Ubud, Ubud, Bali 80571
reviews: ["Beautful hidden place. Take a walk down the small path you'll find on Main Ubud road for the rice fields. Cca 5 mins along the rice fields and you'll arrive to this little paradise. Has wi-fi!", 'What a lovely atmosphere. You can leave busy Ubud centre and after a 10 minute walk you‚Äôre in a nice quiet place. I loved their juices and the Mie Goreng. The starter platter is great! Loved it!', "Find the path outside of town to go walk through the rice paddies. Nestled among them, you'll find cute places to stop & have lunch or a refreshment. Sit back, relax and take in the lush, green views!", 'So peaceful and chill. You can relax here for hour enjoying the view of the rice fields, reading a book. The papaya and banana juice was amazing. So was the salad with the shrimp.', 'An oasis in the middle of the rice fields. Awesome food, great view. Try watermelon & banana juice which is not on the menu. Ayam sambal matah is very nice. Have a pisang goreng after your meal!', "What a beautiful place and what a view. The owner is super nice as well, and the food is very reasonable! It's really only a short walk from Ubud centre", "Great place,with amazing view. Not a big choice of meals though, and it's quite hard to get there. But nevertheless one of the best places in Ubud!", '... such a lovely place a little bit hidden in the Ubud Rice fields. Food was really delicious and prices were reasonable. Very nice & special atmosphere. Warung is serviced by a very friendly family.', "Lovely local restaurant in the middle of the rice fields. Probably the best and friendliest service that we've received in all of Bali.", 'The view is amazing, staff is nice and food is very good. A quiet place to hangout at lunch/afternoon.']

name: Bali Treetop Adventure Park
address: Jalan Kebun Raya Eka Karya Bali, Candikuning, Baturiti, Tabanan, Indonesia (Candikuning), Tabanan, Bali 82191
reviews: ["Fun for all ages and fitness levels! However, if you're looking for a real challenge, this is more fun than challenging. Still a must do for a day of fun though.", 'Great place, definetely worse to visit. Tips: in the morning(before 10) tickets are chieper (-2$), booking online gives 10% discount. Also I will advise to buy gloves before you come here (20idr here)', 'At the Bali Botanic Garden amazing attraction for whole family. Yangsters will loooove it', 'Try Tree Top Adventure Bali designed by Kuta Transport http://www.kutatransport.com', 'Much better and more of an adrenalin-kick then expected. Safety first and a works great for the entire family.', "Crazy amounts of fun!! Don't do the hardest one last after the second- and third-hardest though,  your muscles will already be exhausted!", 'Try Bali Tree Top Adventure designed by http://www.kutatransport.com', 'Good for you to have upper muscle exercises:)', 'Good for family üëåüèª', 'Better wearing gloves if you dont want het your hands full of red marks']

name: Paon Bali Cooking Class
reviews: ["Good selection of dishes and includes a market tour and a rice paddy tour ! Worth it if you're willing to commit a morning. The host is very funny and her husband funier. Pickup incl.", 'Serious cooking school, you can learn a lot in half day: going to the market to choose products, visiting a school, and of course prepare yourself about 8 traditional dishes that were very good.', 'Had a wonderful experience, learning to cook with the owner of Paon! You get picked up a driven to her home which has a cooking school set up. You help make an incredibly tasty assortment of dishes.', 'It was fantastic experience and great rediscovery of traditional balinese receipts. The family is very nice and welcoming. Really recommend this place.', 'The whole experience was great.  It was fun and entertaining way to learn the classics of bali cuisine!  Great family', 'Highly recommended! My friend was sick and he was "treated" like royalty, plus he wasn\'t charged.', 'Well-run class with a recipe book leave-behind. Bring your own bottled water.', 'Simply. Amazing!', 'good tour and cook delicious food!', 'Tolles Balinesisches Essen selber zubereitet unter netter Anleitungüòâes war richtig leckerüòç']

name: La Brisa
address: Jalan Pantai Batu Mejan, Gg La Brisa Echo Beach, Canggu, Kuta Utara, Seseh, Badung, Bali 80361
reviews: ['One of the newest go to places for laid back lunch to smashing sun downers, accompanied by very good music and a lush extravaganza of a decorated garden. ENJOY I wish I was born here', "This place is stunning. Come here during sunset and for the trendy, hip vibe. Even if you're not into that. Get the dragonfruit cocktail and fish croquettes. But what unpredictable, the atmosphere after the sunset..magical!', 'Good customer care, perfect music, tasteful cocktails. Definitely a ‚Äòmust do‚Äô in bali.', 'Great ambience, decent food. Super chill. Do try the grilled corn on the cob vendor just in front of the restaurant along the beach. Great stuff.']

name: Munduk
address: Munduk Village (Jln Raya Seririt denpasar), Buleleng, Bali
reviews: ['Other than the waterfalls, Munduk trekking is popular too, you will be hiking through clove, cocoa, coffee plantations and rice fields. name: Echo Beach (Pantai Echo)
reviews: ["From nine till five I have to spend my time at work / The job is very boring, I'm an office clerk / The only thing that helps pass the time away / Is knowing I'll be back at Echo Beach some day", 'Always had a really great time there! Love da beach, da food superb, and also love da atmosphere! One of my favorite beach in Bali! ‚ò∫Ô∏è', 'One of the best Tom Yam Seafood soup here,tuna steak tasty!Nice view!We liked!', "A great place to hang out, grab a drink, and catch the sunset. name: Bali Botanic Garden (Kebun Raya Eka Karya Bedugul)
address: Jalan Kebun Raya Candikuning Kec. Baturiti (Candikuning), Tabanan, Bali 82191
reviews: ['Amazing park! Practically no people, super neat, you can walk for hours! There is a inexpensive hotel too', "Incredible views. It's best if you venture around the park on foot. Park your vehicle in the car park and enjoy your time! üôÇ", 'Beautiful gardens with interesting statues of their gods throughout the garden. Come here for a picnic on the well manicure lawns. A little far off from Kuta, but a nice visit if you have time.', "If you visit botanic gardens for annual orchid extravaganzas, this isn't your joint. However, if you're a botanist with a keen interest in non-flowering plants, prepare to freak out.", 'So quiet on weekdays. Only visiting the statue, cactus house, super old giant tree, and seeing the lake üòÜ', 'Breathtaking view... Fresh air, old trees and flowers... Nice place for picnic or camping...', 'Ask for the map at the ticket office. name: Satu-satu cafe
reviews: ['Definitely the best coffee shop in Canggu. The staff, the food and last but not least the coffee were marvelous. Go there and support the local owner!', 'One of the best cafes in Canggu. You'll have a great time!", 'Perfect food (breakfasts!) for reasonable prices and the most friendly stuff. name: Finns Beach Club

reviews: ['The spot is ‚ù§Ô∏è, to watch the sunset. Great cesar salad and pi√±a colada. The massage is supper ‚≠êÔ∏è. Ice cream parlour inside the beach club. name: Temple of the Emerald Buddha (‡∏ß‡∏±‡∏î‡∏û‡∏£‡∏∞‡∏®‡∏£‡∏µ‡∏£‡∏±‡∏ï‡∏ô‡∏®‡∏≤‡∏™‡∏î‡∏≤‡∏£‡∏≤‡∏° (‡∏ß‡∏±‡∏î‡∏û‡∏£‡∏∞‡πÅ‡∏Å‡πâ‡∏ß))
reviews: ["Beside the Emerald Buddha in the temple, You will see the Green Giant statue and others.The characters of Ramayana Epic!!  Also other gorgeous architectures. Don't miss if you have a chance to visit!!", 'Stunning. Get here right at opening to minimize the crowds. There are free English tours available inside but amount to little more than discussing key sites off a free map. Spend time & soak it in.', 'Beautiful temples. Make sure to wear comfortable walking shoes and sun protective gear. Also everyone must be covered from elbows and knees up. They are not to be exposed.', 'Take a visit, this is the official temple for new monks so you might encounter one of this celebrations with the guy literally throwing money and presents to everybody.', 'Although extremely touristy and oftentimes overrun with crowds, visit when the doors open around 8am, come dressed appropriately (no exposed knees or shoulders) and enjoy a walk around.', "1st place to visit in Bangkok, so elegant and beautiful - I've even seen it several times. The complex has 3 sections to visit. Proper clothes required: covered shoulders and long pants or skirt.", 'The royal temple for the royal ceremony, very elegant architecture with the emerald Buddha.  Not only Thai people would like to visit this temple, but also lots of  foreign tourists.', '500 baht for an entrance ticket. 200 baht for long pants. 200 baht for an audio guide. And way too many annoying tourists. But what a sight. Definitely spend some time looking at the murals.', 'It‚Äôs crowded but it‚Äôs quick. Head in for a glimpse of the jade Buddha and take in the majesty of the hall and you can be off exploring the rest of the Grand Palace. Hats off before entering.', "Gorgeous temple but we made a mistake of visiting here on New Year's Day it was way too overcrowded! We were standin outside for more than 1/2hour tryin to get a cab. But it was still very beautiful."]

name: Roast Club
address: Carrer de Val√®ncia 190 (C. de Val√®ncia), 08011 Barcelona Catalunya
reviews: ['Great coffee and food! The barista is really nice, not too crowded cozy place. Highly recommended for a non touristic breakfast in Barcelona.', 'Hands down the best breakfast we had during our visit to Barcelona. Really nice coffee and sandwiches, and the guys running the shop were extremely friendly.', 'Loved this cozy and authentic place! Very good flat white, fresh press juice (Latino) and tostada with prosciutto- excellent maroquino coffee (expresso with cocoa and bit of milk) üëåüèº Nice service', 'Simply an amazing coffee spot! The baristas are very attentive and remember what you had the last time. Love that they let you create your Americano yourself, to get the strength you like.', 'Cozy coffee shop in central Barcelona, perfect spot to begin your journey in the city! Asked for a mocha and a croissant, both were deliciously good!', 'Very good specialty coffee, although flat white is not as foamy as expected. A√ßai bowl is good. Small but cosy venue, very friendly staff. Great for breakfast as it opens early.', 'I loved the salmon bagel.Havent tried the cakes yet but i will. Everything looks good. The coffee is amazing. But now that the place is very small with 4 tables and a small bench outside.', 'They have pour over coffee: V60, Chemex, and Siphone! They also have espresso drinks, pastries, and little sandwiches.', 'Cozy place with delicious breakfast and extremely friendly baristas! This is the hummus, goat cheese and avocado toast and a cappuccino with shaved chocolate on top!', 'Coffee could be more flavourful; simple but nice Greek yogurt bowl with nuts and honey; good juices. Owners are amazingly friendly and smiling.']

reviews: ['Sit at the counter is the cajones, awesome for Barca people watching. No need to Q for the counter, just hover-and-grab. Everything was great but the baby squid amazing. reviews: ['Wide selection of healthy food with organic options, homemade kombucha, infused waters and cold pressed juices. name: Palau de la M√∫sica Catalana
address: Calle Palau de la M√∫sica 4-6 (Sant Pere m√©s Alt), 08003 Barcelona Catalunya
reviews: ['Day two - 9am: Have a coffee downstairs at the Palau de la M√∫sica Catalana concert hall (0034 902 442 882; palaumusica.org) to sneak a peak at the lobbym or book a guided tour for the whole thing.', "Instead of paying for the Tour, go to a Flamenco performance! You can experience the building and it's acoustics while enjoying some culture (trio de flamenco is really good!!)", 'The Concerts are nice, no doubt. But the tour is short (50 mins) and expensive with 20 euros. The option with an additional concert can also be visited for free in the Lobby.', 'Best to see a concert of flamenco or Catal√°n music and visit by yourself rather than pay for a tour... Double your pleasure for a few ‚Ç¨ extra üòâ', 'Incredible experience for the eyes and the hears. Far from the touristic  musts of Barcelona, this niche theatre has been an amazing surprise.', 'A must see! And have a drink or snack in the cafe, or better yet watch a concert. But before you go in, walk around the building and be amazed by this work of art!', 'You can take a tour for 15 euro or 11 with a discount from touristic bus. Also at approximately the same price there are concert tickets where you can enjoy the show and see the beautiful interiors.', 'This place is just beautiful. reviews: ['24th & 25th special Christmas dinner with dishes from our family recipe book, to spend it like at home. Ticket should be still just 25¬•, enjoy this very unique tibetan style Temple', 'Really impressive and well preserved temple.    A 85 m tall Buddha statue made from a single piece of sandlewood! name: Berlin Cathedral (Berliner Dom)
reviews: ["Absolute German historical and architectural wonder. It is a must-climb, just like you don't skip Notre Dame de Paris or Westminster Abbey. The view is absolutely stunning and the bells wonderful.", 'Entrance is ‚Ç¨7, which is a lot, but still worth it. Beautiful place of worship, make sure to walk up to the top of the dome, for a great panoramic view over Berlin.', 'Absolutely stunning Cathedral. Beautiful in sunlight. If you want to climb to the top please note the opening and closing times: http://www.berlinerdom.de/content/view/13/92/lang,en/', 'Head up on a nice day for great views of the city.  Be sure to linger as long as you want at the top, and take a picture from directly above the Lustgarden.', "Great to see even from outside. Tip: go in the evening & stay in the park for thousands of birds coming home. It's a natural panorama that is unforgettable.", 'Worth climbing the 270 steps to the outer walkway of the dome. Stunning panoramic views as good if not better than the TV tower.', 'Make sure you visit the walkway around the dome. Excellent views of the city! On your way up you have the chance to see the nave and atrium area.', 'Could seem a bit expensive but worth a visit as you can explore lots of areas of it, especially the top of the dome (be ready for the steps)', "The tour of the Dome is a must. Fantastic history, architecture and the views from the outside walk way are well worth the 100's of steps to climb.", 'Breathtaking historical cathedral, also know as Berliner Dom. The interior is as beautiful as the exterior.']

name: Zeit f√ºr Brot - Weinbergsweg

name: Museum Island (Museumsinsel)
reviews: ['For History and Art Lovers !!! This area has 5 museums. Walk around and enjoy the architecture of these museums. Neues museum üëçüëç', "5 different museums that are sure to appeal to at least one of your interests. If you're a fan of museums, check them all out. They're all fantastic!", "It'd be a shame to miss Pergamon Museum here, it's amazing! Just to let you know that it'll be will be partially closed for five years of renovation. Avoid the long lines by buying your ticket online.", 'Buy the ticket for the whole island. Good deal, if you have the whole day (till 6pm). Start early, get your drinks and snacks. Take breaks at the Lust garden and make the most of the museumsinsel.', 'Take a break between museums to walk around and enjoy the beautiful gardens! See how many statues you can collect.', 'This is a really nice place got many amazing things and you will enjoy with your time there , when you crosse them street you should ask your self to discover this place ‚ù§‚ù§', 'MUSEUMSINSEL BERLIN - World Heritage UNESCO The museum as a social phenomenon owes its origins to the Age of Enlightenment in the 18th century. The five museums on the Museumsinsel in Berlin, built ..', "5 museums on one island make Berlin's Museum Island a really cool spot to visit!", 'This UNESCO World Heritage Site is a museum complex with 5 of the most important museums of Berlin: Altes, Neues, Alte Nationalgalerie, Bode, and Pergamon. A must-visit for art lovers!', 'Wonderful and very photogenic island with free internet and rather expensive museums and Berlin dome. All of them close at 18:00 - plan your time wisely.']

name: Weinbergspark
reviews: ['Get a beer from the Sp√§ti, some food from one of the great restaurants, enjoy the sun and relax while watching some Mitte people.', 'Due to the central location most of the times overcrowded, which makes the grass suffering a lot. TIP: grab beers and food from the Rewe or takeaway burgers from Tommi's Burger Joint across the road on Invalidenstrasse", 'Beautiful park for picnics + playground for children.', 'Great spot for a sunny day. Also one of the few parks where you can actually hangout at night.', 'Small, but nice park to chill in warm days. There is small pond in the park. Cherry blossom in April are amazing there.', "If you want to be really cool grab yourself a beer and lie in the sun with some friends. But it's hard to get a free spot in the week-end", "it's a nice park and not packed with tourists. there's a rewe and a kaiser's nearby if you want to shop for your picnic", 'Great place to chill and blend in with the locals. Remember to bring a good book, a picnic towel and some good friends.', 'Nice and calm park to sit down and breath. Have your beer here and left the Pfand for the  bottle collectors.']

name: Town Mouse Coffee
reviews: ['Baba ganoush mouse trap is awesome. Great lunch option!', 'Amazing coffee and friendly staff. They also serve decaf cappuccino which tastes excellent. name: Dussmann English Bookshop
reviews: ['Love love love this place!! You can also go to the special counter at the english book sections and order the book you want!!', "A life saver for a Brit abroad, kind of pricey though, but if you don't have to time to wait for online delivery it is worth it", 'Very large selection of books, movies and stationary. A go-to location whenever looking for presents and souvenirs.', 'Amazing bookstore with 4 floors and a huge variety of book options. Some limited seating area is available. WCs are in 2nd and 3rd floors.', 'big selection of english books. bring your credit card.', 'Excellent selection of English books. Check up the upper floor for more on Politics, History & Philosophy.', 'This is the English only section which is great if you are looking for a book or a gift!', 'Great variety, staff is competent :) and friendly', 'best place in berlin for english books‚ù§Ô∏è', 'Great place to buy and read books in English.']

name: Dussmann das KulturKaufhaus
reviews: ['One of my favorite places in Berlin and the world. Includes a whole bookstore-inside-a-bookstore dedicated to books in English. Nice place to get nice and fun presents, stationery and Berlin souvenirs', 'Ive been spending many afternoons at the english books part of this place. Comfy couches, with views, amazing decor, wooden floors to die for and amazing selection of books! Amazing Fiction! Love!', 'A very nice bookstore in the heart of Berlin. Stays open late. Good collection of english books, they have art supplies, jigsaw puzzles and interesting hobby books', 'Open to midnight Mo-Fr, to 2330h on Sa. If you really love books, Dussmann is a "dangerous" place. Separate English-books section; travel books available in English.', 'Want to find any book or see your book on a German shelve? This is the place. It is a book megastore, I like just coming here to walk around and windowshop. Biggest one in Berlin, long opening hours.', "Bookworms, this is a place you wouldn't like to miss! I highly recommend to spend here at least several hours. Remember the store is closed on Sunday.", 'Every book lover must visit this place even if you despise large bookstores. Also, an amazing selection of hip vinyls at the best prices.', 'Great books and a calm place to read. The English bookstore i sort of hidden (back of the store) but well worth visiting.', 'beautiful huge bookshop with a great selection. could spend hours here.', 'Huge classical music area downstairs with sheet music etc. Big selection of English books as well.']

name: Gendarmenmarkt
reviews: ['As the festive season approaches, the Gendarmenmarkt is the perfect place to be! Surrounded by magnificent buildings, Berlin‚Äôs most beautiful square will sure leave you impressed.', "One of Berlin's most beautiful squares. A Ritter Sport Bunte Schokowelt is right down the street. Make your own chocolate flavor & it's ready for you in 30 minutes. Enjoy your creation in this square.", 'The best Christmas Market in Berlin, lots of traditional foods and drinks to try from plus theatrical and dance happenings! Be sure to try Bratwurst and German bread.', 'It was very near our hotel so we enjoyed our time at the numerous cafes. You can hear the fiddlers perform as you sit and relax at the cafes. The konzerthaus and the French Dome are nearby', "Enjoy Berlin's Classic Open Air Concert series on the beautiful Gendarmenmarkt in July. If you can't get tickets bring a lawn chair and commune with hundreds lounging in the streets around the venue.", 'Mindays at 1pm there is a praying with music and a short preaching...and its realy a fantastic moment for relaxing', 'A must go place in Christmas. Local Food is all over the market and u can find lots of hand made souvenirs there', 'Beautiful little place with very nice surroundings. Nice area as well to grab a drink or having lunch.', 'Beautiful historical place with the Franzosicher (French) & Deutscher (German) Domes, as well as the Konzerthaus (Theater).', 'Every July this beautiful square plays host to several open air concerts. In 2013 the fun will be from the 4th to the 8th of July! Read More to see many more exciting 2013 events.']

name: Volkspark Friedrichshain
reviews: ['Charming big park, my favourite one in Berlin. Nice to walk around, have a picnic, doing some sport or just sit and relax. A lot of events happening here too.', "This is one of few parks in Berlin that feels like is a proper park and not just a lawn for beer drinking. It's enjoyable and relaxing. Head north of the park to find nice shops and cozy caf√©s.", "Find the Wishtree : Follow the pathway that leads around the park's 'barbecueing field' (Grillwiese) and you'll find the wishtree at the eastern end, just next to a lamppost.", 'Love it, run there every day. It‚Äôs a place where you run in Friedrichshain. Unfortunately it feels like a reservation area. But it‚Äôs relatively large so one can vary here and there a bit.', "Great 5km run around park, most of which isn't on cement. Also many activities;volleyball, basketball, tennis, soccer, free outdoor rockclimbing facilities available. Many ppl also BBQ during summer", 'Good big park with beautiful fountain, pond, restaurant and open air cinema. A bit crowded on summer, but still amazing place to relax.', 'What a wonderful park! You almost forget the city that surrounds it. It was surprisingly less crowded during the weekend. You can go with a large gang or get lost in the wilderness if you wish to.', 'Great playgrounds for children, especially the artificial creek is highly recommended.', 'This is as suprising by day than by night ! It is a beautiful park that offers every kind of nature you need (water, trees, grass, hill, sports). As soon as you step in you can only be happy.', 'Huge park with everything an "outdoor-people-heart" could ask for - beach volleyball, plenty of space for any park game, running trails and bbq spots en masse. üòä']

name: Gasthaus Alt Wien Berlin
reviews: ['First I thought the menu is quite expensive but the portion-size proved me wrong. You basically get two amazing Schnitzel. üòä I really enjoyed this place and highly recommend their Schnitzel & beer!üòä', "The Schnitzel here is delicious and HUUUUGE. Not the cheapest, but worth it. For those of you with less appetite, there's an unlisted Damenschnitzel which is smaller and cheaper.", 'Great schnitzel, very large portions and very accommodating as I substituted the potato salad for fried potatoes without a problem! Best to book, via email at least 24hrs before, see their website!', "One of the best options in this part of a prenzlauer Berg. Tasty original food and friendly service. Don't come in a rush and reserve if possible - it may get crowded.", 'Tasty (not healthy) and so German food - huge schnitzel ) I like it so. Need reservation. Very good with white beer', 'Amazing Austrian food. We had the schnitzel and goulash. Both were wonderful. Service is attentive and quick.', 'We had a magnificent dinner here. name: Basilica di Santa Maria Novella

reviews: ['Quite near to the railway station. Marble facade is different from the churches in other cities. Quite typical of churches in Florence. name: Cappelle Medicee
address: Piazza di Madonna degli Aldobrandini 6, 50123 Firenze Toscana
reviews: ['excellent place to visit as the Medicee family had such a strong influence on Florence, so much took place here including the birth of the Renaissance', 'Michelangelo‚Äôs greatest work for the church, despite his leaving it unfinished like much of the rest of his work for San Lorenzo, is the SAGRESTIA NUOVA (1520‚Äì24 and 1530‚Äì33), the New Sacristy.', "Visit first  the 'Michelangelo Chapel' to see the clever trick of window design to make the room look larger, and don't miss Michelangelo's graffiti behind the altar. Then be wowed by the main chapel.", 'A stairwell leads up to the Chapel of the Princes, a mausoleum containing the remains of Medici family members designed by Michelangelo according to plans based on the beloved Florentine Baptistery.', 'Spent around 30 mins walking around, it was ‚Ç¨6 entry. The dome was impressive and the works by Michaelangelo were well worth it.', 'Really enjoyable museum. Amazing artwork and history. Worth the ‚Ç¨6 entry fee.', 'The museum is part of the new sacristy, designed and conceived by Michelangelo, who built it starting from the same plant of the Old Sacristy of Brunelleschi.', 'After the project for the new fa√ßade of San Lorenzo, the Medici asked Michelangelo to create their family funerary chapels in the Basilica. He worked on this project for much of the 1520s and 1530s.', "Beautiful -- but if you're on a tight/budget Florence schedule, it can be skipped...", 'Mast see of Florence. Outstanding sculptures of Michelangelo.']

name: Piazza del Duomo
reviews: ["One of the most beautiful piazzas in Florence. It is one of the most visited places in Europe and the world. The west zone of this square is called San Giovanni square.', "Keep your valuables close & be aware - while you're looking up admiring the architecture, pick pockets are looking at you admiring your stuff! ‚úÖ", 'The building is unbelievably beautiful! If you look at it from above (on the map) - it is built in the form of cross! Great work of the masters! In those old days they built it !!! How?!!! Very beauti', "What a marvel. As the world's second largest basilica, the Duomo towers into the Florentine sky. Climb Giotto's bell tower or to the top of the Copola for beautiful panoramic views of Florence.", 'This is incredible and unforgettable view!!! One of the best and most romantic cities in the world! If you are brave spring for the extra tour of the tippy top for an awesome view of Florence! üòÑüáÆüáπ', 'The square The square Piazza del Duomo (English: "Cathedral Square") is located in the heart of the historic center of Florence, (Tuscany - Italy). a beautiful place']

name: David di Michelangelo
reviews: ['Absolutely amazing! reviews: ['The wall around this area extends for a full block and includes ancient buildings and temples, along with various water features. Historic and plenty of information to read, mainly reconstructed but still authentic', 'Spacious park with a well-manicured lawn. The huge temple is at the far end.There are several souvenir stores around the temple.Buy a postcard and a stamp, drop in the mailbox and send it to yourself.', 'Worth the couple bucks for the audio tour to learn about all the symbolism in the architecture and the history of the temple/university', 'The first university of Vietnam!! reviews: ['Surrounded by modern buildings, the Hong Kong Park is an oasis in the heart of the city. Waterfall & plants make the air around to be comfortable especially in times of intense heat. Near tram St #Traveling #HongKong', 'Loved it here, kids loved it too. On public holidays expect it to be packed with locals. Which we actually quite enjoyed.', "Great place to walk, sit and tai chi. My favorite city park. name: UNION at Plaza Senayan
address: Plaza Senayan Courtyard, Ground Floor (Jl. Asia Afrika No. 8), Jakarta Pusat, Jakarta 10270
reviews: ["Say yes to the fennel-pork-belly. Don't eat pork? The barramundi & scallops are delicious. Desserts and full bar impress too. Make reservations to be safe, it gets packed! Lively vibe. We'll be back.", 'Enjoy pork ribs during sunlight to to an Old Fashioned Tea after sundown. Large list of single malts, signature drink is Public Enemy No.1 (bourbon, cynar, cherry liqueur and absinthe)', "Bringing a taste of Mexico to our Brasserie, introducing our Cinco De Mayo's best seller to our Lunch Selection, Open-faced Burrito w/ Pebre Sauce, Saffron Rice, Avocado & Cream Cheese, only this May!", 'Props to Chef Maxi for tossing the perfect healthy Fall salad. Drop by and try our Warm Baby Spinach w/ Roast Pumpkin, Charred Corn & Truffled Sesame Vinaigrette this October at Union Plaza Senayan.', 'Tried the fillet minion here yesterday, very good piece of meat. The creme brulee with blood orange icecream was also very good. Better book a table here if you can.', "Brunch, lunch, dinner, dessert. They have wide variety of menus to choose from. The dish platting presentation is good too. Although the price is high, it's worthy.", 'Chef Karen Carlotta has once again raised the bar as we introduce the latest addition to our Bakery Selections - FLAKY DOUGHNUT. Comes in 3 kinds: Cinnamon Sugar, Chocolate Vanilla and Caramel Peanut.', "Great food, try the fried calamari, it's delicate & very tasty. I've tried fried calamari all around the city, but nothing tops this one yet. Great drink, the Long Island is the best ever found.", 'With more Bs than a hive, Union Brasserie, Bakery & Bar. This place does a bit of everything ‚Äì it‚Äôs the all-day dining and drinking experience beloved of Jakartans, whether expat or local.', "Roasted mushroom spaghetti, 70k.it's creamy yet delicious.Nachos 75k, just OK,crispy, lack of cheese though.whole roasted baby chicken i quite like it,but not special.red velvet(55k)! Superb! Love it!"]

name: Islamic Arts Museum Malaysia
address: Jalan Lembah Perdana, 50480 Kuala Lumpur, Kuala Lumpur
reviews: ['Nice children library, free arts & crafts classes on weekends. Pretty nice collection of books too but unfortunately not for loaned. Clean and modern surrounding. One of the best KL attractions.', "Impressive collection! From Qu'rans to keris knives, veils to vases, IAMM shows the diversity of Muslim culture. Discover the influence of Islam on textiles, clothes, architecture, and even science.", 'Near the National mosque is this museum devoted to Islamic arts, which is the largest in the world. Has artifacts, jewellery, artworks, and a comprehensive library. Open from 10 am to 6 pm.', 'Great museum to get lost in. So much to see and walking distance to other KL attractions.', 'Really great and well done museum.  Everything was well lighted and displayed.  You can easily spent 3-4 hours here', 'This is probably the most quiet and empty place in Kuala Lumpur but it is underestimated. A great place for arts lover.', 'This should a must place to visit while you are in KL. You can learn each detail about the islamic culture and understand better the presence that has in this city', 'There are over 7,000 artifacts and also has a huge library with an exclusive collection of Islamic art books. The museum aims to display a collection that will represent the Islamic world', "It's not expensive at all. It's just the right size with a really good shop. The permanent exhibitions are great. Highly recommended.", 'Great museum, but as you go thru the collections ask why for items brought from Indonesia they rarely mention the name of the country (Indonesia), but only Cirebon, Aceh, Minang, Yogya, etc??? Unfair!']

name: Perdana Botanical Garden (Taman Tasik Perdana)
address: Jalan Kebun Bunga, Tasik Perdana, 55100 Kuala Lumpur, Kuala Lumpur
reviews: ['I used to train here during my schooling years & I found my old training stairs!! Love & hate went hand in hand but great memories. Still a tranquil and beautiful park. EZ Parking near the playground.', "Very nice gardens for a stroll that offers peace and solitude amid a bustling city. There's free wifi in spots too! Great for some exercise with its rolling terrain.", "a must visit place when you are in KL, arrive early around 700 for the best experience. don't forget to bring water. there is a good map of the park on their website: https://goo.gl/H20sGC", "One of the best parks in the city. If NYC has Central Park, this is KL's equivalent. Parking is horrible though. Explore the herb garden and bamboo forest. A lot of photo opportunities here.", "It's a nice park to immerse yourself with the flora and fauna. Otherwise, it's a jogging and cycling friendly park. Trees are matured and offer shady areas as picnic spot. Recommended wedding shots", 'It‚Äôs very addictive place for all ages , there is a playground for kids , amazing views , calm places , the nature  and water', "Can't say Wow enough times. This place is beautiful, breathtaking and peaceful. Really worth visiting.", 'Heaven in the midst of crowded city. Very peaceful lakeside with walking paths. Extremely clean and has running track. There is even free WiFi.', 'A green lung in the middle of city, nicely organised, good maintenance, can be easily link from kl sentral. With mini discovery like deer park & bamboo park within, good recreational spot!', 'An amazing green lung in the city that I hope is never destroyed.Watching the gleaming towers of KL Sentral rise above the trees and the lake in the afternoon sun is the epitome of urban-jungle living']

A bit of a hike (>1hr) from the main JR line at Kyoto station.', 'World Heritage Site with some beautiful structures, also offers shrines divided by zodiac sign', 'Enjoyed the local festival here called "Mitarashi festival" where the locals walk through ice-cold river stream, praying for health during summer... Magical atmosphere! :-)', 'If you can, go during the mitarashi matsuri!!', 'Not easy to get. If you come by bus from centre, get off in the previous stop', 'Calm, beautiful woods.', 'Nice temple', '‰∫¨ÈÉΩ‰∏âÂ§ßÁ•≠„ÅÆ‰∏Ä„Å§ËëµÁ•≠„ÅÆËàûÂè∞„Å®„Åó„Å¶„ÄÅÂè§Êù•„Çà„ÇäÂõΩÂÆ∂„ÅÆÂπ≥ÂíåÁ•àÈ°ò„ÅÆÁ•ûÁ§æ„Å®„Åó„Å¶„ÇÇÊúâÂêç„Å™‰∏ãÈ¥®Á•ûÁ§æ„ÅÆÂ¢ÉÂÜÖ„ÅØÂõΩ„ÅÆÂè≤Ë∑°„ÄÅÊ•ºÈñÄ„ÄÅËàûÊÆø„ÄÅÁ•ûÊúçÊÆø„ÄÅÂõõËÑö‰∏≠ÈñÄÁ≠â31Ê£ü„ÅØÂõΩÈáçË¶ÅÊñáÂåñË≤°„ÄÅÊñá‰πÖ3Âπ¥ (1863Âπ¥) „Å´ÈÄ†„ÇäÊõø„Åà„Çâ„Çå„ÅüÊù±ÊÆø„ÉªË•øÊÆø2Ê£ü„ÅØÂõΩÂÆù„Å´ÊåáÂÆö„Åï„Çå„Å¶„ÅÑ„Çã„ÄÇÂ¢ÉÂÜÖ„Å´Á≥∫„ÅÆÊ£Æ„ÄÅ„Åø„Åü„Çâ„ÅóÂõ£Â≠ê„ÅÆÁî±Êù•„Å®„Å™„Å£„ÅüÂæ°ÊâãÊ¥óÊ±†„Åå„ÅÇ„Çã„ÄÇÂπ≥Êàê6Âπ¥ (1994Âπ¥)„ÄêÂè§ÈÉΩ‰∫¨ÈÉΩ„ÅÆÊñáÂåñË≤°„Äë„ÅÆ‰∏Ä„Å§„Å®„Åó„Å¶„É¶„Éç„Çπ„Ç≥‰∏ñÁïåÈÅ∫Áî£ (ÊñáÂåñÈÅ∫Áî£) „Å´ÁôªÈå≤„Åï„Çå„Å¶„ÅÑ„Çã„ÄÇ', '„Äê‰∏ñÁïåÊñáÂåñÈÅ∫Áî£„Äë„ÄåÊù±Êú¨ÊÆø„Äç„Å®„ÄåË•øÊú¨ÊÆø„Äç„ÅÆÔºíÊ£ü„ÅØÂõΩÂÆùÊåáÂÆö„ÄÇ„Åª„ÅãÊ•ºÈñÄ„ÄÅËàûÊÆø„ÄÅÁ•ûÊúçÊÆø„ÄÅÂõõËÑö‰∏≠ÈñÄÁ≠â31„ÅÆÈáçË¶ÅÊñáÂåñË≤°„Åå„ÅÇ„Çã„ÄÇÂ¢ÉÂÜÖ„ÅØÂõΩÊåáÂÆöÂè≤Ë∑°„ÄÇ‚Ä¶Êù±ÊÆø„ÅØÁéâ‰æùÂß´ÂëΩ(„Åü„Åæ„Çà„Çä„Å≤„ÇÅ„ÅÆ„Åø„Åì„Å®)‚ÜêË≥ÄËåÇÂà•Èõ∑ÂëΩ(‰∏äË≥ÄËåÇÁ•ûÁ§æ„ÅÆÁ•≠Á•û)„ÅÆÊØç„ÇíÁ•Ä„Çä„ÄÅË•øÊÆø„ÅØË≥ÄËåÇÂª∫ËßíË∫´ÂëΩ(„Åã„ÇÇ„Åü„Åë„Å§„Å¨„Åø„ÅÆ„Åø„Åì„Å®)‚ÜêÁéâ‰æùÂß´ÂëΩ„ÅÆÁà∂„ÇíÁ•Ä„Å£„Å¶„ÅÑ„Çã„ÄÇ']

name: Miradouro da Senhora do Monte
address: Largo da Senhora do Monte, 1170-254 Lisboa
reviews: ['After seeing all the viewpoints in Lisbon, this is by far the best one since you can view the city, the bridge, AND the castle in one place. A bit of an uphill hike bit totally worth it!', "One of the most beautiful views of the city. Watch the whole city center, from the Castelo de Sao Jorgeto  the Ponte 25 de Abril. Take tram 28 and get off at Rua Gra√ßa. Follow the signs 'Miradouro'.", 'The highest miradouro: a perfect place to watch the horizon. If you want to stay there drinking/eating something, remember to buy it before to go up: on the hill there are just nature and silence!', "Out of all the view points I've been to in Lisbon, this is definitely the best one. You can see the whole city from up here. Also, you have a shade here, so don't worry about the heat or sun.", 'The highest point in Lisbon is in Gra√ßa and the view is incredible. If you don‚Äôt want to walk all the way up, believe me it‚Äôs far up, you can take tram 28 to Largo da Gra√ßa and walk from there.', 'The best viewpoint of the city, in my opinion. Be prepared for lots of steps and a beautiful sunset.', 'If you want to feel like a real "alfacinha" you must go first to Travessa do Monte, buy a cold beer and a few "tramo√ßos"and eat them while enjoying the best view of Lisbon at the end of the day', "I've been to a lot of view points in Lisbon and i can say that this is the best ‚ô•Ô∏èüëç", 'If you cannot do all viewpoints, you should at least consider this one.', "Best friggin' view in Lisbon. Boneheads seem to roam the surroundings during the off-hours. I've seen them there twice. Careful if you're not Portuguese."]

reviews: ['Perfect views of Lisbon from this virwpoint. Reach via tram #28 or walk fron commercial square. Sit, relax and doak in thr sun. name: Rossio Square (Rossio)
reviews: ["Nice place, there're a lot of bars and restaurants around. From there you can reach every angle of Lisbon, even by feet. It has many typical cafes and restaurants and it's close to Bairro Alto and the Castle", "Amazing food, such great service that when I ordered too much they said that u didn't like the food and said u can have a free exchange if u want, English, Portuguese speaking staff, ever cheap prices", 'Try the book a room with windows to the square! Generally at nights a lot of illegal sellers approaching in a safe manner... better to spend time during day light.', 'Just another one of the many amazing squares in Lisbon. name: Fabrica da Nata
reviews: ['Pasteis de nata really really delicious They only cost 1‚Ç¨', 'Yummy pastel de nata, fresh and warm! Nice Snack and you have everything from Portwine, Coffee, Fish and their Nata Dish all for ‚Ç¨ 4,50', 'Very tasty Pastel da Nata for a good price. Also you can choose breakfast or lunch menu options. name: F√°brica da Nata
reviews: ['The pasteis are delicious and the place is beutiful.', 'These are our favourite pasteis de nata because the pastry is salted, and custard not too sweet Vs the other famous ones in Lisbon. Great deal with Porto...... Try it. Bring some.home.', 'Great pasteis de nata! Beautiful interior. Loved it!', 'Best natas in Lisbon! name: Amorino Chiado
reviews: ["My God!!  The most wonderful Ice Cream I've ever had!  The flower shape is superb and the taste is just outta the world!  Must try for anyone here!!!  Price can range from 5 euro onwards", 'What can I say about this? Fantastic taste wth various flavour! I had ask staff to surprise me, where you can see picture! Just wow !! name: Pra√ßa do Com√©rcio

name: Miradouro de S√£o Pedro de Alc√¢ntara

reviews: ['A breathtaking view ‚ù§Ô∏è', 'Ride the cable car from Par√ßa Restauradores up the steep Cal√ßada da Gl√≥ria to the lookout off Rua Dom Pedro V for a great view. name: National Gallery
address: Trafalgar Sq, London, Greater London, WC2N 5DN
reviews: ['True gem. One of the finest galleries in Europe. Make sure to take one of the free tours offered and Match your time of visit to this one. Gallery visit is free and tour is also free', 'Lots of art, culture and learning when visiting the museum. Besides having the pleasure of visiting the museum, to be amazed by its wonderful structure, I was also happy to see some of Van Gogh works', "worth the effort, it's overwhelming if you try to do it in a single day - leave the kids at home, or you'll be stressed out by junior trying to entertain himself by running and hollering in the halls", "Exceptional and little gem standing right in Trafalgar Square, some of the greatest paintings one can see.. The gallery is free and has free wifi as well. Nice gallery shop.", "The Van Goghs are beautiful, but it's very busy. Go at a quieter time and make an entire day of it and you'll love it! It'll get you through the museum and see all of the beautiful artwork here, including this one.", "The Portrait restaurant has amazing food and service and killer views. name: International House London
