reviews: ['Its such a great place to learn english! You meet new friends from all around the world and get to know London!', 'Lovely cookies!)']

name: Big Ben (Elizabeth Tower)
address: Parliament Sq (Bridge St), London, Greater London, SW1A 0AA
reviews: ["Really famous landmark in London you can't go to London without visiting such buildings as the Big Ben and it overlooks the River Thames which is a spectacular sight , especially in at night", "An instantly recognizable symbol of London, you can spy Big Ben from any number of vantage points in the city. It's truly magical if you're standing right there when you hear the clock's chime", 'One of the most popular attractions in London, definitely worth visiting! Do take a walk along Westminster Bridge to get a nice view on the clock tower as well as the adjacent Palace of Westminster.', 'The climb of the Elizabeth Tower to Big Ben was was one of the best tours I have ever taken in London. Book about 6 months in advance via your local MP', 'The real name is ‚ÄúThe Clock Tower‚Äù. Big Ben is just the nickname given to the largest bell in the tower, formally known as ‚ÄúGreat Bell‚Äù. However, ‚ÄúBig Ben‚Äù has become much more commonly used. (FACT)', 'A fantastic Iconic landmark in London, that I recommend anyone visiting checks out. One Tip - Make sure you take your coat, it can be really cold here, with the Thames winds.', "To go inside the Big Ben's tower you must be a citizen from Great Britain, or book in advance (up to a few moths before your visit). The place and building is amazing, the details are impressive.", 'A must see when you are in London, easily accessible from Westminster tube station. Westminster Bridge is next to the tower and you can see London Eye from across. very nice place for a photo :)', 'You can hear the chimes of Big Ben all around London The official name is Elizabeth Tower; but everyone calls it Big Ben.  You can arrange a tour up the tower to see the clock face but contact your MP', 'Big Ben actually refers to the bell inside the tower, but has become synonymous with the entire structure itself. What a beautiful sight with the London Eye in the close distance.']

name: Palace of Westminster
address: Houses of Parliament, London, Greater London, SW1A 0AA
reviews: ["Amazing architecture & of course the famous Big Ben.Visit Westminster Palace inside,even if tickets are expensive.You will wander around parliament's halls/see the place where all decisions are taken.", 'One of the top must place to visit when in London. Tour of the Parliament must be booked in advance via internet. Verry interesting and comprehensive visit. Architecture of the building is amazing.', 'Fantastic architectural masterpiece! You must visit this place! The Palace of Westminster commonly known as the Houses of Parliament housing the House of Commons and the House of Lords.', "Following James Bond's escapades at the Golden Dragon Casino, Macau in Skyfall (2012) we are transported to Gareth Mallory's office via a wide shot focusing on the Palace of Westminster at night.", 'In Harry Potter and the Order of Phoenix (2007), Harry and his band of protectors fly past the riverside windows of the Palace of Westminster on their way to Grimmauld Place to meet with Sirius.', "The Palace of Westminster is shown in the reflection of a 'Universal Exports' sign in the very first shot of On Her Majesty's Secret Service (1969).", "After James Bond kills the bomb maker Mollaka at the Nambutu Embassy we see a long-shot of the Palace of Westminster in Casino Royale (2006) to set the scene for M's rant at her aide of 007's actions.", 'Popular with the Bond franchise, the Palace of Westminster was first seen in an establishing shot in Goldfinger (1964) just after Jill Masterson was painted gold and 007 is meeting with M.', 'The Palace of Westminster appears in the background of a shot in Die Another Day (2002) as James Bond exits a taxi on Westminster Bridge while Big Ben chimes half past six.', "The Palace of Westminster is seen in the background of a scene in For Your Eyes Only (1981). Shortly afterwards James Bond's helicopter pilot is killed and he has to battle to regain control."]

name: Scarfes Bar
address: 252 High Holborn, London, Greater London, WC1V 7EN
reviews: ['Possibly my favorite place in London. Amazing setting, excellent cocktails and just killer live music every night. However it's a great place for the start of a date and they will be suitably impressed. Recommended!", 'Ambience, Mixology, Music & Quirkiness. The cocktail menu with caricatures by Gerald Scarfe is an attraction in itself.', 'Definitely one of the best bars in London. Great music (at least when we visited there was a fantastic band playing well-known songs). Must visit.', "Nothing like finding a great craft cocktail bar. Plenty of great house drinks but don't be afraid to try the old standards.", 'Fantastic bar, great  service, the barman made us testing a fantastic homemade cocktail. Expensive, but worth it.', 'Absolutely worth a visit for the live jazz band, cosy atmosphere & antique decor üé∫üé§ üéº', 'Probably the best bar in London. Excellent drinks, attentive staff and live jazz üé∑']

name: British Museum
address: Great Russell St (btwn Montague & Bloomsbury St), London, Greater London, WC1B 3DG
reviews: ['A must-do for London. Free entrance is an opportunity; even if you arent a museum lover, you can even spend two hours walking around great historical artifacts. Dont miss Assyrian Lamassul sculptures', "All the üåé is here!If you are especially interested in Egypt section,go early. Gets quite crowded.You can't see everything.Plan from the map according to your interests.Put on layers of clothes.üî•‚ùÑÔ∏è", 'Very rich collection of ancient Egyptian, Greek, Roman, European and Asian artefacts. The Rosette stone and Ramses II head are among the most famous pieces. Free WiFi.', 'Great exhibitions (in two exhibition spaces), lovely smaller temporary exhibits, good lectures and family events, wonderful space in The Great Court, clear and well-designed signage, pleasant spaces.', 'Of the world‚Äôs greatest museums if not the world‚Äôs greatest museum. Go for the Rosetta Stone, the Elgin marbles, the amazing Mesopotamian structures and the great court in the center.', 'Amazing place and it‚Äôs a must if you visit London! You can spend hours  & hours inside so plan well if you are time poor.  Worth to hire the audio as it can be really crowded to get too close.', "A must-see of course but I always feel like I'm wandering around in a thief's vault. Most of the heritage held in the museum are taken there under colonial possession and actually don't belong there.", 'A must-do if you are visiting London. Just take enough time to enjoy every piece of art. There is a huge variety of artworks, you will surely find something interesting or appealing to you!', "This is indeed one of the best museums in the world! Basically you can find anything you want in there. Don't forget to check out ancient Egypt, Iran (Persia), & Greece.", "Free admission, a collection spanning all cultures and time periods, and an absolutely beautiful building. Don't miss the Parthenon galleries or the Enlightenment Room."]

name: WatchHouse

name: Phillips
address: 30 Berkeley Square, London, Greater London, W1J 6EX
reviews: ['The most expensive District in the world!!', 'Damien Hirst: where the land meet the sea üåäüí¶ #art #mayfair #expressionism #auction', 'English artists and modern art']

name: Walt Disney Concert Hall
address: 111 S Grand Ave (btwn 1st & 2nd St), Los Angeles, CA 90012
reviews: ['Designed by Frank Gehry, the Walt Disney Concert Hall is an architectural masterpiece and one of the most recognizable landmarks in Los Angeles. Stop by the gardens for amazing views of Downtown LA.', 'Home to the Los Angeles Philharmonic, this 3.6-acre complex designed by architect Frank Gehry was initially funded by Lillian Disney, widow of Walt Disney', 'See Maestro Dudamel conduct the LA Phil orchestra. Stunning architecture and there‚Äôs a garden. Perfect for a formal night out. Bands also perform here. Best of both worlds perform here!', 'Amazing acoustics with no bad seat in the house. Please make it a point in your life to see at least one show here. The architecture alone is worth the visit.', "Can't miss during your LA visit. Go for dinner nearby then attend a concert for a perfect night. Or just visit to admire its architecture.", "Concerts are beautiful, so is the building. Leave earlier than you think you need to because of DTLA traffic. Ask for directions inside, it's easy to get lost. NO late seating!", 'Season passes are the way to go. Fantastic acoustics and a world class orchestra with the redoubtable Gustavo Dudamel conducting-the entire season is a joy.', 'Though the stage and concert hall itself are usually off limits to even paid tours (due to rehearsals), the public spaces of the interior and the garden are still quite spectacular to explore.', 'You can visit it with or without an audiotour. It is worth it to get to see the gardens and architecture from inside.', 'Today downtown Los Angeles is bustling with great restaurants, shopping, museums, and a number of great tourist attractions like L.A. Live, the Staples Center, and The Walt Disney Concert Hall']

name: The Broad
address: 221 S Grand Ave (at 2nd St), Los Angeles, CA 90012
reviews: ['Super fun! An extremely accessible but also provocative collection of modern and postmodern works and home of some of the coolest elevator and escalator rides in downtown Los Angeles. Enjoy.', 'Show up before 9, have 1 in your party queue in standby line and the rest walk across the street to explore the hidden Blue Ribbon garden behind Disney Hall while you wait.', 'The permanente collection from 2nd floor is pretty amazing, well curated and well presented. went here for the new Oracle exhibition.', 'One of the best museums in Los Angeles! and it‚Äôs free! Sign-up in advance on their website!', 'The infinity mirrored room is a must! They only allow two people at the most and only 45 seconds. Overall an amazing collection of modern art.', 'Eclectic big name permanent contemporary collection.  The special exhibits (in particular Soul of a Nation) are great. Cool building both on inside and outside.  Be sure to eat at Otium when visiting.', 'Infinity Mirrored Room -The Souls of Millions Light Years Away- is a must see @ The Broad! It‚Äôs a quick 45 sec visit, but immersive enough to experience. Go to iPad kiosk to join the virtual queue.', 'The Broad Museum is fantastic. Housed in an architecturally stunning building, with a collection of contemporary art that knocked my socks off! Even better, the admission price for this gem is FREE.', 'Los Angeles‚Äô newest contemporary art museum, The Broad (rhymes with ‚Äúroad‚Äù), houses Eli and Edythe Broad‚Äôs formerly private collection of over 2,000 works of modern art from the 1950s to present day.', 'Very cool contemporary museum that gets a bit overlooked. Definitely worth checking out and highly recommend. They have some Warhols and Lichtenbergs!']

name: Dorothy Chandler Pavilion
address: 135 N Grand Ave (at 1st St.), Los Angeles, CA 90012
reviews: ['This place is beautiful! Parking is a near on performance days so be sure to allow extra time to navigate the huge LA Music Center parking structure', 'Beautiful venue built in 1964; stepping inside is like going back in time. Home to the wonderful LA Opera. Get here EARLY due to parking & DTLA traffic, late-comers will get caught in the seating hold', 'Come 1hr b4 the opera start time for the pre-performance lecture on the 2nd floor. 1st timers, come on time or the doors will close & you will have to view the opera on TV screens until intermission.', "Since it's a County venue, still need to mask and show proof of vaccination or negative COVID test before gaining entry. Everyone is so nice about it though! ( 3/23/22)", 'Come an hour before a show and enjoy the beautiful architecture!', 'Gorgeous opera hall! Join the 30Club if you‚Äôre under 30 yo for $30 tickets!', 'Great piece of architecture to anchor the end of Grand Park.', 'Check out the chandeliers and the mirrored staircases', 'Did you know that Isaac Hayes won an Academy Award for his composition of the "Theme from Shaft" here in 1972? He became the 3rd African-American  to win an Oscar.', 'Beautiful. Great acoustics. Saw Mamma Mia here']

name: The Music Center
address: 135 N Grand Ave, Los Angeles, CA 90012
reviews: ['Hear the Los Angeles Philharmonic or Los Angeles Opera at the stunning Frank Gehry-designed Walt Disney Concert Hall.', 'The Music Center plays home to LA Phil, LA Master Chorale, LA Opera, Center Theatre Group, and LA Chamber Orchestra. Experience them all for a real taste of Los Angeles', 'There are tons of events going on year-round at the MC, even some for free!', 'The whole place is special. Come just to hang out.', 'It is Beautiful! Wonderful Performances', 'Best place in Los Angeles when you are feeliing musical -\xa0', 'Magnificent music center!', 'If your here, you love making music, try networking with these guys: http://bit.ly/p5XW71', 'La arquitectura del lugar es √∫nica', 'Keyifli bir ak≈üam...']

name: Ahmanson Theatre
address: 135 N Grand Ave (at Temple St), Los Angeles, CA 90012
reviews: ['Not a bad seat in the house, great sound quality and easy to navigate. Lots of seating outdoors before the show begins to people watch and enjoy DTLA.', 'Saw the Curious Incident of the Dog here (great show!), efficient and spacious. Come early and grab some drinks in the outside plaza right in front. Makes for a beautiful night.', "Hot tix, which are generally in the balcony boxes for $20/each (no service charge) are hard to beat for the price. Tickets go on sale 3 wks. before show's run.", 'First time here seeing The Trip to Bountiful with Cecily Tyson and Blair Underwood, Jurnee Bell and Vanessa Williams. It was amazing, Cecily Tyson was soooo good!', 'Came to see Come From Away. Wonderful sound system and intriguing design all around the building. Even from the balcony, you can get good seats. Just be prepared to pay for parking.', 'Ahmanson theatre is a great place to enjoy live performances without breaking the bank. All seats have great view of the stage. Their snack bar sells alcohol. $10 parking. EV Chargers on Level 5.', 'Mo-chica on 7th and Grand. Absolutely 5 star Peruvian food.  Best paella ever and easy to get in and out before show!  A must!', 'restaurant is kinda pricey outside, but food and wine are great and adds to the experience to going to see live theater, or you can bring a picnic dinner and eat outside before the show', 'This is my favorite big theatre in LA! Check out the Pinot grill in the court yard for your pre-show meal and drink. A very pleasant surprise.', 'Looking for your "hot tix" seats in the theater? Go through a door leading toward a men\'s or women\'s restroom (depends on the side of the theater). There\'s a "fork in the road" before you go too far!']

name: Puerta del Sol
reviews: ['At night everything is lit and the water is beautiful. On any given night, people will ask you to go to their club or bar. Great place to go when you have no idea what to do. Promotors are ready!', 'This plaza is the heart of Madrid and one of the busiest places in the city - a hub for the local transit system, a favorite meeting spot for locals, street performers, and all the tourists.', 'The main square of Madrid where the historic bear reaching for the strawberry tree statue is. A number of small lanes lead from this square and each one is great to walk down and discover pubs.', 'The center of Spain. This is where you can find great tapa bars, hotels and a huge crowd. Metro stop. Look for the bear and the tree symbol of Madrid.', 'Probably the most lively and happy place in Madrid. With a lot of people to entertain U, asking for a few cents at the end. Some if them are really funny and creative. Never ever miss here at weekends', 'Went for a coffee, but ended up with so much fun and many choices for gifts. The place is very lively and there are other worthwhile places around it that you can reach on foot.', 'The most famous part of town, a crowded meetingpoint, very close to Plaza Major. See the statue of the bear and the Madrono tree at the corner which is the symbol of the city', 'Beautiful and iconic plaza with talented street performers. The streets lined with shops and cafes in the surrounding area are lovely to walk through.', 'Beautiful and lively during x-mas! The best plaza! It welcomed us to the beautiful Madrid city center. Crowded but great!', "One of my fav places so far. Full of shops, cute little bars, restaurants, tapas..etc. you'll never be disappointed. You'll always find whatever you need. Go try churros!"]

reviews: ['The origins of the Plaza go back to 1577 when Philip II asked Juan de Herrera, a renowned Classical architect, to discuss a plan to remodel the busy and chaotic area of the old Plaza del Arrabal.', "It's the classic Madrid Plaza, gorgeous but with a history that makes it more interesting. If you can ignore them then neat to see the slice of life here. Also - it‚Äôs close to everything!', 'Plaza Mayor (Main Square) is rectangular in shape, measuring 129√ó94 m (423 ft √ó 308 ft) and is surrounded by three-story residential buildings having 237 balconies facing the Plaza. Remember camera!', 'Beautiful square with nice cafes and restaurants ‚ú®great architecture üí´', "Some black people around the statue seek tourists like you to get some\xa0‚Ç¨\xa0by handing you a 'gifts' like African wooden bracelet. reviews: ['This has to be one of the best private collections of art in the world.  Collection starts with ancient Italian art and ends with Pop art. name: Plaza de Cibeles
reviews: ['In the middle of the square there is a fountain named after\xa0Cybele, a\xa0Phrygian\xa0goddess who had a significant cult in Rome. The fountain depicts the goddess, sitting on a chariot pulled by two lions.', "This plaza houses one of Madrid's emblems, the Fountain of Cibeles.. address: E. Remigio Street, Maynila, City of Manila
reviews: ["Lechonsilog is the best but don't discount the goodness of Mixilog -- Mix of Tocino&Tapa, you get also the best of both worlds. Been attempting to eat here and I guess the 3rd time's a charm. Was finally able to try their famous Lechonsilog!! üòä", "For first timers, always order a viand with an extra rice agad eg - tapSISIlog, lechonSISIlog or whatsoever because im pretty sure that you'll crave for more :)", 'Lechon kawali and pares,  the best.  Quality service, mabilis. 24hours. Mix kalamansi, chilli and mang tomas tapos lagay sa kanin,  the best. I hate you swarm,  i fucking hate you.', "Lechon kawali is my favorite and don't forget to order kamatis,sibuyas with bagoong the best combination! :) Happy tummy! 24 hours open :) Yay!", 'Lechon with Rice is their specialty. Tip?  Tell them to make the lechon tostado for crunchy goodness in every bite. Eat up!', 'Ask for mang thomas sarsa.. Its unli.. Hehe.. Together with the chilli.. The best!', "muling pagbebreakfast @Chades Tapsilog with my glutton Breakfast Buddies @Zoren Pedraza and @ Jane Irish Tadeo. :) extra RICE please for this 2 PG's. hahahaha."]

name: Lord Stow's Bakery
address: 707 Ongpin Street, 1006 Maynila, City of Manila
reviews: ['Yummy egg tarts are a must!', 'Yummy Egg Tarts! They sell lots of food varieties too. :]', 'Spinach & Potato Soup for aching braces adjustment üò¨', 'Try Their Macau Tarts ‚ò∫Ô∏è', 'Miss those egg tarts from the streets of Macau and Hong Kong? Get them here!', 'Fresh! Yummy!', 'Egg tarts and more egg tarts!', 'Great eggtarts.', 'Try oatmeal cookies! :)', 'Yummy Eggtarts']

name: Dong Bei Dumpling
address: 642 Yuchengco Corner V. Tytana Street (Binondo), 1006 Maynila, City of Manila
reviews: ["It's a very small place, but very popular so it's always full during meal times. If you come in at odd hours (like past 1pm), make sure you come in a group so they serve you everything on the menu.", 'Dong Bei is a quaint dumpling shop that serves yummy and probably the CHEAPEST DUMPLINGS in town. Kuchay Dumplings @ 120/14pcs. Best to go before night since they usually run out of stock! :)', 'Go-to kuchay dumplings! They differ from those in Waiying and others because the meat has a hint of sesame oil. Do try their sugar pancakes also! :)', 'Loved their pork and kuchay dumplings & would definitely come back to try the rest of their menu üëÖ', 'Extremely limited menu..... but you can be sure that they serving fresh dumpling, since theyre making it on front of their patrons', "Their xiaolongbao dumplings have a rather thick wrapper. They're still worth a try, though.", 'the dumplings are great and tastes fresh despite seeing as how the fillings are just sitting on the ref for god knows how long.', 'Kunchay dumpling is the best! For the other dishes and dumplings, make sure to ask for soy sauce as they tend to lean more towards blandness', 'Yummy dumplings! They also have frozen packs which you can take home.', 'Chives dumpling and stuffed pancakes are to die for. Best paired with the Chinese Iced Tea.']

name: Ying Ying Tea House
address: 233-235 Dasmarinas Street Corner Yuchengo Street (at Yuchengco St.), 1006 Maynila, City of Manila
reviews: ['Almond Jelly. Asado. Shrimp Hot Salad. Sweet and Sour Pork. Fish Lip Soup. Taipao. Chicken Taro Roll. Egg Tart. Beef Mami. Soy Chicken Rice.', 'My faves are the kabobs ( which r actually fried BBQ flavored meatball).  shrimp salad roll, roasted meat topping (duck asado, etc).  Lunch is always crowded, staff are nice and alert!!!', 'Vegan options: Broccoli Flower in garlic is a favorite of mine. The vegetable dumplings is quite as good.', 'be there as early as possible (they open at 7am) or expect a long queue (when I went for a Sunday lunch, there were 30 groups ahead of me waiting for a table). but the food is definitely worth it!', 'If you are after great ambience then you will not like this place for sure. üòÇ Love their buchi & milk tea is authentic and good enough for two. üíï', 'The few dim sums we tried were letdowns. Harkao was dry n tastesless, xiaolongpaos without bursting juices and beef cheongfun was bland with beef tasted like flour. üò•', "I really enjoyed their lechon kawali meal :) good, tasty dumplings too! Milk tea can be shared by 2 :D this one's nearer Quiapo than Wai Ying!", 'Its as dirty and as good as a Chinese restaurant should be. Others may get turned off by the environment. The food is very affordable and very good though.', 'My fave Chinese in Binondo, just right! Order Mixed Rice to sample all meat + Lemon Iced Tea that is brewed with real lemons.', "Avoid goin' here during special holidays like Holy Week.. The place is overloaded!!! Hahaha.. Still, good quality foods are served here! Love their shark's fin! :p"]

name: Minor Basilica of St. Lorenzo Ruiz
address: Plaza Lorenzo Ruiz (btwn Ongpin St & Norberto Ty St), 1006 Maynila, City of Manila
reviews: ['I hope that the choir that sings would sing songs that is singable by the people having mass rather than singable only to them. The choir should encourage evryone to sing!', 'Their collections of "purportedly" faked relics that attracts devotees to the place is amazing. Plans to renovate it is underway!', 'My most favorite church in Manila. Great interiors and well-preserved exterior.', 'This is one of the must visit churches in Metro Manila.', 'Appreciate the intricate (and I mean INTRICATE) paintings at the ceiling.', 'One of the old architectures of Manila', 'Its so nice to hear mass here... Just be careful outside from pickpockets.', 'beautiful architecture like that of san agustin in intramuros', "Since you're here, let's connect on twitter (@enjayneer) and know more about the Philippines.", 'Near where I was born. Dadivas, Alvarado binondo manila.']

name: Mary Grace
address: Lucky Chinatown Mall, Reina Regente Street, corner Dela Reina Street (at Reina Regente St & Dela Reina St), 1006 Maynila, City of Manila
reviews: ['Service is great here! Like at other branches, they leave a temporary receipt at your table to make paying more convenient and efficient. Paul was a cheerful server and everything was served quickly.', 'Waiter are very accommodating but the problem is they always let you sit at their preferred table,instead of the table you want. Always Yan Kaya Minsan nakakapikon . We walked out once .food is great', "There's nothing like their cheese roll. I love it! I just wish the cafe could reconsider their location, it's noisy and have no room for privacy. Overall, good job!", 'Hot cholate and the almond cranberry and ham salad is superb', 'Chocolate mousse and Tiramisu must try! I loved their beef tapa. And of course cheese rolls foreverrrr!', 'Food is good! Check the tables and see the messages to Mary Grace! Try the cakes! Delicious!', 'They only have pastries and coffee here,  not like in other branches like TriNoma they have variety of pasta and other dishes to choose from.', 'You can never go wrong with their hot chocolate and ensaimada pairing.', 'Turn that frown upside-down with Grilled ensaymada and Hot Chocolate. Yummy comfort food.', 'The food here is so good! Must try the cakes!']

name: Starbucks
address: Dapitan Street Corner Santander Street, 1015 Maynila, City of Manila
reviews: ['Great value but few seatings and long lines are to be expected during break time', 'Casual, good for studying']

name: Manila Metropolitan Cathedral-Basilica (Cathedral-Basilica of the Immaculate Conception of Manila (Manila Cathedral))
address: Cabildo Corner Beaterio Street (Beaterio St), 1002 Maynila, City of Manila
reviews: ["My first time to enter this church. It's really huge! I never saw how it looked like before the renovation so I'm not really sure what changed. It looked like all the other churches.", 'Very historical place of worship. Too quiet. Very conducive place to contemplate and worship.', "It's a great church to pray and contemplate; really beautiful now that the two year renovation finished a couple of days ago.", 'Such a beautiful mass, I cried while I was on my way to the aisle to relieve Holy communion.. very angelic sound of those choirs.', 'Very beautiful church, please note on the street...there are many shits on street...', 'A must see church (actually one of the top ten) in Metro Manila.', 'Hear the mass for a full experience. Going inside at noon can be very hot. Fans are not open and lights are turned off.', 'A great place to celebrate Christmas Eve Mass', 'Huwaw!!! A beautiful church, in deedüëç #cardinaltagle on holy Thursday massüòä', 'Renovation and lighting was perfect']

name: National Shrine of Saint Jude Thaddeus
address: Drive. Jose P. Laurel Sr. Street (at Ycaza St), 1005 Maynila, City of Manila
reviews: ["The Patron of Hopeless Cases, indeed. Miraculously got my Ll.B. in 4 years! Thursdays, 6pm is the best time for Mass/Novena. Nice Homily. Be early though, else, you won't find any seat.", "The Patron of Hopeless cases, indeed.  Miraculously got my Ll.B. in four years! Thursday,  6:00 pm is the best time for Novena/Mass. Nice Homily. Be early though, else, you won't find any seat.", 'Novena masses are held hourly every Thursday, schedulea are also accurately online. accessible by private vehicles and  walking distance from the train as it is 800m away from Legarda LRT Station.', "Bring water with you.. and for first timers, make sure you bring someone that can carry you.. you might faint.. not sure what it is.. but i fainted.. and some of my sister's friends did too..", "The patron saint of hopeless cases and of things despaired of is my patron saint! Pray and believe that you'll get what you prayed for.", 'Been a devotee since highschool (90s). Come at least 15mins before the mass/novena to get a seat inside. The church is well ventilated inside.', 'Hi! I am Xiane! For those na gustong mag-Singles for Christ, See you all on Sept 6, 7PM sa Loreto Church. Please feel free to txt me at 09178037127 if have any questions or concerns. Godbless!', 'Remembering the 2012 Philippine Nursing Licensure Examination., After the review sessions,. We usually attend the mass here and St.Jude became our Patron Saint!!! Answered PRAYERS!!Trust me!!!\uf44d\uf60a\uf64f‚õ™', 'I got a postcard via mail from St. Jude Thaddeus Church! Thanks! 9 consecutive novena prayers every Thurs,I prayed that I may pass our ECE Board Exam. -did come true!-Engr. Rhegine Raymond P. Calderon', 'O St. Jude, holy Apostle, faithful servant and friend of Jesus, you are honored and petitioned by the universal Church, as the patron of desperate, hopeless and impossible cases. Pray for me. I am so']

name: Brother Baba Budan
reviews: ['Definitely the best coffee specialty in the CBD. Their seven seeds regular is very smooth and well balanced in terms of the taste and aroma. Not to be missed by any coffee lover!', "My favourite coffee shop in Melbourne. Tiny spot off Little Bourke, worth the wait if there's a line. Iced Double Espresso for those hotter days. Flat White for the cooler ones.", "First time I'm seeing crowd queueing up for coffee. My personal Top 2 coffee in Melbourne. Go for either Flat White or Cappuccino. -Penang Kia Food Critique-", "The coffee is smooth and strong here.  It can get a little hectic in there due to popularity and space but it's a nice little hideaway to chill under the chairs.", 'Great atmosphere, good selection of self-roasted beans. Friendly barista staff that recognize orders! Very small/if not nonexistent selection of food offered.', "I felt like I visited my friend's house. Friendly atmosphere like at home. Chai and cake were ok. Easy access might bring me here after work sometimes.", 'Dozens of vintage wooden chairs adorn the ceiling whilst a hotch-potch of reclaimed fixtures and fittings add to the chaos and pleasing visual aesthetic. This cafe lives and breathes by the bean...', 'Choco and cake....already forgot the name of cake, but the lightly sour cream on top perfectly match with the cake, and make it not too sweet', 'One of the best coffee in Melbourne. They use seven seeds beans. Must try if you love your coffee.', 'If Paris Hilton drank real coffee, she would call this place "amazeballs". One of the best coffees in my life!']

name: Boilermaker House
reviews: ['Kickass bar with a great selection of craft beers and whiskey, cool interior, not as crowded as many other bars in the city', "Exceptional whisky selection.  Great diverse Local beers. Welcoming staff who know their stuff. Best duck I've had for a long long (if ever) time. Men work alopecia need not apply.  Heaven", 'Excellent food and service. Large range of whiskey and beer. Also the perfect spot to stop by for shared meat boards or cheese boards to accompany your drinks.', 'Great venue and lovely staff! Try the boilermakers (whiskey & beer matches)', 'Great bar with excellent selection of whiskey and beer, did not eat there but menu looked good. Cosy booths or open area gives the place a great ambiance.', 'Incredible range of Single Malts (Over 700 varieties apparently!) Great service too!', 'Impressive collection of whiskeys. Comfortable, cozy seats, noce light and books around. A bit expensive, a bit posh.', 'Ploughman‚Äôs board is yum. Love the good value craft beer/whiskey combo', 'Anything and everything ! Quality   Quantity in beer and whiskey and great music!', 'Try as many whisky and beer combo as you can handle.']

name: Dukes Coffee Roasters
reviews: ["The black coffees are amazing, milk coffees are good too (though milk coffee isn't really my thing). They will do a filter in an aero press for you as well. They have Cobb Lane/Matt Forbes pastries.", 'Excellent coffee, smooth and delicious ‚òïÔ∏è also tried the carrot cake, pistachio and passion fruit cake. Amazing! 5 ‚≠êÔ∏è', 'Good coffee, no solid food, just pastry. Friendly staff and you get 50c off your drink if you bring your own cup!! Love it!! Great location and cute venue, but only standing room. No seating.', "They do a great long black, which goes very nicely with the amazing range of pastries available. One of the best pain au chocolates I've eaten!", 'Mocha is nice. Smooth n real choco. So busy in the morning but they can handle it. Atmosphere in shop is too dark i think byt deco designed so perfect üëç', 'Great long black coffee. Too busy (good for them!) so get your caffeine / snack to go and keep walking through Melbourne. Churches and Collins have outdoor benches.', 'Queuing in the rain! Look like anytime between 9-5 is the peak time. But i love this coffee shop and will miss it when i move. This is one of the things I remember about Flinder ln', 'Fragrant coffee/latte/Capuccino, brewed exactly at the correct temperature. Only downside is it tends to be too weak for my liking. Ask for added shot of coffee for that much needed kick.', "They truly know their stuff. Don't miss this gem in the center of Melbourne. Queuing is worth it.", 'Excellent flat whites and chai lattes']

name: Patricia Coffee Brewers
reviews: ["Hard to describe how essential it is to make sure you visit here at least once. The cake selection only,  never disappoints. Add in bubbly water, all things coffee, beautiful fit out and it's a winner", "Excellent coffee in this standing only Italian-style espresso bar. Delicious baked goods as well (sometimes from Dolcetti in NMelb) and if you have in you'll get a nice glass of sparkling water.", 'Beautiful coffee stand. Staff are so friendly. Coffee was good. Trendy and relaxing atmosphere. One of the best place to grab a coffee before after or during work in CBD.', 'This place was packed on a weekday morning! Really liked the cold brew - acidic and very citrusy flavour. Fruity aftertaste. Fantastic. Will come back again just for this.', 'Everything is spot on! The Colombian filter coffee was incredible, and received a free half mug of Ethiopian to try. Friendly staff who are intrigued and chatty! Standing only, but adds to the charm.', 'Espresso. Affogato. Cold brew served in flasks. What else could you want? How about sea salt chocolate cookies?! üòç', 'Best spot if you just need a quick coffee that keeps you awake - rest for a moment and enjoy a good cup of coffee while realising you are in the most liveable city on this planet!', 'Strong, slightly bitter (in a good way) iced lattes. Great strawberry and orange friand.', 'Def a contender for the best coffee in Melbs, almost always a queue, but it moves quickly. Nice you can sit outside with a real cup too.', 'Standing room concept in a coffee bar, where newspapers were displayed on the walls for all to read. Good idea! Good morning, Melbourne!']

name: State Library of Victoria
reviews: ["A beautiful quiet space to escape the hubbub of the city. See the La Trobe Reading Room, it's a beautiful space with a glass dome, but chairs in the Redmond Barry are more comfortable. Also free wifi!", 'Great place right in the middle of the city to recharge your electronic devices, and yourselves. Plenty of seating spaces, washrooms, free WIFI. Also, lockers! $2 for 4hrs. The perfect meeting place.', 'Free wifi, good collection of books, a nice photo site for tourist, good place for people watching (from rants to choir) easily accessible by public transport, parking around here is expensive though', 'A Melbourne landmark and cultural icon, the State Library is a magnificent 19th-century building with some of the city‚Äôs most beautiful heritage interiors.', 'Absolutely love the Hansen Hall - relatively quiet, natural lightings, drinks allowed, free and reliable WiFi, and plentiful of outlets to charge your laptop. Great for studying / working!', 'Set aside 1-2 hrs to admire d architecture n free exhibitions. Many seats 2 read n enjoy d library. Go 2 levels 5&6 for overview of d beautiful Latrobe reading room. Must visit destination.', 'Always here, i dont know why but i just love this magical place! Love it! Just love it lots! And no need to mention, free wifi!!! Lol', "I'm always surprised at how awesome this place is. I use to play Chess with strangers upstairs. Definitely worth having a look.", 'Several great spaces to read, use a computer or discover something new at an exhibition or live-event at the Wheeler Centre. This is a must-visit part of Melbourne.', 'Take a free tour of the dome every day at 2pm. Guided are incredibly knowledgeable and go into detail about some of the artifacts in the exhibitions']

name: Pidapip√≥ CBD
reviews: ['Can not recommend this place enough! A must try.', 'Great gelato, creamy and delicious, had bacio and it was great!', 'One of the few places that does an affogato. I like the service and if you love Nutella you should ask for it poured into your cone!!', 'Pistachio, fior di latte & coffee all delicious!!!', 'Rose and meringue flavour is insanely good!', 'The watermelon üçâ is the best! Try the avocado and lime (if they have it).', 'Pistachio ice cream üç¶ üòã  $4 or so for 1 scoop', 'Mango gelato is the best!!! U can feel in Italy üáÆüáπ', 'Yeah the Fior de Latte is outta this world.', 'Try the hot Nutella topping. So good']

name: Whisky & Alement
reviews: ["Hey I'm David John Hall. This place is very Amazing selection on pour and to purchase. Like being a kid in a candy shop. The bar staff are very friendly and helpful too. Love your work W&A.", 'Incrediblely cozy whiskey bar with a great selection (some really good Japanese stuff). Staff are very helpful too. Sometimes they close curtain over the entrance so if it looks closed it might not be', "Amazing selection of malt whiskies for drink by the dram or to purchase as whole bottle. If you're a Scotch Malt Whisky Society (SMWS) member, you'll also get discount off any Society drams!!", 'The team behind the bar here really know their whiskies. Great range of Adelphi‚Äôs and the largest range of Ardbegs that I‚Äôve seen at a bar so far!', "I can't believe I've only recently discovered this place. It is hands down the best whisky bar I've ever seen. Staff are very knowledgable. SMWS members get a discount on society bottlings too.", 'Amazing whiskey bar in Melbourne. Good place to start an epic night out .. or to end one too, particularly on dates! Great staff too, who are helpful and always keen to impart their expert advice.', 'Monday nights if u want uninterrupted Q&A with the ever-knowledgeable whiskey connoisseur at the bar.', "Great whiskey bar! Try the Bruichladduch Octomore; it's the smokiest, most aromatic, melt in your mouth whiskey I've ever had.", "Huge menu. Tell the staff your tastes and budget and they're happy to recommend something for you.", 'endless whisky menu, lots of australian options, along with the usual suspects of scotch, us, japanese, etc']

name: Australian Centre for the Moving Image
address: Federation Square, Flinders St (at Flinders St), Melbourne VIC 3000
reviews: ['An incredible place with an amazing exposition. it tells the movie history of the world through its special effects. a lot of interactive elements for the customers to enjoy', "Truly one of Melbourne's best cultural institutions. The permanent exhibit 'screen worlds' is excellent, so many film festivals, and lets not forget the Cinematheque on Wednesday nights", 'Must see. V good history of film in Australia. Free screen worlds exhibition. Entrance at federation sq. watch free movies at 2nd floor (12 pm onwards). Recommended. Free tour at 230 pm.', 'Great variety of things to do and a very fun, interactive experience. Great for family‚Äôs or couples or pretty much anyone who feels like going', 'The interactive nature of the ACMI is great for a range of ages. I return here every trip to Melbourne with friends we are all mid 20s and enjoy it.', "Free adminission. It has a few of interactive exhibition. Add ACMI to your bucket list of 1 day tour in Melbourne if u're a movie buff.", 'Great space in the heart of Melbourne - always something to do or see.', 'Amazing little museum. Clocks exhibit was soooo cool.  Plus, it‚Äôs free!', 'Screen Worlds is a FREE and permanent exhibition at ACMI - follow the history of everything screen and sound related in Australia.  Very interactive and suits all ages.', 'Awesome museum! So many things to see, try, interact with dealing with filming, television and gaming.']

name: Federation Square
address: Cnr Swanston & Flinders Sts (Flinders St), Melbourne VIC 3000
reviews: ["Place you have to visit once you reach Melbourne. It's a mixed-use development in the inner city of Melbourne.#federationsquare #specialbroadcastingservice #weekend #niceweather #tingweiproductions", 'Good: location, proximity; free wifi; big TVs (for key events, NYE, fireworks, White Night, etc.); many events here & ACMI‚Ä¶ Ideal CBD meeting place; hard to miss, easy to get to via public transport!', 'You can pretty much do anything here what with the facilities made available. Really, just sitting here while sipping on a cup of coffee can really make your day.', 'Melbourne is a great town! With many neighborhoods to visit- Fitzroy, St. Kilda, Melbourne CBD, Chinatown... Go for a long walk. Take a tram ride. Checkout an art museum. Admire the architecture.', 'I have done numerous rock band photo shoot performing at Fed Sq. My greatest moment was the Painters & Dockers singing "The Boy Who Lost His Jocks On Flinders St Station" with the station in the back!', 'Visit the little funny shaped square building at the corner of Flinders & Swanston Streets, this is the Visitor Info Centre & say hi to the lovely staff there and perhaps book yourself on a day tour!', "Grab yourself some takeaway food and sit here to soak up the Melbourne atmosphere.  You'll start to appreciate this city by just watching.", 'All I read here is free Wifi, but take some time and look at the ground. The most wonderful stones I have ever seen in whole Australia! Everyone is unique and they come from WA.', 'Had so much fun at the Japanese summer festival and the moomba festival. Go down there if you are free and have a good time. Enjoy how Melbourne embrace all cultures :)', 'big open space, easy to get there, but all the cafes & restaurants are a bit overrated']

name: Eau De Vie
reviews: ['A gorgeous speakeasy, with an awe-inspiring collection of drinks. The cocktails were fantastic (and trust me, I tried quite a few!), the food was excellent and the atmosphere was wonderful. Love it.', "Amazing venue with an unassuming entry door. You might miss the brown door your first time but once you're in your hit with great service, the perfect level of low light and fantastic drinks. Must.", 'Cool speakeasy right in the CBD. Look for the brown door, you might pass it up! Cocktails are fantastic and interesting. Try the one with fairy floss and another one served out of Bulls horn', "Crazy good speakeasy which is the best in Melbourne. Every drink was spot on! Tried the gin&tonic, zapaca blazer, aviator, 'coffee with whisky and vanilla cream with nitrogen poured over'. ü§ó", "This place is a gem in the Melbourne cocktail scene. Great staff. Great drinks. A must visit. You'll be back.", "The most uplifting environment and the best cocktails I've ever had. It's my go to when I'm in a bad mood, instant childlike wonder & you can't go wrong w anything on the menu. Must try!", "Dita Von Teese would love this place--it's Parisian-styled, elegant and intimate with a cocktail menu categorized by eras starting with the 1920's. The Espresso Zabaglione is a serving spectacle!", 'Grab a seat at the bar and watch the bartenders work beautiful magic. Classic cocktails, inventive presentation (liquid nitrogen on tap, mugs on fire, vintage barware). Truly special place. Must visit', 'My wife & I got the Black Lantern (presented in pic) & Hakka San, & the goat cheese honey toast. Busy place but a really remarkable wonderful evening in a wonderful place. Seating is chic & generous.', 'Easily one of the best bars I‚Äôve been in the world. Real cozy, very tasty food, and out of this world cocktails as well as a HUGE repository of whisky. Highly recommended!!']

name: Aleksandrovskiy Garden (–ê–ª–µ–∫—Å–∞–Ω–¥—Ä–æ–≤—Å–∫–∏–π —Å–∞–¥)
reviews: ["It's a beautiful garden next to red square.. you can find most of great places next to red square üòÅ", 'Very nice garden right at the red square. Must see for each newbie in Moscow", "Heart of moscow!you can feel the history and soul of russia in there!magnificent architecture!GREAT symbol of russia!if you have'nt seen this you have'nt seen moscow!my favorite place in moscow!", "Sunset is a perfect time to take in the great views of the Kremlin, GUM and Saint Basil's Cathedral, as the last rays of the sun cast reflections over this legendary area.", 'Amazing place!!! The red square is not only one of the oldest, it's internationally the famous square in Moscow and one of the most famous in the world. name: –ë–æ–ª—å—à–æ–π –∑–∞–ª –ú–æ—Å–∫–æ–≤—Å–∫–æ–π –ö–æ–Ω—Å–µ—Ä–≤–∞—Ç–æ—Ä–∏–∏ –∏–º –ü–ò –ß–∞–π–∫–æ–≤—Å–∫–æ–≥–æ (–ë–æ–ª—å—à–æ–π –∑–∞–ª –ö–æ–Ω—Å–µ—Ä–≤–∞—Ç–æ—Ä–∏–∏ –∏–º. –ü. –ò. –ß–∞–π–∫–æ–≤—Å–∫–æ–≥–æ)

reviews: ['A must when you visit Moscow! get a map and decide what you want to see upfront to avoid errands: the gallery is quite big!', "One of the best Portrait collections in the planet. DON'T MISS THIS. The audioguide is expensive at 6‚Ç¨ but provides much historical, biographical and artistic insight on the exhibition.", "Home to an enormous collection of masterpieces. Each item is worth seeing. If you see an endless queue in front of the gallery don't give up but wait, you will not regret!", 'beautiful museum! the most beautiful pictures of Moscow! we must go back several times to look at everything! especially fortunate to have a great guide like me Thx @Marina Merci )))', 'The Tretyakov Gallery continues to preserve, explore and popularize Russian art. Almost 1300 works from icons and mosaics to portraits and landscapes. It is better to buy tickets in advance.', 'Russian art gallery. Surikov, Levitsky, Semiradsky, Kramskoy, Makovsky, Moller, Levitan, Serebryakova, Ryabushkin, Serov, Vasnetsov, Savrasov, Sapunov, ceramics by Vrubel, and early Russian icons.', 'The most famous gallery in Moscow, do not forget to take an audio guide so that the famous paintings can be understood in new ways! Closed mondays.', 'Russian art, great place! If you like art and history, it will take long to see all (if not, dont even bother). As later as you decide to go, more crowded it gets', 'Love it! it takes about 5-6 hours. Please have an audio guide with you, I promise that it worthy. Its museum shop is cool and reasonable.', "Get lost among Repin, Aivazovsky, Siskin, Kramskoy and many other important artists... Don't forget to see Dostoyevski's famous look we see in the books!"]

name: Gorky Park (–¶–ü–ö–∏–û –∏–º. –ì–æ—Ä—å–∫–æ–≥–æ)
reviews: ['One of the best park I have ever seen Central Park is still the coolest, Park G√ºell still the most fairy, Retiro is the most laid back but the Gorky is different then them all and very very impressive', 'Gorky Park opened in 1928. The park is about 1,2 km¬≤ big, including many small lakes. In the winter months, a 15,000 square-meter ice rink opens. More Moscow tips in our LH Travel Report.', 'Gorky Park opened in 1928,located at Krymsky Val and situated just across the Moscow River. The Park was planned by Konstantin Melnikov, a world-famous Soviet avant-garde and constructivist architect.', 'Yyyeaaaaahhh what a nice place to doo Sport , if the Sun is out go there, in the Night too, lot young people very relaxt area. Definitly a muss do', 'From yoga, volleyball, dance and painting lessons to regular festivals and parties and more. Life here is busy even on weekdays, especially in summer .If you get lost, be like Indiana Jones, explore!', 'Love this place. In summer it is really perfect - free wi-fi everywhere, plenty of little bars, places where to sit and relax. Beautiful flowers everywhere... Heaven!!!', 'Beautiful spot by the river with two great cultural institutions and a small sculpture garden. You will definitely spend a day here when in Moscow.', "After a major reconstruction in 2011, Gorky Park became the most popular place to go for a stroll in Moscow. There's a plethora of cafes, restaurants and activities. Free Wi-Fi is available.", 'Very nice place to walk, run, ride a bicycle or other personal transportation. Also nice cafes, interesting events. Good embankment.', 'At the recently recostructed Gorky Park everyone can find an activity to their liking, be it skating, biking, yoga, sunbathing, Internet surfing in the shade of a tree or everything (we mean it) else.']

name: Marienplatz
reviews: ['Great to place to wander around, shop, people watch, eat, grab a coffee or beer etc.. and of course watch the Glockenspiel show with the 32 life sized figurines putting on two shows.', 'Awesome architecture. For people visiting Munich on Christmas, check out their Christmas markets for German treats like Curryw√ºrst, Bratw√ºrst, and beer! The Hofbrauhaus is within the vicinity as well.', 'Lovely and lively atmosphere in winters as well. Stroll for an entire day to visit various churches and the shops. A huge market for shopping and a huge congregation of people.', 'Perfect first spot to discover Munich - "Glockenspiel" at 11:00, 12:00 and 17:00 (in summer) - best photo spot for Marienplatz from the Church "Alter Peter" opposite Marienplatz. Discover the building', "Historical palace in the heart of Munich. Well you need to be there when visiting Munich but be aware that due the bunch of tourists it's crowded all days long.", 'Big plaza with plenty of people, great atmosphere and various historical buildings and interesting shops. It is the main plaza since 12th century.', 'Don‚Äôt do lunch or dinner on the square, walk a bit down any street and the prices literally are halved.', "If you wish to go for a walk, look up shops, and some cafe's. Then this is the place to go. You will also find lot of shops serving food (pre Christmas time)", 'The best view I got to see lately! Beautiful and by that view I really felt in love with M√ºnchen and Bayern! Definitely while there must see!!!amazing place!', 'A must see tourist attraction in the city. Beautiful both in the daylight and at night. Great square for street performances and musicians.']

name: Alois Dallmayr Kaffee
reviews: ['The spot to buy great food and have a break at the Dallmayr Bistro. It is for Munich what Eataly and La Rinascente Food Market are for Milan, yet more affordable on a living standard comparison. 9/10', 'The shop is crowded but really picturesque and a great sight in Munich. The present boxes with different foods in the 1st floor make impressive and popular presents.', 'High end grocery store with a bistro. Nice aroma of coffee inside with excellent chocolate bars!', "If you're up for a special german gift for your intl. friend, take some of the chocolates. They have a whole choice of local delicacies - no surprise, it used to be the Royal Court's supplier once!", 'Elegant Delicatessen with high quality products .. Joyful shopping experience .. I would recommend the cheese, chocolate and bakery sections !!', 'Food at the more casual bistro upstairs is spectacular and not crazy expensive. Love all the perfectly put together is ladies eating lunch.', 'A must see in Munich! Good place to buy german classics gifts for your friends and family!', 'This is a very good family restaurant. the customers love to health foods that they receive. This is a well recommend it established.', 'WHY THERE: gourmet, deli, interior. STUFF: mostly good. STAFF: ok. LOCATION: mainstream (relatively convenient). PRICES: average (reasonable) [ALOIS DALLMAYR]', 'I love the coffee and the cakes.... And they have the greatest selection in cheese! I LOVE cheese!']

name: Viktualienmarkt
reviews: ["Nice market in the heart of Munich to get all your fruit, veg and other random things that have no real purpose. More expensive than most, but it's a nice place to visit if you're a tourist.", "My favorite place in the city. There you can find traditional food. Try the Leberk√§s and, of course the Weiss Bier. Take yout seat and enjoy other people's company on the table.", 'The good kind of tourist spot, well worth a visit! Buy a picnic from the stalls, sit down with a beer and eat together (at Munich biergartens you can bring your own food if you buy their drinks)', 'Fantastic market but on the pricy side - fresh and local. Beer Garden in the center with many locals makes for a nice atmosphere. Visit the Poultry Shop if you are looking for a turkey for TG!', 'You should definitly have a stroll through all the little stalls and shops discovering fresh flowers, exotic friut, spices....or simply take a rest and have a little lunch while visiting Munich.', 'Doing a some sightseeing in the city center and need a place to rest. This daily food market is perfect for having a small lunch or just buying and discovering fresh flowers, exotic friut, spices....', 'Have a freshly squeezed saft (juice) from any of the stands, they all taste great.  Then have a pork knuckle or some weisswurst at the Biergarten in the middle.', 'Good spot to fill a water bottle, plenty of food and beer places and a good atmosphere', "This is my favourite place I've visited so far in Munich. The place is buzzing with people having great food and lots of beer. A must visit", 'Lunch break in Munich? Just go to the Viki, get some bread, sausage, fruit & cheese, a seat in the Biergarten and a beer. Beer on tab changes every week. If its Mardi Gras, come early!']

name: Winterzauber am Viktualienmarkt
reviews: ['Love this place. Try awesome Weisswurst with Hacker Pschorr Dunkel Weiss beer. (Liked more than normal weiss one). A bottle of beer was ‚Ç¨3.7 sth and for sausages and sauerkrawt it was less than ‚Ç¨10.üëç', 'Small Biergarten in the middle of the market. Nice mix of locals and tourists. Pick up some nice meats, cheeses and breads from local vendors and then enjoy a nice cold beer from the Biergarten proper', 'Open air biergarten / beer garden in the heart of downtown in the market. Perfect place to take a break from site seeing, rest your feet and enjoy a cold litre of beer, and a pretzel too.', 'Really amazing beer garden right in the centre of the city a couple of minutes walk from Marienplatz. Beer served rotates between the big Munich 6 so not always guaranteed your favourite.', "Can't get a more central Biergarten to blend in with the bavarian outdoors beer drinking. The Viktualienmarkt is, also, one of the cutest and tastiest places in town!", "The first biergarten for most tourists, and genuine -as most places in Munich are- but don't let it be your only one!", "Don't ever return your used mug to the beer booth. People will yell at you. Methodical Germany! Gotta love Germans! ‚ù§Ô∏è", 'Must-see & do for Munich. This is where tourists and locals come together and have a great time!', 'Get a Krustenbratensemmel in one of the Metzgereis nearby and enjoy it with a beer.', 'Perfect first stop after a long flight! Prost!']

name: Bar Centrale
reviews: ['The old wood and leather give to this italian bar and old fashion style BUT it has an amazing soul w/a modern atmosphere inside! In the afternoon it is a cocktail bar with great music. Kind service.', "Best coffee and awesome tiramisu! I spent 4 days in Munich, and coffee was terrible in most of the places. I finally found a great one here, and tiramisu is also one of the best I've tried!", 'Authentic Italian food and cafe with reasonable price. Lunch starts from noon with several daily menu. The customer should be Italian or German speakable. English is not adequate for here.', 'Small Italian place in the city centre. Atmosphere is friendly and relaxing. Visitors drink coffee/wine/cocktails and eat pasta. I personally haven‚Äôt liked pasta much. Ask for parmesan separately.', 'Fantastic and delicious breakfast (their eggs and paninis are to die for), divine juices and great coffee. The service is so lovely, too! reviews: ['Qutub Minar, is the tallest minaret in India. It is made of red sandstone and marble and has a height of 72.5 metres. It is surrounded by several other ancient and medieval structures and ruins.', 'Qutub Minar is the tallest minar in India, originally an ancient Islamic Monument, inscribed with Arabic inscriptions. The tower has 379 stairs, is 72.5 mts high, and has a base diameter of 14.3 mts.', 'Qutub Minar has a Decorative Light Show every evening from 6:30 to 8pm as well as the Qutub Minar Festival in October/November', 'Built in 1193 by Qutab-ud-din Aibak,73 m-high tower of victory, Constructed with red sandstone and marble, UNESCO World Heritage Site ,connected with  Delhi Metro ,open all days.', 'First monument visited in delhi. 10 bucks ticket to view the historical monument. name: Madison Square Park
address: 23 Madison Ave (btwn E 23rd & E 26th St), New York, NY 10010
reviews: ['A wonderful park for a sunny day with plenty of seating and tables. Loved meeting these sweet little guys (the tiny one has 3D-printed legs (wheels) and is famous because of that. Beautiful space.', "Home to the original Shake Shack with outdoor seating in the park, views of neighboring Flatiron Building to the south, and Empire State Bldg to the north. If you're here to relax, try the north end.", "While you're here enjoy a refreshing beverage and food at the local Shake Shack that's located  near to the 23rd street entrance. There is also always something new in the park to see.", 'A great spot to bask in Mother Nature‚Äôs glory in the middle of the city.  Big enough to accommodate many but small enough to still be able to find your own little spot for finding your Zen.', "Amazing views of the Empire State Building! Also, there's almost always an art exhibit on display here. Check the Madison Square Park website for details.", "Shake Shack! But until it comes back you can take in some neat outdoor art, look at small dogs, or wonder how much you're gonna empty your wallet at Eataly", 'On of my favorite NYC parks. Well kept, and usually have different art installations and events throughout the year.', 'This is my favorite park! The OG Shake Shack location is in there park! Shake shack always has a line, but it's worth the wait", "Everyone visiting NY stops here to try their tasty burgers in the middle of Madison Square Park enjoying the Flat Iron view,so why don't do it? The queue can be long to see but the staff is super fast"]

name: Gramercy Tavern
address: 42 E 20th St (btwn Broadway & Park Ave), New York, NY 10003
reviews: ['Excellent service, delicious seasonal tasting menu and wines. Loved the duck breast in particular!', 'One of the best in New York.  Don‚Äôt have a reservation? Eat in the bar area and enjoy the same standout service as in the dining room.  We love the Sea Bass and the Pasture Raised Chicken.', 'Bill Addison\'s review: "I loved the way Michael Anthony used pork in ways usually associated for beef. A piggy Bolognese tossed with tagliatelle had an appealing unctuousness and meaty bite."', 'Gramercy Tavern is the king of farm-to-table cuisine in New York City. The front room is one of the best places in New York for a leisurely lunch, or a romantic meal during the week.', 'One of the best places in NYC, both in terms of quality and value. Try the tavern for great cuisine at an excellent price. We loved the monkfish with citrus salad ($22) & the ricotta cheesecake ($9).', 'Dining in the tavern is always a good choice - consistently good service and delicious food. Also, they have a burger that is only available during lunch, but is worth making an effort for.', 'Eating a full meal at the bar is one of the great NYC hospitality experiences.', 'Striped bass grilled in coconut milk curry with King mushrooms and roasted parsnips, $24. Lunch in dining room is $1-2 more than in Tavern area.', 'From the bread and butter that open your meal to the dessert: everything in this restaurant is outstanding. The calamari and lobster starters & the main monkfish were top notch. A good find in NY.', 'The Burger: Only available at lunch time and at a limited quantity, this patty is made of brisket, short rib and beef topped with aged cheddar and house-made bacon served with duck fat potato chips.']

name: Strand
address: 828 Broadway (at E 12th St), New York, NY 10003
reviews: ['In a corner of the Rare Book Room, you‚Äôll find a little hallway of bibliographies and art books. The first few shelves have bargain leathers, where you can get a book older than our country for $6.', 'Strand is frequented by both tourists and locals for its rare book room, deal bins, and "Strand"-branded tote bags and T-shirts. The Strand has events, from readings and classes to art shows.', 'Outliving City Lights in my lifetime - volumes to go before one sleeps. Amazing way to spend the day from the rare book section to all stacks in all floors.', "Best bookstore in Manhattan. If you want a lot of specific stuff, look the titles up on their site before to see if it's in stock & where it is. Otherwise just browse & enjoy hunting for treasure.", 'Christmas shopping sorted in one trip. Can‚Äôt think of a suitable book for your particular friend or loved one? Luckily this place also has the best magnets, socks, posters, coffee mugs, tote bags, etc', 'One of the best bookstores I‚Äôve ever been to. Great prices, friendly staff, lovely store with a huge selection.', 'Secret entrance to the Rare Book Room: enter door to the left of the main entrance, take stairs to 3.', "not my favorite bookstore in Manhattan, and sometimes it's way too crowded, but it's iconic to NY, and a definite must see if you've never been. Sometimes the dollar section is really on point too.", 'the best bookshop in NY - browse for hours. get lost in the stacks - reused and reduced price. $1 selects outside. new books of every topic on every table', "I've been coming to this bookstore since I was a kid.  I can still say this is the greatest bookstore to come to. It's an Icon for booklovers and even has the same smell of paper & ink. Stop by :)"]

name: Malt & Mold
reviews: ["A great little cheese shop filled with craft beers - we stopped to pick up a gift on the way to a dinner party. Very cool idea and it's way more unique than your average liquor store.", "Very happy addition to the 'hood. Doesn't hurt that I love craft beer.  You can drink there or buy a growler (solid selection on tap). They also have daily sandwich specials. Prost!", "taste the beers they have on tap while you peruse their bottled selection and pantry items - don't miss the goats milk caramel or the locally brewed Grimm ales.", 'Great local place. They have an awesome variety of cheese. They also have a bunch of different craft beers on tap and in the can. The pre-made sandwiches here rock', "Beyond craft beer and cheese there's crackers, truffle things, spreads, meats, pickles.. Basically all my life necessities.", 'Friday from 5-8pm, free booze tastings. Also tipsy scoop ice cream is sold here (alcoholic ice creamüç¶üç∏)', 'They know their stuff. Make sure to sample something on tap.', 'simply incredible, such wonderful selection and surprisingly inexpensive!!', 'Great little neighborhood spot with interesting craft beer selection and good outdoor seating options!', 'Friendly staff, nice craft selection, totally chill.']

name: T√© Company
address: 163 W 10th St (btwn 7th Ave S & Waverly Pl), New York, NY 10014
reviews: ["Cozy and quiet place to relax, sip all kinds of oolong teas, and converse with a friend. Small space so don't bring a crowd. Owners are friendly. Pineapple linzer cookie is delicate and delicious.", 'Come here to appreciate how great oolong teas can taste (unlike those served at typical Chinese restaurants). I also liked Pineapple Linzer. Be prepared to share a table with other customers.', 'The food here is truly exceptional. Everything stands out, from the potato tortilla to the salads, meats, and bread... Whatever you decide, do not miss the chocolate cake. A true hidden gem.', 'Probably one of the best tea places in NYC. Solid selection and the pineapple cookies are out of this world.', 'The tea is amazing and the pastries are appropriately sized and amazing. It can be hard to spot the entrance, so I took a picture of it.', 'Absolutely best tea place in the city. Ask for food parings for tea and stay there for a while. Owners and staff are so kind and great to chat with.', 'There are few experiences more lovely than tea and linzer cookies at this compact tea shop in Greenwich Village.', 'Cozy tea spot! Perfect for a relaxing a bit with wonderful soft jazz music.', 'Menu is ever changing, favorites like the linzer cookie remain. So many great teas- try oriental beauty grand !', 'One of the best spots in the city for a beautiful and delicate cup of tea. They have mastered the Taiwanese tea and the pastries are one of the cities most hidden secrets.']

name: Washington Square Park
address: 5 Avenue A (btwn MacDougal St & University Pl), New York, NY 10009
reviews: ["This is one of the coolest places in NYC...I'll take it over Central Park any day! In the summer there's music and art fairs all over the area and kids jumping around in the fountain!", 'Located in the heart of the Village this iconic park has a great atmosphere. Chess matches on the SW side, singers every corner, entertainers beside the fountain. Pass under the arch towards 5th Ave..', 'Love to people watch here. Always something going on ranging from groups of friends jamming together to artists creating chalk artwork on the ground', 'Though Bowie lived at 285 Lafayette Street, where tributes and memorials have been going up, he had reportedly\xa0said that his favorite place in New York City was\xa0Washington Square Park.', "A beautiful park and a must see for any visitor. It's perfect when you just want to sit on a bench and read a book or do some people watching. On nice days you can find all sorts of live music too.", "When the weather is nice, there are few places I'd rather be than enjoying the sunshine at WSP. Grab a book and some boba and enjoy one of NY's best parks.", 'There is nearby always music being played here, and often multiple bands all around the park. Look out for the piano on weekend and the guy who plays two trumpets at once üé∫!', 'NYC‚Äôs oldest known tree, a 310+ year old Elm sits quietly and unmarked in the NW corner of the park. Check it out.', 'One of the most iconic parks in NYC. Located in historic Greenwich Village, the park was a gathering place for members of the Beat generation. Also folk, and Hippie movements in the 1950s and 1960s', 'Great for peoplewatching and taking a break from it all. When you are done, find a nice spot to eat in the area and pay with Cover to quickly get to your next destination!']

name: David Zwirner Gallery

name: The Public Theater
address: 425 Lafayette St (btwn Astor Pl & E 4th St), New York, NY 10003
reviews: ['Some of the most provoking theatre in NYC is being done here. Recent top productions include Agony and Ecstasy of Steve Jobs and iHomo; both shows hit it out of the park.', "Need a night out? Come to see a show at The Public! Currently, we have The Agony and the Ecstasy of Steve Jobs. Beginning on Friday, Stew and Heidi Rodewald's new musical, The Total Bent will be here.", 'Tourist tip: take a detour off Broadway and support up-and-coming playwrights, amazing performers, and innovative productions at The Public!', 'If you constantly walk past this magical place and are constantly hit with a shy urge to go inside but are constantly afraid nothing will happen, do it. It‚Äôs exactly what this place is designed for.', 'This adored staple of Off Broadway also produces Under the Radar, the best Off-Off Broadway festival. Jump on tickets to see the daring international program of experimental theater.', 'Won tickets from TodayTix app and watched Winters Tale! Great view from any angle', 'Often fantastic staging and intimate experience. The Public Library has delicious American cuisine in a cooling and relaxing environment.', 'Hilton Als on Lisa Kron and Jeanine Tesori‚Äôs adaptation of Alison Bechdel‚Äôs ‚ÄúFun Home‚Äù: ‚ÄúThey‚Äôre aiming to showcase what we all share in: the exigencies of being human.‚Äù Through Nov. 3', 'black-shirted, fascistic staff, barking instructions at intermission: "take your ticket for re-entry!", and only saying this after you left your seat several minutes earlier and made your way to door!', 'Staging always great and a v intimate experience. Saw Dry Powder tonite - EXCELLENT.']

name: MUJI
address: 475 5th Ave (at E 41st St), New York, NY 10017
reviews: ['Free Wi-Fi! This is like a higher price, better quality IKEA + Asian stationary shop. The aesthetic is to die for & is such a breath of fresh air in midtown Manhattan.', 'LOVE this new flagship store. Beautifully rustic, fresh plants, Labo fragrances, simple and elegant products at a great price.', 'This is like an understated, utilitarian yet very charming Japanese version of say an IKEA. A lot of cool stuff at great prices!', "Clean and just what you want if you know the brand (if you are looking for the pens here doesn't have black, go to the Moma one)", 'Muji is awesome. The skin products are great, & there are so many nice pens to choose from!!', 'I love Muji anyway and the new 5th Ave location has all the good stuff. Stationery department is the best.', 'One of my favorite stores. The stationery is so professional and cute. The home goods are great too.', "Great space to buy things to fill and organize your space. The aromatherapy counter smells great. It's a good place to linger.", 'The notebook and pen selection here is wonderful! Head downstairs for the clothes and furnishings.', 'Love this shop! Great value for money üí∞']

name: Bryant Park
address: W 42nd St (btwn 5th & 6th Ave), New York, NY 10018
reviews: ["üå∫üå∏Love this park. It has everything you need to enjoy a awesome day or evening. Don't miss the daily activities and the tours. Visit the website and check what's going on! name: Cathedral of Notre-Dame de Paris (Cath√©drale Notre-Dame de Paris)
reviews: ['The view from the top of Notre Dame is breathtaking, and definitely worth the 402 steps it takes to get there (no elevators)! Make sure to check out the gargoyles and make the most of the free entry!', 'Of all famous Parisian landmarks, the Notre Dame Cathedral is the oldest. After a long construction period, this Gothic masterpiece was completed in 1345. But it is still as popular as ever!', 'Long long queues, but worth waiting. Free entrance, both exterior and interior are superb. Must see in Paris.', 'such a nice view to river and has a great classic architecture , when you walk into the church you can feel another sence of being in space .', 'a different visit to the ‚Äúcloches‚Äù ‚Äúbells of Notre Dame. you have to climb around 300 stairs to reach them. it really worth it!! the view is unique', 'Its worth the 10 euro to climb the stairs to the tower.From the top you can see both the Eiffel tower and  Sacre Coeur aka as Basilica of the Sacred Heart of Paris as well as see gargoyles up close.', 'Going to the roof is a must at least once in your life. An unbeatable view.', 'Amazing city view from towers!You have to wait in a long line of visitors even though you have a "museum pass".Visitor hours ends ~6pm,but I advise you to go there at most ~4pm before queuing ends up.', 'Impressive architecture. I recommend Day time Visits to enter the cathedral for beautiful views of the city & worth a look in the evening as the exterior is lit up beautifully.', 'Gothic cathedral, it is impossible not feel overwhelming by it. Go all the way to the top, and get a nice view of the city.']

name: Shakespeare & Company
reviews: ['A place full of magic. Every single detail is a peace of art. A place, where you feel the incredible power of books, where you can read, write, breathe...a source of inspiration for book lovers.', 'Old typing machine in the second floor and the old seats were interesting,it was great to be there. Different books with variety of subjects.I like it and I bought the "Body electric " from C.E.Smith', 'A most quaint bookstore with its own pet cat to boot. Quality books sold here, as are antiquarian books. Look out for the ultra cosy poetry corner and piano on 2nd floor (u can play it if in the mood)', "1/Actually, this place was recommended to me by a friend. It's highly worth the visit. They have one of the largest selections of used and new English books in Paris.", 'Most amazing English book store in Paris, cozy, a lil tight but always up to date, great events & lectures, normal prices, very friendly staff', "Full of whimsy and magic. This place is so worth it. Go for the poetry tea parties Sunday's 4-6. And, if you're lucky, someone brilliant will be playing the piano.", 'Such a beautiful bookstore, and perfect if you want to spend a quiet afternoon reading. Very peaceful ambiance, and all the books are in English. No photos allowed but I took one anyways. :^)', 'My favorite bookshop by far. Well curated, helpful staff, killer location, and steeped in history. I daydream about writing a book while living upstairs or having my own Before Sunset rondez-vous.', "Such an unbelievably beautiful place, especially for book lovers. It's a combined bookshop and library. Quiet place to sit down and have a nice read. All books are in English!", "This place is heaven. The ambiance feels so warm and cozy. And the selection and service are just as equally great. Don't forget to get a look upstairs!"]

reviews: ["The world's most famous art museum as absolutely worth visiting when in Paris. name: Aterro do Flamengo
address: Pq. Brig. Eduardo Gomes, Rio de Janeiro, RJ
reviews: ["I love walking and running in this park, it's one of the calmer places in Rio!", 'Beautiful place to rest and enjoy the sightseeing', 'We walked here during the daytime and were advised not to stay too late as it can get dodgy after dark - relatively clean beach, but don‚Äôt know if I‚Äôd swim in the water', 'Stunning park with a great view of Morro do P√£o de A√ß√∫car!', 'Facing Guanabara Bay and Sugar Loaf come Rio 2016 time, the park will become the venue for road cycling and race walking.', 'Facing Guanabara Bay and Sugar Loaf come Rio 2016 time, the park will become the venue for road cycling and race walking.', 'Linda paisagem.
