name: Christ the Redeemer (Cristo Redentor)
address: Estrada do Corcovado (Pq. Nacional da Tijuca), Rio de Janeiro, RJ, 22241-200
reviews: ['Children aged 6-12 pay half the adult fare and under 5 get in for free. Try and arrive as early as possible so as to avoid big crowds and get the best shots at the top. The view up there is amazing!', "There is no doubt why this is one of the 7 wonderful things in the World! Its amazing, fantastic view of all Rio de Janeiro. It's definitely a must do when in RJ.", 'this place occupied our minds butconsidering the best time of day:)) just do it as earlier as possible and focus on the rest in Rio ‚úåÔ∏èeven if there is fog up in there, take your sun cream with you.', "Highly recommend hiking up from Parque Lage. Takes about an hour and a half and isn't easy going but it's a great feeling when you get up there! You can buy your entry ticket at the turnstile up top.", 'This is a must see for anyone christian or not. The beautiful panoramic views of Rio plus the immense size and history of Cristo Redentor is a sight you will never forget!', 'Amazing. Take a moment to enjoy Cristo Redentor and the breathtaking views of Rio De Janeiro! Bring your camera and allow ample time when visiting.', 'RIO DE JANEIRO - World Heritage UNESCO The site consists of an exceptional urban setting encompassing the key natural elements that have shaped and inspired the development of the city', 'It looked to tiny on top, but after taking the tour the view is incredible. So many people visiting a famous monument :)', 'It a must when you visit Rio. Its a verry powerful experience to take the stairs up to Cristo to get a close view of his face. The city view from the top is absolutely gorgeous üåü', "Even early in the morning it's crowded so be prepared. But no visit to Rio will be complete without visiting it! Shuttles from Praca do Lido will take you there for much smaller fee than the tour"]

name: Corcovado
address: Estrada do Corcovado, Rio de Janeiro, RJ
reviews: ["Go early, during morning hours, otherwise you'll find it packed and incredibly hot. I'd suggest taking a van (not the train) so you can stop by Mirante Dona Marta.", 'This is Brazil! One of the best places ever to live! Pessoal, em vez de ficarem preocupados com as fotos no ig e no facebook, curtam a paisagem, sintam a energia do lugar! Much better! √â inexplic√°vel!', "Don't just take your beach clothes if you're going in Winter. If you're looking for amazing photo opportunities, pay close attention to the weather because the fog can hide everything.", "If you like hiking, it is a must! It will took you about an hour if you don't stop. But you will: at least to take pictures to the monkeys trying to steal your food.", 'If you would like to take the train or bus to the statue of Christ. Ask the employee at the railway station what the weather expectations are. Within a short period of time unclouded skies can change.', 'Try to go on a clear day to avoid clouds, and avoid weekends! Stay there if possible until sunset!', 'Much easier than expected, got there by 830am on a weekday, bought the train ticket by 845am I was already taking pictures, hassle free.', 'Take a stroll up Corcovado for a fantastic view if the Christo (Redentor) from the back.', 'Fantastic views but be prepared for large crowds.', 'New experience üòç love every place in Brazil,People so friendly.']

name: Parque Lage
address: Rua Jardim Bot√¢nico, 414, Rio de Janeiro, RJ, 22461-000
reviews: ["This place is so beautiful that you don't need to use any filters when posting your photos on fb ;) quiet oasis in the middle of the city home to the art school and lovely botanical garden behind.", "Beautiful parque. If you're brave and in good shape you can hike from the back right corner of the park up Corcovado Trail to Christ the Redeemer.", 'This is a huge tropical park, with lakes and English gardens and the trailhead that leads up Corcovado mountain. Have breakfast at Caf√© du Lage while everyone is doing their morning exercise routine.', 'The most beautiful setting for break/brunch. Back drop is the lush Tijuca national park with Christ the Redeemer overlooking the city. The  food looks amazing. Great for breakfast and brunch drinks', 'Wonderful waitress who speaks fluently english. Great spot for breakfast, the bread is amazing. And the walk around is worth to be seen.', 'Extremely memorable brunch and visit. Recommend walking around the property and doing some exploring of the aquariums and ruins.', 'Beautiful place and great bistr√¥ for a Sunday brunch', 'Incredible place in here! Such a beautiful spot to see the nature.', 'Take the trail up to Corcovado from here & skip the crowds.', "It's a beatiful place that used to be a good spot for a picnick, now they don't let you step on the grass and you have to sit on an unconfortable area."]

name: Basilica di Santa Maria Maggiore
address: Piazza di Santa Maria Maggiore 42, 00100 Roma Lazio
reviews: ['Rather drab-looking exterior hides a fantastic interior. The largest church dedicated to Mary in all Rome.', 'Basilica Santa Maria Maggiore ‚Äì Piazza Santa Maria Maggiore (Termini) - One of the basilicas of Rome in all its Baroque style glory. If you like mosaics, this is a definite must-see.', "I'd say go in the daytime, because we went at night and a lot of the interior was not lit up. I could see where the light from the windows would help. A great church you otherwise!", 'The las arquitectural work of Michelangelo. A bit forgotten by tourists and a gem amidst too many churches. It has some Vatican artwork and some hidden surprises.', 'It has the relic of the Holy Crib, shards from the Holy Manger, a piece of the True Cross, and the tombs of St. Matthew, St. Jerome, and Pope Pius V.', 'Another piece of art. If you want to visit a few churches, this is definitely one of them! Great interior, I stayed there and admired it.', "One of the most beautiful churches in Rome.. Don't forget to see the crypt too.", 'Inside there are lot‚Äôs of beautiful and important thing, and all of this is free. The excursion you will be offered for 5 euro for the ‚Äòunderground‚Äô. It‚Äôs a little bit boring, but underground is ok', 'It is the largest Catholic Marian church in Rome. Other churches in Rome dedicated to Mary include Santa Maria in Trastevere, Santa Maria in Aracoeli and Santa Maria sopra Minerva', "Favorite church I visited in Rome. It's so massive and stunning, really breathtaking. Make sure you visit it."]

name: Colosseum (Colosseo)
address: Piazza del Colosseo 1 (Via dei Fori Imperiali), 00184 Roma Lazio
reviews: ['Must visit! First Sunday of each month is free. Ticket includes Roman Forum and Palatine Hill. Book your reservation before hand to skip lines. Free entry also costs EUR 2 online. Level 2 is must.', "What else can be said, it's the colloseum! Amazing. However, very crowded. Buy tickets in advance and go early in the morning. Download the free Rick Steve's audio tour and listen as you walk through.", 'The private tour costs 9‚Ç¨ and is totally worth it! Our guide was this very nice and professional archaeologist. You get to ask questions and access places that are forbidden to other visitors. Lovely!', "Historical, glorious and imperial! Definitely worth a visit if you're in Rome.Buy the ticket online to skip the long line of ticket and no need to pay a lot extra to tour leaders,there are audio/video", 'Gets very hot here, bring water, hats, some shade. Vendors outside hounding you for these items', 'It‚Äôs amazing and beautiful. You can buy the tickets in advance with some agencies the which it helps a lot with the long lines, ask if they have entrance for the arena it‚Äôs totally worth it.', 'No introduction needed, just make sure you buy your tickets online beforehand to avoid the queue. Really reccommend to choose the visit that allows you to go to the 3rd level and the underground floor', 'A must do in Rome! Make sure you book the tickets with the fast-track option. Download Rick Steves free audio guide beforehand or get a tour which takes you to places where normal tickets don‚Äôt.', 'Get Roma pass to avoid the crowd. Place needs around an hour to check. Go to the second floor. Views r awesome. You will need to be dressed comfortably. Better visit in the afternoon to avoid the heat', "Awesome, just awesome, must see also from inside. Take a guided tour it's worth it. Many people offer the tours outside for approximately 30 euros per person."]

name: Arch of Titus (Arco di Tito)
reviews: ['The archs are really one of the spotlights of the Roman Forum. This one, despite having a single archway, is memorable and monumental.', "An excellent place to sit down and have a rest when it's too hot outside.", 'As a Jew, I‚Äôm used to seeing evidence of the bad luck of my people. This was still pretty interesting to look at.', 'Wonderful arches with reliefs showing important historical events.', 'A big piece of Jewish history available to see in Rome. Very interesting.', 'Continue to Arco di Tito after Colosseo - use the same ticket...You will be walking in great Roman history!!!', 'One of the most detailed arches telling the tale of when the Romans conquered Jerusalem/ the holy land', 'Entrance to Roman Forum and Palatine Hill. Exit from Colosseum and teach here.', 'The Arch of Titus commemorated the Roman victory over the province of Judaea (Israel) in A.D. 70.', 'Historical arch with many details! Very impressive']

name: Temple of Romulus (Tempio del Divo Romolo)
address: Piazza di Santa Maria Nova 53, 00186 Roma Lazio
reviews: ['Beautiful buildings, barely ruins in places', 'Lugar muito interessante, deixe-se levar pelas estruturas e volte imagine-se naquele tempo.', 'Peque√±o templo con unas de las puertas m√°s antiguas del mundo.', 'Hist√≥ria por cima de hist√≥ria!!!', 'Um dos componentes do f√≥rum romano! Como um todo vale antena conhecer o F√≥rum!']

name: Roman Forum (Foro Romano)
address: Via dei Fori Imperiali, 00186 Roma Lazio
reviews: ['One of the coolest places to v itisit in Rome. Wear comfortable shoes and be prepared to take tons of pictures. I suggest a tour guide so you can learn the history as you walk around the Forum.', 'Looks a lot smaller than it actually is! Wish I had come earlier and taken the audio tour. Wonderful ancient Roman site! Worth spendig more than a few hours if you are into history and architecture!', 'For a free audio guide: Download the podcast "Italy Audio Tours" by Rick Steves and follow the instructions. Was a really fun way to discover the sight!', 'It is amazing historical place with absolutely unique architecture from the old Rome. I am very glad to be at this place. Lifehack -- good observation point is outside of Forum near the capitol.', "This is a must-see! But wear good shoes, come here early and remember water since there's hardly any shade and you'll be walking in difficult terrain.", 'Walking the Roman forum is truly mind-blowing, taking you back to antiquity. Afterwards take the exit to Via dei Fori Imperiali behind the Basilica Emilia to see the fora of Augustus and successors.', 'Perhaps one of my favourite places on Earth. It felt sublime to walk among history and art. And the views are amazing. And the green areas quiet.', 'Included in the colessum ticket,the area is huge,dont suggest to walk all the place in August..It takes you back to medieval times,if you like to imagine how it would to live in those ages, go for it!', 'Try to get Roma pass which includes two free pass for the museums and colosseum and Forum counts oneüòá all public transportation is free with this. The ambiance is great..', 'A must see, included in ticket of Colosseum. Saturn and Venus temples are quite awesome. Stroll around to visualise the grandeur of Roman Empire.']

name: Gelateria La Romana Roma Ventisettembre
categories: ['Cafe, Coffee, and Tea House', 'Ice Cream Parlor', 'Italian Restaurant']
address: Via XX Settembre 60 (Via Piave), 00187 Roma Lazio
reviews: ["Best ice cream place in Rome! Flavour names are in Italian so don't forget to bring your dictionary! üòä They are speaking English but they are so busy to translate the flavour names to you sorry üòä", 'One of the best (if not, THE) best gelateria in Rome! Had the Crema dal 1947 and Bacio di Dama con Mandorle Tostate, which are must-try flavours! Multiple visits warranted!', "If you don't know about the choices, the staff will love to recommend to you the ice-cream. It's the best in Rome with 4 scoops of ‚Ç¨3 and free flowing chocolate inside the cone. Pistachio is the bomb!", 'best ice cream in Rome with good price. love the texture and all kinds of nut-flavors. they also add melting chocolate into the cone, that makes your last bite so yummy.', 'Amazing Ice cream! 2 scoops for ‚Ç¨2.50, either in a cone or tub. Only problem is we had to google the flavours as they wasn‚Äôt in english. I got chocolate and lemon with a white chocolate filling.', 'I have tried a lot of gelatos in Rome but this one made it to the top. Croccantino della nonna or sth like that and whipped zabaglione cream are out of this world!', "If you want to taste the very best of the famous italian gelato, this is where you should go. Their pistachio ice cream is DELICIOUS!!! Every gelato flavour of this place is amazing. Don't miss it!", 'Best ice cream in town. Best value for money, and very friendly personnel with respect to their clients. Who ever takes vasetti desert, they give a clean sealed vase as a free gift.üíú', 'Excellent ice cream, very friendly staff, my fianc√©e loved it, too. Can recommend the Crema Dal 1947 and Fiordilatte. Welcoming interior and decor. Can watch how ice cream is made through a window.', "Everything except the queues, which are out of the door at peak times. Around 3pm is best from my experience. Some of the best ice cream you'll find anywhere, let alone Rome."]

name: Palatine (Palatino)
address: Via di San Gregorio 30, 00186 Roma Lazio
reviews: ['What a place!!! Must see if you like history and legends. Though you need to have a guide.', 'Please educate yourself before entering! We did the whole walkthrough backwards...you should first see the Forum ruins, then the Palatine Hill. It seems to make more sense anyway. Enjoy!', 'Absolutely gorgeous! It is a must see in Rome. A huge hill overlooking the city. Includes a museum as well.', "It's an invaluable experience. We loved all of it! Archeology, history, humanity, aristocracy, luxury living and smart architecture/engineering of past people will make you think more of humanity :)", 'Amazing views of the city & wonderful ruins to wander through! Worth stopping here first to pick up your combined ticket for the Colosseum as the queues there are absolutely ridiculous.', "If possible, go with a guide or an audio tour to get the full picture of what you're seeing. Plenty of water fountains for the hot days.", 'My absolute favorite. We had a very educated and experienced guide who participated in the dig. She was supremo! My favorite because of the preserved times of Roman society.  Quite sacred, I felt.', 'Some of best views of Rome especially the Colosseum and Roman Forum!!!', 'Worth going in but go early cause they start closing around 19:00 and the area is enormous so you might want to see everything once and not have to go back again cause you went too late', "My absolute favorite part of Rome. I could have spent hours exploring the grounds. If I ever come back to Rome this is what I'm coming back for first and foremost. Don't miss it!"]

name: Foro di Cesare
address: Via dei Fori Imperiali, 00186 Roma Lazio
reviews: ['Book your night experience for one of the best visits of your life.', "In summer they illuminate the ruins with a great light and audio show! Don't miss out! More information can be found at www.viaggioneifori.it/en/", "Caesar's forum is less impressive than some of the other ones but if you consider the grandness of the character it's worth visiting, particularly if the audio visual tour is included", "Not much remaining, there's indicative plaques at many spots around with information and graphic representation of how it used to be. A pity so little has made it to our century.", 'Make sure to check out the Imperial Light Show! Truly innovative entertainment!', 'Get the SUPER ticket ahead of time. You‚Äôll get so much more out of it.', 'Must see! Not much left, but gives you a great impression of how people lived long ago!', 'Try the light show at night! Beautiful!!!', 'Nice to see, we even witness how they look for treasure on the ground', 'Large historic site!']

name: Foro Traiano (Foro di Traiano)
address: Via dei Fori Imperiali, 00186 Roma Lazio
reviews: ['Ideal for night walks. Read about it you will learn and enjoy', 'If you‚Äôre going to buy art from the artists around the area, make sure you sit and watch them create before committing to a sale. Do pay artists prices for printshop work.', "Is more than just a lot of colums. I suggest to' go inside from via 4 novembre amazing to' see how well preserve everything is from the 2nd century ad", 'Amazingly grand and beautiful. Awesome views in the night. Spend some time in the night imagining the grandeur of Roman Empire.', "On the north-east side of via dei Fori Imperiali are the extensive remains of Trajan's forum, the last of the fora, laid out in the early second century AD.", 'Excellent view on piazza Venezia and via foro imperali, but the entry  is a little expensive(9euros)!', 'Interesting ruins preserved especially the huge columns.', 'Stunningly beautiful ‚ù§üáÆüáπ', 'Ruins giving you the feeling how it was before... Great impression', 'A nice walk amongst historic ruins!!!']

name: Trajan's Column (Colonna Traiana)
address: Via dei Fori Imperiali, 00187 Roma Lazio
reviews: ['Everywhere you turn Rome offers a historic treat. This column has a lot of History and is a lovely to stumble upon, particularly during sunset', "One of the sights in Rome that you really need to visit. Built in 113 to celebrate emperor Trajan's victory over the Dacians.", 'Made in Carrara marble, a carved frieze winds from the bottom to the top, telling the story of Emperor Marcus Aurelius heroically battling barbarians about A.D. 170.', "A sight to see. The stairwell that goes to the top isn't open to the public but still worth a visit to this impressive structure", 'Originally the images wrapping the column were painted. Think of the amazing color and stories they would tell.', "There's a staircase inside that leads up to the top of the column! Not open to the public though", 'Impressive column next to the tomb of the unknown soldier.', "It's a must come and see from the inside and outside!!! What a feeling!!!", 'Details on the column are Breathtaking ‚ù§Ô∏è', 'It is amazing to see the column! Must see!']

name: Gwanghwamun (Í¥ëÌôîÎ¨∏)
reviews: ['Incredible landmark. Visit the Sejong King museum underground. Great views of the mountains surrounding Seoul. Recommend to visit both at day and night!', 'One of the most iconic monuments of Seoul that was in many Korean movies. It‚Äôs much more huge and wast than it seems from the photos and it‚Äôs always crowded, but it‚Äôs a must see when you‚Äôre in Seoul', 'Beautiful historical monument, you could spend a good 1-2 hours here enjoying the scenery and taking pictures. A MUST SEE if you had to choose just one historical site during your stay.', 'Gwanghwamun is the main and largest gate of Gyeongbokgung Palace. The royal changing of the guard ceremony is held in front of the main gate every hour from 10:00 to 15:00. It takes about 15 mins.', 'Gwanghwamun was first constructed in 1395 as the main gate to Gyeongbokgung Palace, the main and most important royal palace during the Joseon Dynasty.', "A must go if you're in Seoul. You don't need a guide to appreciate the aesthetics of the place. 8/10", 'Better to go in the evening, it looks amazing then.', 'Historical place, Korean drama "Iris" has been use here as a "major battle place"', 'This place needs no introduction, every tourist will come and it worths your time.', 'the castle is really big, and the view is really great. For tourist its a must visiting place if u go to seoul.']

name: Gyeongbokgung Palace (Í≤ΩÎ≥µÍ∂Å)
reviews: ["Be sure to check out the time for the guard changing ceremony. You can exit gyeonbokgung station to reach this palace directly. It's a huge palace but the main hall and rooms are restricted to enter.", 'Each rock plate represents where the soldiers stand by their level. There is a beautiful lake on the west and mountain at the back of the Gyeongbokgong palace.', 'The main palace from the Joseon Dynasty. Aside from the breathtaking Korean/Chinese architecture, this is also home to the National Palace Museum and National Folk Museum. Definitely a must-see.', 'They shut the entry doors 1 hour before it closes. That‚Äôs your key to visit the palace and its surroundings avoiding massive crowds. Also, the sunset‚Äôs light has a beautiful impact in the architecture', 'Rent a Hanbok and you get to enter for free! I think this palace is a must visit if you travel to Seoul for the first time! It‚Äôs really beautiful seeing so many tourists wearing Hanbok.', 'The biggest and main palace so if you don‚Äôt visiting others this one is must to see! Very big territory so it will take time to walk around. Also don‚Äôt miss guard changing ceremony!', "One of the main attraction and iconic site of the city, a very big complex with many historical palace, residences, pavilions and halls. There's free guided English tours at specific times", 'this place is must visit if you are in Korea especially Seoul. this palace are sooo beautiful, you can also rent hanbok (traditional Korean dress) for taking picture inside this palace.', 'Obviously a must visit if you are in Seoul!! So big and right in the middle of the city. Book a tour, it is worth it!! Allow a few hours to just wander around :)', "This is the largest of Seoul's Five Grand Palaces built by the Joseon dynasty - and the crowds indicate so. Suggest getting the pass at 10,000 Won to see all 5 and then take 2-3 days to visit."]

Their bread is also very tasty', 'Great pastries and nice ambiance! The place is not loud so, it is possible to stay for a few hours and study while sipping your coffee.', 'In the evening, all the bakery items are 20% off. Plan ahead and save on your breakfast the next morning!', 'Whatever you choose for bread, will be satisfied...  Anfu road shop is the best to take a rest among Baker n Spice cafes in Shanghai..', 'Spacious cafe with a range of pastries, juices, coffee and wine. The carrot cake is too notch!', "Sprinkle some acid on your croissant  and enjoy the weird music in this place. If you're lucky you'll get a background chorus of crying babies. Meanwhile the basics are what matter: bread and coffee"]

name: Fat Cow
reviews: ['Good burgers and even good fried chicken.  The burgers are big but not crazy big where everything falls apart.  Well crafted burgers.', 'Good value at happy hour. Loud, western theme gives an impression of a busy sports bar in...maybe the Minneapolis airport', "Fried chicken, burgers and the sundaes! Best I've had in Shanghai and right next to WeWork.", 'Avoid on Monday if you aren‚Äôt deal seekers! There‚Äôs BOGO on Monday and always super packed with loong queue!!', 'Excellent selection of burgers and sides. Very fresh salsa and the do not exaggerate about the milkshake quality!', 'Just love the place, they have the best burgers in Shanghai and variation of super great salads', 'What? A gourmet burger place in Shanghai? Never seen one of those! Crazy! I‚Äôd come back. Great place to watch Tinder dates go down (no pun intended. Come on, it‚Äôs a public place!)', 'Great burgers, shakes, fries - pricey but awesome! Noisy and buzzing atmosphere is fun. Acoustics are awful.', '$5 cocktails very good! Whole bill under $20pp for very good meal and drinks. Very good, had the cheesiest one possible and wasn`t dissapointed.', 'A surprisingly very good veggie burger! Great service as well. 100% recommended.']

name: BREAD etc
reviews: ['Excellent breads and pastries. Shakshoukah (sp?) is fantastic. Good wifi and plenty of outdoor seating for warm weather.', 'If you sit outside, there is a big risk that no one come up to you to take an order. Nice for coffee, breads and pastries', 'salmon eggs Benedict was good, served on a croissant! Their special Turkish breakfasts were unique and yummy too. Coffee needs some work.', 'Amazing pastries! Good for a quick brunch or breakfast', 'Really good Shakshuka. The bread and veggie dishes are great too. Pizza is decent.', "Pretty bright place and already quite busy. Good place for coffee and pastry. Haven't tried the mains yet", 'nice popular place with good bread. good for friends gatherings', '"Accepts credit card" = only Chinese credit card, be prepared!', 'Really good shakshuka with chala', 'Coffee only mediocre though the baguette was beautiful.']

name: Goodfellas
reviews: ["Very cozy warm and quaint! Good prices, great portions, good service. I suggest the starter platter to share for two & lamb ragout as it has everything but it is a lot of food so don't over order", 'Great food, reasonably charged, nice decorations everywhere ;) They have a terrace also on the 7th floor now - with a stunning view. Better bring cash rather than cards up there...', "The most authentic italian food in shanghai! Cozy small space with very friendly service and fantastic food! I'll be back!", 'Undoubtedly my favourite Italian restaurant in Shanghai. The Eggplant Parmigiana, Beef Carpaccio and Porcini Risotto are a must try! Seating is limited so reservations 24 hours in advance are a must.', 'Great small Italian place. Anticipate with reservation or avoid peak times. Great English speaking service. Simply go for a salad and pizza for four, they‚Äôre huge! Starters can be expensive.', "Ask for the pizza that has truffle, parmesan cheese, homemade sausage, and other stuff, the BEST I'VE HAD! The staff was incredibly nice, and they gave us one drink on the house for our honeymoon!!", "So delicious aragosta gratinata: lobster with mushrooms and mustards souse from chef's recommendation!", 'Great food, great vibes and friendly staff. It was quite a pricey dinner but was worth it for my birthday celebrations!', 'Great location in The bund , small but cozy , make reservation , good selecci√≥n of wine , food ridiculously tasty . Excellent . Service top', 'Love the restaurant! Fresh tuna tartar and octopus are my favourite. Not mentioning the great service from Luca!']

name: National Gallery Singapore
reviews: ["Wow! You can really get lost here as there are so many staircases and turns. There's also a 6th level with restaurants that have a great view of the Padang. Free entrance for local residents.", 'Friendly staff who explain the displays and point you in the right direction - the building‚Äôs a bit of a maze. Alongside the art galleries are some interesting rooms detailing the history of Singapore', 'Exploring 2 mini houses at the foot of the tree trunk below the Treehouse. Quite fun to join curious kiddos with their adventure in this Enchanted Forest at Keppel Centre for Art Education (level 1).', 'Above entrance of former Supreme Court, find sculpture of Justice wielding her scales, & a frieze of the 1819 treaty signing to establish Singapore as a trading post. Source: Singapore Book of Records', 'Beautiful artworks in a large restored courthouse and gallery. It is confusing lay laid out and the signs do not help. Many levels that do not flow correctly. Wonderful to walk around but ask for help', "Females and kiddos would love the feeling of walking into this fantasy 'story book' The Enchanted Forest. The kiddos were fascinated with this fairytale playground, including the Treehouse and River.", 'Let your imagination run wild at this story book playground at Keppel Centre for Art Education: Relaxing on a floating wooden plank in the river of The Enchanted Forest ignoring the crocodile behind.', 'From Lift Lobby B, take lift to level 5 (Ng Teng Fong Roof Garden Gallery), then walk up the steps to Padang Deck at level 6 to view nice scenery of Marina Bay and city skyscrapers (^_^)', 'History: Orig known as Municipal Bldg when built in 1929. With SG proclaimed a city (Royal Charter granted by King George VI in 1951), it was renamed City Hall. Source: SG Infopedia', 'Nicer to watch "Facade Show" - musical lights show on the external of building live (in conjunction with <Gallery Light To Night Festival> from 25 Nov to 4 Dec 2016). üòâüëç Got Milo van here at 8pm üòã']

name: Esplanade Park
reviews: ['Swings, slides for children üëçüèº', 'undoubtedly, my favorite structure here in Singapore! :D I fell in love with it instantly!!', "Take a stroll down the park at night. You'll love it!", 'Love the view!', 'enjoyed Esplanade park last night.. a place worth visiting in Singapore', 'Sit and relax with a cup of tea on a Sat evening.', 'just wish ur here comforting me', 'Singapore arts festival 2011', 'Î©ÄÎùºÏù¥Ïñ∏ ÏûÖÏóêÏÑú ÎøúÏñ¥ÎÇòÏò§Îäî Î¨ºÏùÑ Î∞õÏïÑ ÎßàÏãúÎäî ÏÑ§Ï†ïÏÉ∑Ïù¥ ÏµúÍ≥†', 'malem bagus buat foto2.. ato sekedar duduk2 sante']

name: Esplanade - Theatres on the Bay
reviews: ['Durian look is actually triangulated glass & sunshade system. Tradeoff betw solar shading & panoramic views. Offers shadow & texture during day; & as glowing lanterns @ night. Source: DP Architects', 'Locals call this place the "Durian" (after a regional thorny fruit). However from sky, we see curves than thorns of the popular local fruit. Aerial photo taken by Yeo Kai Wen. Source: Straits Times', "Concert hall is the smaller of the two and is one of the most 'glam' venue in Singapore for a classical music performance. The best thing is that there is no phone reception inside!", 'Besides the F&B outlets within the Esplanade, we also enjoyed ourselves at Gluttons Bay just right beside the building! Local food, alfresco & shaded dining, affordable cold drinks üçª', 'Esplanade has some really beautiful view from the top of the building. Do not miss the view of the city from the top during evening times.', 'Live shows. Many of them! Quite new names but really good quality. Amazing promoters that spoil the audience and give a chance to young bands to prove themselves', "There's a car grooming service at carpark level B2. Called GroomWerkz, they operate Mon-Fri 7:30am-4:45pm. They'll even provide a spare car while yours is being given spa attention. Source: website", 'Walking/scooter tours can be found at The Walking Singapore #01-18. Rental of e-bikes, money changer, discounted tickets to local attractions & other tourist services are offered too', 'Did u know? Theatres on the Bay is built on reclaimed land. Construction began 1998 & completed 2002. S$600M cost fully financed by Singapore Pools & Singapore Totalisator Board. Source: Infopedia', 'A nice arts center and a familiar place for meet-ups with friends for dining & a performance. I like the exhibitions & festivals as well! One horrible experience with a rude theatre usher though!']

name: Esplanade Theatre
reviews: ['Pre-event dinner & drinks. Besides the usual F&B outlets within Esplanade, we discovered Gluttons Bay right next to the building. Local food, alfresco dining & affordable drinks üç∫', 'Seats 1,950 and has 3 circle levels. More details here: https://www.esplanade.com/venue-hire/theatre', 'Nice placeeeeeeeeeeee']

name: The Merlion
reviews: ['Basically just a landmark with few cafes. But it is really iconic and near several attraction such as museums at civil district, garden by the bay, and singapore flyer (important for your itinerary)', 'One of five official Merlions in Singapore. The national icon of Singapore, a lion head on a fish body, representing the origins of a fishing town, and its original name Singapura (lion city).', 'Take a photo here with the Merlion statue and marina bay sands hotel as the background. My most favorite photo view in Singapore. Better view at night.', 'designed in 1964. Lion Head=Singapura=Lion City in Malay. Fish Body=a fishing village Temasek=sea town in Javanese. at the mouth of the Singapore River in 1972, relocated in 2002 to Merlion Park', "A beautiful water spouting statue. You can't visit Singapore without visiting The Merlion! Lots of people and naturally. So beautiful the place of Singapore.", 'Merlion is a the ionic symbol for Singapore, walk to the Merlion Park and take a photo of Merlion and also have a good view of the Marina Bay and Financial Centre of Singapore.Breath taking scenery!', 'Sometimes, patient is required to make one good photoshoot as so many people are there during the day (and also at night). It is best to take a photo at around sunrise time.', 'Did u know? The Merlion was designed & used as Singapore Tourism Board‚Äôs logo back in 1964 until 1997. The board still holds exclusive rights to use the symbol. Source: Infopedia', 'An icon of Singapore. Best photos are actually at dusk/twilight as the statue becomes too bright against the dark night skies. Amazing views of the city & Marina Bay complex.', 'Geek notes: There are 6 authorised Merlion statues in Singapore, with the pair here being the 2 most famous. There used to be a 12-storey version at nearby Sentosa island. Source: Wikipedia']

name: Esplanade - Theatres on the Bay
reviews: ['Free art showcase on the bay. Enjoy variety of performances while looking at the scenic view across the river :)', "Make sure to drop by this magnificent building. It's within walking distance to The Merlion so you can visit both in one trip.", "It's the best place to take photos and to enjoy the light show. Sometimes (in the weekends) have live music!. The best place to see the skyline too. Sublime!", 'Great place 4 visit! Nice view n one of best place 2 relax! My favorite place!!!!!!', 'Check out the slush shop, Chill out. Ice cold slush made from 100% fruit juice. It is located beside the theater, opposite No Sign Board', 'If you love live music, this is the place for you during weekends.', 'Esplanade Theatre #throwback #06092010', 'A really nice place to be at :) love the view of the buildings!', 'Dun park n wait at the foyer too long, security will think u r a terrorist even though u r there every other day !!', 'Totally chill and relaxed.']

name: Fort Canning Park
reviews: ["It's great for walking but not much for a runner since it's quite small. The beautiful trees are worth the visit.", 'Great park, but can be very busy on Sundays. Reservoir in the centre is off limits. Check out the battle box and the spice garden. They also hold awesome concerts and movies on the green.', 'Public parking. Anticlockwise around the hill, 1) ROM after Coleman St, 2) behind the National Museum, 3) up the slope at the end of Fort Canning Walk, 4) small one off Clemenceau Ave. CBD rates apply', 'A welcome oasis of greenery in the city. Lots of shaded areas. Takes effort to walk along the meandering & uphill paths/stairs', 'Pancur Larangan (Forbidden Spring). A tranquil water feature at the southwest corner of the park. The spot was said to be where the wives & consorts of Malay Kings of the land used to take their baths', 'aka Bukit Larangan (Forbidden Hill), the resting place of ancient kings. renamed Fort Canning in 1861 to honor Viscount Charles John Canning, the Governor-General and first Viceroy of India', 'Terrific park for an afternoon walk in the heart of CBD. Lush tropical plant aromas, historical monuments, and local music.', 'Another magnificent heritage tree, the terap, a tall forest tree found throughout the Malay peninsula and in Singapore. Located behind NAS', 'Plenty of private rest areas around the city park, offering quiet respite', 'Lovely park with a lot of history. Outdoor concerts are held here and there are some nice cafes here too.']

name: Napoleon Food & Wine Bar
reviews: ['The staff was great. Easy order from iPad & charging ports for your phone. My risotto taste like it came out of a box üòñ But the wine & champagne selections are notable. Great place for a drink.', 'Did u know? In modern-day Georgia & the Zagros Mountains of Iran, grapes were 1 of the earliest fruits to be domesticated, & wine was made as early as 7,400 years ago! Source: National Geographic', 'Yellowtail ceviche. Tried 4SQ user Sawit‚Äôs recommendation. Marinated in greenish calamansi & lemon dressing, & topped with crunchy bits (onions, turnips, seaweed), the cold dish was refreshing & light', 'Good variety wine by the glass. Good quality. It‚Äôs the highlight here. You can enjoying different wine, even available in half glass', 'Overall menu not much of choices. Pasta, I gave it a Missed, not impressive. Desserts, Gelatos are good. I like chocolate ganache too. (Photo: Iberico pork chop)', 'Limited seating, Reservation recommended. You can have dinner at the bar. Outdoor seating and indoor high tables available.', 'The homemade chicken liver pate served for the set lunch was tiny üòÇ Wished I had placed a cutlery to demonstrate my point. Still it was tasty, & I wiped the remnants with bread', 'Hand-cut wagyu beef tartare. Substantial main course; probably can share. Chunky pieces of beef, with capers & croutons adding playfulness to each bite', 'gr8 for drinks with mixed platter to share (cheese, bread & charcuterie). apart from tht, portions were meagre for the price. we had 2 pastas & a salad, all of which forgettable', 'Beef tartar is massive main course. You could share for two. Taste good']

name: Marina Bay Sands
reviews: ['Wooden lounge chairs available to lie back and see the surrounding CBD and occasional water activity. Rent a bicycle or stroll along the waterfront.', 'Take a stroll along the board walk. Enjoy the cool wind, the business city lights and the company. Go on Sunday night and you might catch a "Songs of the Sea-esque" show.', 'Nice place to go for a walk great photo opportunities for photographers get the between 7:45-8:45 to see the light show with all the lasers looks impressive from the bay', "A very chill place to hang out or to spend your Sunday afternoon, reading a good book, while listening to the swingin' jazz music from the speakers all around the Bay. Just like what I'm doing now.", "I love this place for 1000 reasons that they don't fit into words. If everybody could visit just to see what this place offers to all citizens here!", 'Pleasant walk with magnificent views. Worth visiting twice, at day and closer to evening.', 'Fantastic I love this place', 'Variety of restaurants and shopping strip. Ate at Carnevour; my 2nd visit here. Meat lovers paradise.', 'Catch the laser show everyday at 8.30 and 9.30pm. Its beautiful with water fountains, music and lights.', 'certainly one of the best waterfront venues in Singapore! great place to chill. lots of space for events too!']

name: Louis Vuitton
reviews: ['Floating LV boutique just outside Marina Bay Sands. A must visit for LV fans. In the evening during the laser light show, there will be a sort of musical fountain going on just outside the LV store.', 'Very nice Louis Vuitton store.  Feels like Ure on a boat ‚ù§Ô∏èüö¢.  Plus a small vintage LV section at the lower level near the exit üòò', 'Go upstairs at the terrace where You can rest during/after shopping... Nice new cruise collection available now!!! For all European: prices are slightly higher than in Europe even after tax refund.', "You can discover every categories of Louis Vuitton ; RTW,Shoes,LG,W&J as well as travel. Don't miss the balcony with the greatest view!", 'Highly recommended specially when you are a Louis Vuitton fans üòâ', 'The very first Louis Vuitton Island Maison and the first Maison in Southeast Asia. Here, find the biggest Louis Vuitton Bookstore in the world, an exclusive Travel Room, and an art exhibition space.', "A fancy store with nothing you can afford! The staff is nice and let's you just walk around and check it out, so why not!", 'The store is connected from the island building to the one inside the MBS mall. Enter to either one.', 'A brilliant store for LV lovers. Very impressive!! xoxo', 'Look out for the new art work by Artist Yayoi Kusama at the LV window. Its pokka dots mania! :)']

name: The Baxter Inn
reviews: ['Not easy to find, but most amazing wall of whisky in Aus, including Islay single malts like Bruichladdich Octomore. Order the Ploughmans platter with the fancy Pepe Saya butter & side of HOT mustard', 'Best collection of cocktails in Sydney. Very crowded and extremely noisy, but great atmosphere. Favourite spot is at the bar, bartenders are really fun and creative if you let them be!', 'Consistently excellent experience: great drinks, crowd and atmosphere. Go on weeknights or arrive before 8pm Fri/Sat to avoid long queues. Must try a whisky sour, old fashioned or whisky apple juice.', 'Super popular speakeasy located in a small alley in CBD (it‚Äôs downstairs). Great whiskey cocktails and a cool vibe. No table service. Arrive early.', "Unassuming stairway tucked away in an alley. One of the best whiskey selections I've ever seen. Great speakeasy feel with artist bartenders", 'Over 800 whiskies on tap and they make a mean Negroni. Unpretentious and worth the line for one of the best spots in Sydney!', 'More than 200 whiskeys to choose from. Lovely bunker culture with the new breed of hipster / retro young professionals along with other whiskey. Love it, bar tenders are knowledgeable.', 'Great speak-easy vibe, fantastic mixologists, huge whiskey menu and good music. I was with someone who introduced me to whiskey and apple juice . I‚Äôm sold on this place.', 'Awesome hidden bar in the CBD serving up a wide range of whisky. Proper old pub feel with great atmosphere. Free pretzels.', "Tucked behind an alley way and down some concrete stairs you'll find the most extensive collection of whiskies amongst dark brick walls and incredible swing/oldies music. I never wanted to leave."]

name: State Theatre
reviews: ['Stunning room to see a show in with fantastic sound', 'Every June the Sydney Film Festival makes the State Theatre its home.Buy a subscription and you can have your dedicated seat and avoid rushing to get a good seat. Love making friends I see once a year', "Beautiful venue, but can be hard to view screens because of seating. I'm tallish, and still had the guy in front of me blocking half the screen with his head. I feel for whoever was sitting behind me", 'A very pretty venue. I prefer downstairs to the upstairs. Up to 3/4 of the way back is still good', 'Beautiful Art Deco interior.', "Note to future self: Sit in row A for the Sydney Film Festival! It's perfect, trust me -You", "Remember to get your drinks/goodies and stash them in your bag before you get here... well I guess you're too late if you're reading this.", "Lovely theatre. Staff on the other hand - bunch of clowns. Couldn't look after a goldfish.. And security guard looks like he's 12. Lolz. Whatevs, B.B. King was rad!", "NO PHOTOS ALLOWED in the entrance because it's a heritage site yet still being used constantly??! Awh come on! It's probably management excuse for people to join the tour..:( Very beautiful place tho!", '#littlemermaid #sydneypremiere #statetheatresydney #statetheatre #disney #sydney #preview #nowwatching']

name: Hyde Park
address: Elizabeth St (at Park St), Sydney NSW 2000
reviews: ["Hyde Park is nice and peaceful when I want to work in quiet, but also has cool events that don't disturb the rest of the park. I just wish there were more WiFi hotspots, and fewer ibises.", "This is a safe place, night and day. I've never had trouble walking through. It's also stunning all year round. Take a book, or simply lay back and enjoy the sun.", "Fall in love with Hyde Park north's central avenue with the canopy forming from grand fig trees. Love walking through this section of Australia's oldest park", 'Green lung in the heart of Sydney. Definitely a place chill when weather is nice.', 'Nice place to chill, have a picnic, sit on the bench with a book and just daydreaming! Calming and peaceful park.', 'The tree canopy is spectacular here and you can watch or play large scale chess.', 'Hawkfield Gallery Consultants Review: Thriving Classic American Art on Display', 'Lovely place. You could lay down on the grass, dream, read, relax or even play chess.', 'Grass is greenest opposite the Australian Museum. Also, the quietest and best spot for a nap in the park.', 'Beautiful park, especially by night where you can see the possums and stunning war memorial. Very calming and serene place to be.']

name: Royal Botanic Gardens
address: Mrs Macquaries Rd (Cahill Express Way), Sydney NSW 2000
reviews: ['Beautiful and wide Garden. I love that many people come talking and sitting here. There are many giant trees that I cannot find in my country', 'Huge, beautiful garden with over 40 thousand types of plants and trees. I recommend using the little train inside the park as it is very very big plus the train driver doubles as a guide of the park.', 'Took the tram around the gardens. $10 for adults, $5 for children. Really worth it for the guided tour and an overview of the place. After that we took a walk around and had a nice cuppa in the cafe.', "beautiful place to visit with lots of green surroundings to chill at, there's cafes inside and walk to the end to be next to the sea, it's just so relaxing and peaceful. https://t.co/bgnB9cGlMg", 'There are beautiful little secret gardens to find, with roses or veggies or fragrant flowers, try to find your own secret spot!', "Nicest garden I have ever been, super cool that it is in the middle of the city center, you forget you are in Sydney! You need days here, it's huge so many things to explore!", 'Free entry. Always opens at 07:00 every day of the week, however closes anywhere between 17:00 and 20:00 depending on the time of year, unless its New Years Eve.', "Where else in the world does the nation's best botanical garden abut the nation's best view? As old as white Australia itself, this magnificient garden is horticultural heaven: with Opera House views", "Check out the Calyx, to admire an inside wall made out of 18k flowers, and Mrs Macquarie's Chair for lovely views of the city and the Sydney Opera house", 'Stunning place clearly laid out and maintained with flora and fauna thought. Leads to some wonderful historical places too which are worth a visit.']

name: Art Gallery of NSW
reviews: ["The special exhibitions are always worth seeing. But don't forget about the permanent exhibitions, there always great art to see in them and they're free!", 'Very nice gallery!The permanent exhibition is free to visit! Free WiFi!I very enjoyed Asian collections which until 13 mar.2016. Also there are nice cafes! I hope I back here sone! ‚úåÔ∏èüòä', 'I wished I had more time here and will go back the next time I am in Sydney. We paid extra for the Archibald, Wynn and Sulman exhibit and was well worth it. Do it!', 'Went to art after hours and it was fun. There is talks and tours. We went to see a Japanese exhibition and there there was a interview done with a local tattoo artist who does full body Japanese tats', "Just as Melbourne's cool, ordered NGV exemplifies its city, Sydney's AFNSW is a bewildering clusterf*ck of architectural styles. Dig deep for a wonderfully diverse collection: Wednesday is late night", 'If you decide to visit just one gallery or museum, i recommend this one strongly.', 'The Pop to Popism was well worth seeing! Ticket price includes a film screening, so make sure you check out the session times', 'Restaurant on the Mezzanine level (NE corner) provides excellent views across the Harbour and The Wharf.  Hidden gem.  Menu is pretty good value and food generally good quality.', 'The amount of artwork and the spacious displays. Easily spend a day here. Great special exhibits too.', 'The European arts section is awesome. Make sure you check the guided tour schedules before you go. Makes a lot of difference.']

name: Observatory Hill
reviews: ['Got there by accident whilst on the way to the bridge pathway. Fantastic view.', 'One of my favourite to go on a date! Great place to watch the sunset and have a picnic.', 'The perfect spot for a lunch if you work in the City, quiet and such a beautiful view!!', 'Perfect place for a quiet lunch break in the sunshine', 'Come in the evening and listen to the bats while enjoying the view.', 'Wonderful views', 'Great view! Must see places in Sydney', 'Nice little park with good views', 'Beautiful little pagoda to take a picnic or relax and watch the stars', 'Nice place to relax in the city. Great views.']

name: Opera Bar
reviews: ['popular bar to grab a drink and food after office hours, be sure to arrive early to get a table. view is pretty amazing at this place, watching the sunset is awesome. https://t.co/bgnB9cGlMg', 'If stamina allows after the evening show at the Opera House, the Opera Bar is your best choice for a gourmet night cap, with its astounding views on the harbour. A special end, for a Perfect Day.', 'Great place to take out of town friends. Drinks are on the spendy side, but you pay for the location. Sit in the sun, keep the cold beer flowing and enjoy the tunes by the water!', 'Come early, grab a table if you see one, or just chill by the sidewalk. Great views of circular quay and the Bridge in the evening', 'The best views in Sydney beside the opera house looking out over the harbour bridge. Extensive range of beer wine spirits and food. Perfect for Sunday lunch.', 'Amazing view here!! We came here in the evening and enjoyed the warmth from the heater since it was very cold during the winter.', 'Outdoor dining with the view of the Opera House & Harbour Bridge ‚Äì good view, good food, good friends... what more can you ask for?', "Can't go past it for views of the harbour bridge and opera house. A must-do if visiting Sydney, and the cocktails are delicious.", 'One of the best bars in Sydney. It has the most epic view of the Harbour bridge and Opera House. Great place to watch the sun setting. There is also live music at the weekend.', 'Great view and food but it does get pretty packed during the weekend.']

name: Sydney Opera House - Playhouse
reviews: ['Sydney Opera House', 'Great view when at intermission', 'Bernadette Robinson - DIVAS #sydneyoperahouse #bernadetterobinson #divas']

name: Barangaroo Reserve
reviews: ['Absolutely perfect view for sunset! Beware though, it gets extra windy and you might get cold.', 'Barangaroo lures weekend throngs with its stellar location on a formerly industrial, unused slice of the harbor foreshore that has been transformed into a vast green space.', 'Can you believe it used to be an industrial container port? Be sure to sign up for their Aboriginal guided tour to learn about their culture and history.', 'A good place to feel the love from God, listening to de angels singing inside your head. Great for creating and drawing the future in your mind. D+.', 'Beautiful part of town- grab a drink and meal from nearby cafes and sit on one of the benches to enjoy the view', 'Nice park, great views back to the city from a unique aspect. Good sunsets!', "Nice walk with Sydney's skyscrapers in front of you. The park looks perfectly manicured.", 'A perfect spot to bring a picnic and watch the sunset with your friends.', 'Great to see this park transformed and great to have another park along the foreshore.', "Amazing views from the Harbour Bridge, don't miss it"]

name: Sydney Opera House
reviews: ['Absolutely an amazing complex! Its history is unique. Guided tour is essential. Right after the tour you have a discount for a show! I had a chance to watch Tosca!', 'Must do site in Sydney. Walking to the right of the opera heading to the botanical gardens provides an unfamiliar view of the opera and allows for pictures of the opera and of the bridge in one shot.', 'The Opera House offers tours led by good humored guides give insight into the origins, construction, controversy and conflict leading up to the opening of the Sydney Opera House in 1973.', 'While the Opera House is mighty impressive up close, check out the views of it from the Sydney Harbour Bridge, Cahill Walk, or the Overseas Passenger Terminal for a good, less crowded view.', 'This is one of the most beautiful buildings in the world! Take a tour or attend a performance if you can.', 'The most iconic landmark of Sydney and since 2007 on the list of the UNESCO World Heritage. A hotspot for tourists, food, bars and a picture postcard of Sydney. Magnificent view at day and night.', 'The guided tour here is great, with a great balance of technical and historical. Lovely clarity from the guide over headphones giving a real sense of both the amazing story behind it a working venue.', 'Beautifully designed and watched a circus show at the CH. it was a small hall house but the performance was fantastic and amazing!!', 'Beautiful architecture, and a neat way to see the performance areas without shelling out $$$ for one of the shows. Guide was knowledgable and witty.', 'We enjoyed the show here. Got some seats in the middle of the first section of the 2nd tier. Just close enough to enjoy. We can see how the seats to the sides can be fun too.']

name: BERG
reviews: ['Beer and tapas, great ambiente', 'Sausage, beer, atmosphere', 'Be prepared to stand, as there are not enough chairs. Great tapas. One of the few places you can smoke at by the station.', 'It‚Äôs pretty hidden on floor B1. reviews: ["Ohitsuzen - choice of meat or fish (choose bbq Eel) on a bowl of rice, with various condiments and miso soup. You mix it all together with brown rice tea. It's delicious and very cheap! 1850Y each.", "I didn't love the raw tuna. But I LOVED the unagi (eel) Ohitsuzen. I had never had Ohitsuzen so the server helped show me how to do it. Try the unagi ohitsuzen', 'Unagi (eel) ohitsuzen is delicious and affordable, and they have the best onigiri I have had in some time', 'Really nice environment, great food, good place for solo dining', 'Ohitsuzen is great! name: Meiji Jingu Shrine (ÊòéÊ≤ªÁ•ûÂÆÆ)
reviews: ['one of my favorite places to visit when i am here. wear comfy shoes, pack lunch and water and set your fuel bracelet for walking!! find a spot to tune out, close your eyes and tune in to nature', 'Visit. This. Shrine. In the concrete and LED jungle that is Tokyo, Meiji Jingu offers an immediate connection back to nature, quiet and the sacred. Visit at dusk for an especially magical experience.', 'Big shrine dedicated to Emperor Meiji, who opened Japan to the world after long period of self-isolation and after decades made it one of leading countries of the world.', "247acres of heavily-forested area in d middle of Shibuya!Peaceful & quiet.Great place2get away 4a relaxing stroll.It's a site of historical significance.Def shd b on 1s bucket list when visiting Tokyo", 'One of the most famous shrines in Japan. You must be amazed at its huge area. The interesting thing that I found is there are displays of wine barrels not only Sake barrels. Please find it!', "It's a full experience shrine visit in the heart of Tokyo. Avoid going on a really hot day,or if you do, please take water with you it's easy to loose yourself in the surroundings", 'It‚Äôs a must see when in Tokyo. It is free, visited during the autumn festival. beautiful park, nature, Shrine, it is super peaceful and you can spend hours just walking around.', "The shrine is under renovation but you can still feel the peace and serenity. There's a nearby 'Homotsuden' (Treasure Museum), allocate 1 day of your visit here so you could roam around.", 'Beautiful shrine located near Yoyogi Park. The path to the shrine is very photogenic. The shrine itself was also awesome. I go back every time I come to Tokyo. Bring walking shoes for the gravel path!', 'Very peaceful and serene temple located in a beautiful park. A nice change of pace from modern Tokyo. I was lucky to catch a traditional wedding on site']

name: Shinjuku Gyoen (Êñ∞ÂÆøÂæ°Ëãë)
reviews: ["This is my favorite park in Tokyo. It's usually much less crowded than others parks in the city.  Beautiful all year long and with different styles of gardens. An oasis surrounded by skyscrapers.", "Absolutely beautiful park with greenhouse, tea house etc. Can easily spend a whole day here and entry is cheap. Recommend going to Shinjuku-gyoen-mae Station as it's a fair walk from Shinjuku Station.", "Pretty japanese garden among skyscrapers. For drowning in green, enjoying the beauty of nature and deep relaxing. Don't miss this park, it's one of the best in Tokyo.", "You pay 200yen at the entrance but it's more than worth it. Gardens are so beautiful, and the grass is more than inviting to sit on;)", "Probably the most beautiful park in Tokyo. Several styles of landscapes from british, to french to the typical japanese one with cute bridges and a big pond. It's worth the 200¬• entrance.", "It's a must visit every time I go to Tokyo ... It will give you a very relax atmosphere with many small children playing around ... And the restaurant serve a very gud Japanese food", 'Amazingly beautiful! Japanese-style garden with a city skyline makes for postcard-like pictures. Tickets (¬•200) sold at ticket machines. Gazillions of Pok√©mon trainers since Pikachus were spotted.', "This is the quietest park in Tokyo. It combines traditional Japanese garden with some western elements. Don't miss the greenhouse in the northern part of the park.", 'Such a fabulous park with a great variety of flora, always something to see here even with the 500 yen entry fee', 'The greenhouse is super cool and great to go to on a cold winter day!']

name: Yoyogi Park (‰ª£„ÄÖÊú®ÂÖ¨Âúí)
reviews: ["Really huge park in the city center. Sometimes overcrowded, but in the same time it's very spacious, so don't take care about number of people on entrance and get ready to spend here few hours in row.", "A short walk from Shibuya & Harajuku, it's the BEST place to unwind & forget the stresses of city life. My favorite place to escape on summer weekends. Completely mixed crowd. Doesn't feel like Japan.", "Given the sheer size of the park, you'd never know how many people were there, but it's very obviously a popular spot. Alcohol and picnics are encouraged and there's a dedicated bike path for cyclists", "Rockabilly's gather at the entrance after 2pm on Sunday to dance to rock and roll, fun to see. Park is pretty but heaving during Hanami (cherry blossom viewing at end of March/early April).", 'Absolutely wonderful park. A must-visit‚Äîespecially when the weather is nice. There‚Äôs always something going on. Picnics are great here. One of the best places to relax and people-watch in Tokyo.', 'The best place for a picnic when the weather\'s nice, we love sitting by the lake and chilling. Not too many people on weekdays. See dancing Japanese "Elvises" at the entrance on every Sunday!', 'One of the biggest park in Tokyo which located adjacent to harajuku & meiji jingu shrine (but there‚Äôs no direct access) if you lucky you can find costplayers who frequently gather in it#TravelingTokyo', "Lovely wee garden. There are also public toilets. They have heated seats and are the most cleanest public place I've been to! It's quite busy because of the meiji shrine but overall still ok.", 'This is an amazing place to jog or do yoga if you are into it but anyway is a beautiful place to walk and specially the visit to the temple right next to.', 'Beautiful park located right next to JR Harajuku station. Meji Shrine is located inside and the inner gardens and worth the fee. Make sure you go to the well.']

name: FUGLEN TOKYO
reviews: ['Norwegian hipster paradise. Great to chill outside in the evenings. Serves Shiga Kogen beer.', "Cool place where you are able to get nice coffee and special cocktails! It's cozy in the morning and chill at night.", 'Interesting small specialty coffee shop mixed in with a cocktail lounge. Well poured coffee and good selection of home roasted beans', "place is small with library spirit cappuccino teasts unusual for me could'nt recognize the beans used and could ask place was so full.. I took some freshly roasted beans also to try at home", "my happy place. whether you here after a run at yoyogi before for a pourover, or come here at night when they change into a bar for their scandinavian negroni using aquavit, you're in for a treat!", 'my happy place and one of my favorite spots in Tokyo. come for coffee or a drink and sit outside or in. always friendly interesting people üñ§', 'Place oozes style with Joni Mitchell records playing in the background. Cozy space. Coffee by day, booze by night. wifi = cocktails', 'This place offers all of the good things Scandinavia is known for: wood based interior design, excellent coffee, a wide selection of craft beer and spectacular cocktails.', "Sometimes they have donuts from GOOD TOWN DOUGHNUTS (in Harajuku) for maybe ¬•100 more than original price. If you don't have time to visit there, definitely grab one here! üç©", 'Very hip. Always great music playing, relaxed vibe, great coffee & cocktails (the latter start at ¬•1000 or so). If you want to chill, this is the place. To eat, go to Bondi around the corner.']
