name: Blue Note Tokyo
reviews: ['If you have an ticket, Entry calling start at open time after 5min. If you want to get nice seat you should come venue just in time when the venue open time or 10min earlier.', 'Went here for Avant\'s event. June 20-21, 2013. The menu is quite expensive but you get what you pay for. The food is great and they even have "Toast of Love"(Avant\'s song) cocktail in honor of him.', 'Hi, jazz lover! If you‚Äôre planning a trip to Italy, don‚Äôt miss Blue Note Jazz Club in Milan. Good italian cuisine and, of course, the best jazz music from all around the world.', 'Experience live jazz at Blue Note Tokyo, a world-renowned venue. Pair it with excitement from casino plus vin and HOT51 app live for ultimate fun!', 'Book online to reserve the best seats.', 'Bio Actives offers an assortment of spice products keeping in mind the objective of adding taste and value to our customers products.', 'Glad to meet the talented jazz pianist from Indonesia at Blue Note - Tokyo...Best "jazz" wishes always! üòéüéπ', "Any seat and you're bound to get a good view of the show.", 'If you like WHISKY. Most to try this place with The best whisky menu and Jazz selection. Enjoy. Cheers.', 'Nice stage, tasty food- spent an awesome night']

name: Fiesta Farms
address: 200 Christie St (at Essex St), Toronto ON M6G 3B6
reviews: ['The best grocery store in the city, and independently owned too. Heavy emphasis on local products, always fresh produce, and shockingly fair prices.', "Huge variety of vegan products and great produce. Local soyerie Ying Ying tofus, Gryfe's bagels, Sheese, GoVeggie, Daiya cheese, coconut yogurt. Prices aren't always competitive w/ health food shops.", 'Great grocery store. Lots of health food store kind of options. Lots of vegan stuff!', 'You obviously enjoy excellent food. Chef Michael Stadtl√§nder will be serving up his sumptuous, local and organic menu at the @EarthDayCanada Gala on June 6th at The Drake http://bit.ly/KSVhVK', "I love fiesta farms but today my high regard for this place was shattered as I witnessed a crabby old man berate a cashier right in front of me and several other customers& he's the OWNER.  Not cool!", 'Great produce and selection. Independent grocer. Not always the best prices.', 'Excellent produce selection and some good house made sausages.', 'Fantastic selection of cheese, meat, breads, plus huge stock of gluten-free and natural organic products at decent prices.', 'great selection of organic and local foods', 'Great neighborhood grocery']

name: Blood Brothers Brewing
address: 165 Geary Ave (at Barlett Ave N), Toronto ON M6H 2B8
reviews: ['Relaxing ambience with friendly staff. Paradise Lost (Guava) tasted great, the other 3-4 beers I tried from their list were all too bitter. The kitchen was closed and they offered no snacks/food.', '16 options of beer. You can taste by 4/4oz at the time. Big choice of beer for women with different tastes', 'Amazing beers, if they have it try the White Chocolate Stout. Really good.', 'Good brewery with nice sours and citrus forward IPAs. Friendly and helpful staff. Good space, but gets crowded.', 'One of the best breweries in the city', 'all the beers here are great but especially try the paradise lost guava üçª', 'Everything and the merch is great too', 'Must try their sour beers, best ones!', 'Everything is good.', 'Milk of the Poppy üçì']

name: The Greater Good Bar
address: 229 Geary Ave (at Dufferin St), Toronto ON M6H 2C1
reviews: ["Finally, skee ball in Toronto! Great craft beer list and North of Brooklyn pizza. It's basically Get Well North.", 'Great tap selection + North of Brooklyn Pizza will never disappoint (try the Kale and Bacon pizza)', 'Cool bar with great beer selection, amazing pizza, and old arcade games.', 'Great vibes, great space, great lighting, yummy beers and pizza!', "Masks are mandatory when you're not seated at the table. Even if you're outdoors!", "It has pizza too, get's busy on weekends.", 'Nice space. Two floors. North of Brooklyn makes excellent pizza. SKEE BALL.', 'Cervejas boas']

name: Civil Liberties
address: 878 Bloor St W (at Ossington Ave), Toronto ON M6G 1M5
reviews: ['It\'s what cocktail bars want to be. Other places, where you have a conversation with your bartender? This place... you just say, "Something <word>‚Äìy?" and they read everything in that question mark', "Love this place. No menu, just tell them what you like in your drink and they'll make something amazing for you", "Tell them what you like, they don't disappoint üëåüèªüòÄ", 'Absolutely delicious cocktails. There is no cocktail menu ‚Äì they just create incredible concoctions based on your tastes. I have never been disappointed.', 'Coz spot with very knowledgable staff who will gladly mix you a cocktail to suit your preferences and current mood.', "No menu, tell the bartender what you like and they'll make you something great", 'Friendly and skilled bartenders. This signless bar has great taste. Want to hear someone play that piano though.', "Great cocktails. If you don't know what to order, the bartenders are very helpful.", 'Custom cocktails. Several other bars have a schtick of not having a menu, but this one delivers.', 'no menu. no snobbery. extraordinary drinks. excellent bottles.']

name: Hailed Coffee
address: 44 Gerrard St W (Yonge St), Toronto ON M5G 2K2
reviews: ["Coffee here is amazing! Don't miss trying the hailed (cardamom infused) cappuccino or latte!", 'Highest quality coffee, costs less than Starbucks, custom roasts, skilled baristas, fantastic pastries. Try the signature Hailed Cappuccino or Hailed Latte.', 'I am not a big fan of flavoured coffee but the Hailed Latte had the right blend of coffee and milk infused with cardamom', 'On weekends Hailed is the spot to be at for French Desserts. Try the edible latte! A signature dessert inspired by coffee culture and Middle Easter flavours.', 'Try the Hailed iced latte with almond milk.', 'All pastries are fantastic. Working staff are super nice. High quality coffee with amazing prices', 'Closest independent coffee joint to the Chelsea hotel.', 'French pastry every weekend. All inspired by Middle Eastern culture and flavours. Unique and spectacular.', 'Chocolate line is award winning and unique.', 'The best cappuccino in town! Try it Hailed for a kick of cardamom üòã']

name: Art Gallery of Ontario
address: 317 Dundas St W (at Beverley St), Toronto ON M5T 1G4
reviews: ["Did you know that the AGO's spiral staircase, designed by Frank Gehry, is purposefully narrow so that people could bump into each other and fall in love. Ahhh!", 'The best thing about this museum is the architecture, it is a lovely building. If you are visiting Toronto, make sure to stop by for a visit. Mixed feelings about their collection in view.', 'At $CA 25 it is the most I have paid for entrance at a museum. But it boasts an impressive collection thanks to its founders, benefactors and private collections that were once enjoyed by a lucky few.', 'Gorgeous spiral stairs that lead up to the top floor gallery. Don‚Äôt forget to check out the basement which has many models of naval ships, mostly from Britain. It‚Äôs spectacular and often overlooked.', 'Right On: Maybe the best salad buffet in town every other Friday at the AGO Cafe.  The exotic toppings seem to be disappearing as they may be having a hard time staying in the black.  Best hidden gem', 'The architecture alone is worth coming. Add the view as well as the Group of Seven exhibits to make an enjoyable and worthwhile visit. To see everything more visits are needed. Seems great for kids.', 'This is a great museum that focuses on art both European art, First Nations art, and Canadian artists. There is a collection of model ships on the bottom floor.', 'Guided tours can be tough to follow specially if there‚Äôs a lot of tourists. The collection is awesome, though.  My favorite is ‚Äúthe lady of Shalott‚Äù', 'Great museum with plenty of art to see. Mostly by Canadian artists but they also have works from artists around the world including Picasso, Monet, and Rembrandt.', 'This museum is definitely worth the visit, permanent collection of Canadian and European art, great contemporary exhibits. Building itself is very well designed as well']

name: Sonic Boom
reviews: ['Good selection of pop and rock, but also some electronic among others. A large bottomfloor with a huge selection of vinyl', 'They have great selection, prices and service. Would recommend them to anyone :)', 'Cool T-shirts and souvenir store if you want something that is not the classic ‚Äúblue jays/maple leafs‚Äù thingy.', 'Amazing selection, no House though? And great gifts', "Fantastic selection, beautiful storefront! Music lover's delight ü§òüòé", 'Great selection of vinyl, DVD‚Äôs, gifts and more. Cool vibe', "Huge selection and some discounts on records you wouldn't expect!", 'So many records and other cool things to check out.', 'S√∫per cool =D', 'Great place']

name: Trinity Bellwoods Park
address: 1053 Dundas St W (at Gore Vale Ave.), Toronto ON M5H 2N2
reviews: ['Drum Circle is every Tuesday from spring until Halloween, it is open to all hand drums we play until 11:oo Pm. This is from the original drum and dance group and NOT affiliated with drummers in exile.', 'Bring your six-pack (of beer) and go directly to the off-leash dog park. Sit at the top of the hill and enjoy your beer. Now consider yourself having earned a true Bellwoods experience.', "Perfect place to hide out after a variety of small crimes and or misdemeanors such as robbery, attempted robbery, or assault. Also makes a great temporary home for those 'in between apartment' nights.", "Drum circle is now every Sunday in the park, it's been an amazing journey drumming in this park, what started as a quiet Tuesday night over ten years ago was first forced out by the city. We're Back!!", 'Off-leash dog bowl. Hipsters galore. Wonderful acroyoga and slackline communities. Great playground. Lots of space to picnic and drink. LOVE THIS PARK!!', 'It‚Äôs big and has everything you want in a park. Dog unleashed area, kids playgrounds, and picnic tables. It‚Äôs rare to have a nice big park in the city of Toronto.', "A wonderful escape in the city. Flanked by drool worthy spots like Nadege and Oyster Boy. Grab a few Macarons and cruise through the park. Followed by a few Kushi's and some Norman Hardie Chard.", "Say hello to Mo at the slacklines, he's the nicest guy!", "Great park in the middle of the city. This is the perfect place to walk your dog, picnic, and bike. Don't forget to look out for the famous white squirrels!", "This is a friendly park but a quick warning.  Don't let your dog off the leash, there are now City of Toronto bylaw officers who prowl the park and the fines are excessive."]

name: Riverdale Park East
reviews: ["Lovely sunsets. Grew up around here so it's very sentimental to me. During summertime you can lay on the hill or run around the track, play baseball, soccer, etc. Wintertime is for sledding! Love it.", 'Most of the fields are choppy and uneven. Great for relaxing in a huge open space on the hill or playing catch/frisbee. Not as good for football or running sports.', 'Such a beautiful place and an amazing view of the Toronto skyline anytime of the day or night... Great place to meet ppl, exercise or relax with a good friend or good book!!', 'Movie in the park during the summers, a place to lay in the grass and enjoy the downtown skyline, enjoy magnificent sunsets or challenge yourself to sprint up the hill.', 'Big park with 2 base ball court, 1 running track, 1 football court and plenty on space with a huge gallery kind of slope üëç However we love playing cricket üèè', 'One of the most accessible vantage points of the city. Nice view indeed', 'Enjoy an outdoor movie in the grass at Riverdale East Park on the last Sunday of each summer month, at sundown. Proceeds from each screening go to the Kiwanis Boys and Girls Club.', 'quiet park, magnificent view of the skyscrapers, ‚ù§Ô∏è', 'Great in the winter for some Tobogganing!', "A wonderful place to see Toronto's skyline!"]

name: City of Toronto Sign
reviews: ["It's a sign! But in Toronto. One of the best cities in the world. Near to most things and an abundance of hotels. The sign is great for a picture in any season, and winter will even give you skating", 'Especially when the sun is gone great scenery', "If it's busy and you still want a good photo, try standing on the elevated pathway around the edge of Nathan Phillips Square for a better angle", 'Gorgeous part of the town. At night the sign is simply beautiful']

name: Dai Zemei
reviews: ['Great place to try Venetian cicchetti off the tourist trap!', 'Amazing selection of crostinis. Try the one with sardines or any of the meat ones - prosciutto, parma ham, speck, mortadella!', "Amazing bruschetta selection. You won't be able to control yourself. Great for lunch or s snack.", 'Sit, drink and eat while the significant other shops... great place to people watch!', 'Spritz!   Crostinis from heaven! Owner speaks English well!', 'An excellent Ostaria for an afternoon drink and snack.', 'They are so kind !!! Love it', 'Had an excellent wine recommendation. And great cichetti!', "Best cicheti I've ever tried.  Excellent prices", 'Convenient place to stop for a drink on your way out of tourist hell. Crostini is reasonably priced.']

name: Canal Grande
address: Santa Croce 1979 - Campo San Stae, 30100 Venezia Veneto
reviews: ['Venice is renowned for the beauty of its setting, its architecture and its artworks. The city in its entirety is listed as World Heritage Site, along with its lagoon.', "Take a public water boat. Sit in the open area (if not available, wait for the place, take day tickets so you don't need to get down). Sit, relax, soak in and enjoy Venice's essence.", 'If in Venice for romance, think about taking a gondola ride around some of this fascinating network of canals. If not, take the public transport to get around - less costly but still the same beauty!', 'Most of these buildings date from the 13th to the 18th centuries and pose a Venetian-Gothic style. The best way to see these beautiful buildings is to travel by the vaporetto, the water bus.', 'Just relax and enjoy the stunning architecture. Sit outside to feel the energy.', 'Beautiful and picturesque. Some new and amazing round every corner. Great place to chill and people watch. Friendly staff great food.', 'Unlimited pass for 1-3 days on vaporetos is the best investment during the stay here. Also it allows you to swim over to the other neighboring islands', 'Boats work 24H. You can ride in the evening and in the night. It‚Äôs very special atmosphere here) Make sure to take warm clothes.', 'Locally called as Canalazzo.  The best way to see the beautiful buildings along the canal is to travel by the vaporetto, the water bus. There are a few halal kebab and takeaway outlets.', 'To do: take the No.1 vaporetto ACTV linea 1 from Piazzale Roma to Piazza San Marco.  To avoid crowd: Go in the late afternoon, as at this time of day, most people travel in the other direction.']

name: Campo San Polo
reviews: ["During summer, if you're walking the city, this is the best spot to rest on a bench under the tree and watch people.", 'Wonderful place for some people watching.', 'Billarira restaurant highly recommended . Order the pestrin pizza', 'Bright place to rest and enjoy the sun', 'Ice skating in Venezia? Come here in winter and give it a try!', "Very big even tho' there isn'y much to see", 'Visit Customers.', "Da il nome al Sestiere che lo ospita ed √® il pi√π grande di Venezia. Anticamente vi si svolgevano le feste del carnevale, i mercati, le corse. Nel 1548 vi venne assassinato Lorenzino de' Medici.", "Da non perdere l'istallazione d'arte contemporaneo polacco che si svolge con motivo della denominazione di Varsavia come capitale europea della cultura a 2016", 'Mais uma das muitas pra√ßas de Veneza']

name: Cantina Do Spade
address: Sestiere San Polo 860 (Calle delle Do Spade, 19), 30125 Venezia Veneto
reviews: ['Excellent local cantina with amazing food and wine! Start with the typical starters and enjoy the delicious pastas or risotto or mains!! I loved this place! An hidden gem among many touristy places', 'Spicy baby octopus as antipasti, mixed fried seafood with vegetables with vegetables as a second dish. Nice and cosy, we really enjoyed it!', 'Best local restaurant of Venice; happy staff, happy costumers even the f.cking fried calamari was happy as I was chewing it or I drank too much Prosecco.. Your call ..', 'reasonable prices for seafood excellent shrimp and sea bass good tiramisu', 'The foods here are awesome! Try the cichetti (small tapas/ fried foods), pasta is good, mixed fry seafood, and I love the Tiramisu cake here, not too heavy and more cake-like!', 'Its a nice small bar restaurant! We go twice one for wine and one to try the cousine. I suppose is not cheap for those plates. Tha stuff are happy and helpfull but the food is poor. If hungry dont go', 'The best food in Venice. Make a reservation, order the mix starter plate and the mixed fried fish. You will not regret it.', 'One of the best Bacari in Venezia. Traditional food on a young and friendly environment. Get meatballs.', "Sardines do spade are really nice! ‚Ç¨1.50 each or four for ‚Ç¨6, so try it first. The cod and tomato and fried zucchini flower is nice too! Love the tiramisu cos it's more cake than cream.", 'This is one of the must try in Venice, very tasty "cicchetti" and also the main courses. They only need to fix a problem with the smell, as after dinner you need to change your clothes.']

name: Rialto Bridge (Ponte di Rialto)
address: Ruga Vecchia San Giovanni, San Polo 1023 (San Polo), 30125 Venezia Veneto
reviews: ['An architectural icons of Venice and one of the most visited tourist attractions of the city. You will never miss this bridge if you are crossing between San Marco and San Polo. Enjoy the view!', 'Incredibly beautiful and scenic views here. This is the famous bridge of Venice and the architecture of it is incredible. Does get very busy with people, and there are tourist shops along it.', 'The bridge is always packed with tourists and gives great views and pictures along the Grand Canal - Well worth the visit.', 'One of the two most recognized landmarks of Venice. The bridge itself is choked with people :). Go either early or very late in the day. Best photos from Rialto ACTV station.', 'One of the must-see sights in Venice. I recommend to take the water bus line 1 starting at Pizzale Roma and sit in the very front. You can take pictures like from a postcard.', 'The most touristic bridge in the city. A must see touristic attraction. Great place to enjoy the city and the canals and people watching. One of the best places for picture taking.', 'Very beautiful bridge but very crowded. A half of it was under reconstruction and huge ad of some clothes store, which spoiled the view. Best to visit in evening when shops located there are closed.', "A great place to visit any time of the year. If you're an early bird like me, I prefer walking by early in the morning. You get to see everyone preparing for their days work! Beautiful.", 'You can buy souvenirs, ride on gondola and enjoy the food in this area! Ask the local to get more info (:', 'Iconic Venetian bridge . Pretty much covered in people though...which is worth bearing in mind if you, like us, are travelling with a buggy...']

name: Al Grill
reviews: ['The first day in our holiday in Venice we came to this restaurant and I gotta say, it was worth it. We had a amazing time with my family here. The meat is delicious, especially the Black Angus T-bone', 'The steak I had here was one of the best I‚Äôve ever tasted. We started with the tartare as an appetizer and followed it with the tomahawk. Make sure to visit!', 'Thank you Christian for your utmost hospitality üôèüèª', 'Tomahawk with bread shrimp. Simply excellent.', 'Costata fiorentina: macia, deliciosa, no ponto certo. Pe√ßa junto batata frita, √© muito crocante e sequinha. Claro, por ser carne, √© mais cara, mas vale cada euro! Ah, uma cervejinha acompanha bem!', 'Gran lugar , carne y postres de lo mejor']

name: SuSo
reviews: ['Possibly the best gelateria in whole of Venice! Went for tiramisu and another flavour whose name I have forgotten, and it was fabulous! Very friendly staff too, and close to Rialto Bridge. Must visit!', 'the ice cream is really nice, the best I had so far. fresh flavours. the staff is amazing, good service!! the best way to get there is from the square', 'Slightly more pricey than other places but still worth a taste. They let you taste flavors and staff is very nice. If you like chocolate fudge swirls get crema del doge or moro di venezia.', 'Literally the best  ice cream üç¶ that I have ever eaten in my entire life! I really mean it! Imagine eating it with the view of Rialto bridge in Venice‚Ä¶', 'Amazing gelato,, defiantly worth the going to!', 'Great ice cream! Milk free ice cream yet very creamy and soft. I would recommend the dark chocolate and the tiramisu flavors', 'The most delicious ice cream shop in town!üòçüòç Try opera, lemon and yoghurt..', 'My favorite gelato shop in Italy. Try the Manet. And the Suso. And the Academia. Basically just try everything.', 'We were in Venice for 2 days and got it 4 times, do it! Highly recommend the salted pistachio with chocolate one', 'The line looked long but wasn‚Äôt more than 15 mins and totally worth the wait. The Nutella and pistachio were both some of the best gelato I‚Äôve ever had.']

name: Teatro la Fenice
reviews: ["Such an iconic and important teather. Don't miss out on the opera season here. No need to book in advance for an audio guide tour which will last 50 minutes circa. Price ‚Ç¨10 enjoy!!", "This is one of the city's best and most beautiful opera houses, and though it has seen lots of unfortunate events, it has been properly restored. Go on a 45-minute tour here to learn more.", "Since opening and being named La Fenice, it has burned and been rebuilt twice more. That's how the name defines a destiny of the place. Visit amazing opera here, one the best Opera Houses in the world", 'Loved the show and experience,  take seats that are on the second or third floor for best sight', 'Great visit and you can assist to the repetitions. Do not arrive too late otherwise you wont have access to certain rooms.', 'What an opera house! What a performance! We watched from a box, Best to be in a box directly facing the stage to enjoy the performance the most.', 'Stunning building with an interesting audio guide', 'Wonderful gem in the middle of a jewel.', 'Amazing! Came just before new year and got an entirely free new year concert preview, with orchestra, chorus, and soloists!', 'La traviata, awesome ! And beautiful theatre']

name: Venchi SPA
reviews: ["Very very delicious...tastes fresh...i cannot say if its best in venice since I'm only a tourist and tried only 3 places...but it is totally good and a must try...try the dark chocolate and strawberry", 'I loved the mango gelato. The raspberry sorbet was delicious as well but a little tarte. Definetley recommend trying it out!', 'Marvellous, expensive. In the very centre, next to Piazza San Marco. Strongly recommend a portion in a cone (salty one) with dark chocolate(as brownie), vanilla(creme br√ªl√©e like) and mango!!', 'Good gelato but quite expensive, $5.50 for 3 scoops and cream. I enjoyed the strawberry a lot, and the chcolate hazelnut. The pistachio was quite subtle.', 'Delicious: such a great place. The best ice cream i have ever had. Coconut, just perfect . Highly recommended‚ù§Ô∏è‚ù§Ô∏èüçß', "It's a franchise, sometimes when ur lucky and the temperature is right, then you get a great gelato (gelato freezing point), or u get a cone with melting liquids....", 'Rasperry sorbet, dark chocolate, pistachio and lemon sorbet if you love your lemon tart - all yummy!', "It may be a chain but it's still authentic.  Remember kids if the gelato is piled high above the rim and looks fluffy and cloud like it is not real.   Real gelato is dense.", "Milk flavour and the Egg Vanilla flavour if you're a dairy fan! The shop itself is vividly decorated and very inviting. There are no proper seats, however.", "I've ate gelato lots of times and lots of places but never eat like this. name: Tivoli
reviews: ["Great fun for the whole family! Get the unlimited pass so you can go on as many rides as you like. The hidden gem of the park is the 'Train' roller coaster, if only for the super happy controller.", 'Go before it gets dark and see the tivoli turn into a beautifully lit magic garden. Stay until it closes and see the water, light and music show at the lake. Go well in advance to get a good spot!', "Tivoli's traditional outlook extends far beyond their carousel and other much loved attractions. A traditional customer service ethos ensures any issues are quickly dealt with and questions answered.", 'Tivoli Gardens is an amusement park and pleasure garden located by the Central Station. During Christmas time there is a big Christmas markets w/ lots of ornaments, lights & decorations. Go see it :)', 'The entrance fee is about $12 USD, not including rides. Get an unlimited pass if you plan to go on a lot of rides. Very charming place. Worth checking out. I recommend going at night for the lights', "Go at Christmas & have some gluhwein. It's cheesy and amazing. Save money & don't pay for unlimited ride entry - you can buy a few tickets inside if you want to go on some.", 'entrance fee (120 dkk) There are cafes, restaurants, and entertainment park. But you pay again to take a ride in the park.I dont recommend if you have a plan for legoland', 'It‚Äôs a reason on its own to visit Copenhagen. Very cute on special days like Valentine‚Äôs, free concerts in summer, turns magical during Christmas. Try to go on weekdays, too crowded otherwise.', "This is an amusement park like no other in the world. It's from 1843 and although new rides and restaurants open each year, it is always done with respect to tradition and history of the park. Enjoy!", 'Great Christmas market and lovely way to spend a night with friends. Fun to walk around in even if you don‚Äôt go on any rides. Price is totally worth it - go at night to see everything lit up!']

name: Faraos Cigarer
reviews: ['Very nice hobby and comics and collertors shop. Quite interesting. Worth to visit. English comic books are available.', "They seem to own the entire city. There's a shop for disguising, one with classic comics (BD/strips), one with comics, one with games. Very large selection.", "A favorite one if you're into comics and figures. Even if not it's worth to visit.", "Large, clean, excellent comic shop. Graphic novel types are well organized, there's something for everyone here.", 'A must-visit when in Copenhagen. Visit all four stores close to each other.', 'Best comic & geek store in Scandinavia, lots of books, magazines and collectables. Love it!', 'Huge selection of comics, graphic novels and merchandise', "All sorts of comics and merchandise. They also have lot's of english issues.", "There are four different storefronts, some with multiple floors. Make sure you don't miss any!", 'Not a classic comic shop, but with a great collection of whole series and books.']

name: Gorms Torvehallerne
reviews: ['This is foodie Valhalla. You could eat lunch every day here. Get the duck confit sandwich at Ma Poule, juice at Palaeo, oatmeal at Grod, and espresso at Coffee collective. Enjoy the outdoor patio.', "Many food stalls with different choices from all around the world. Go for an authentic smorrebrod with fresh fish. Don't miss the Cafe Collective at the entrance for a nice cup of cortado!", "if you're a foodie, this is your Nordic heaven. Bring lots of money and time. Get breakfast at Gr√∏d with a Coffee Collective drink, for lunch get a salad from Smag.", "Great indoors market for food/drink lovers. You can spend all day long here with the only problem being finding a space to sit. Options for breakfast, lunch, quick bite, coffee and wine. Don't miss!", "The confit de canard sandwich from Ma Poule is the most recommended for a reason, and you won't be disappointed. Deliciously tender and salty duck on a baguette, simple but utterly incredible.", "Torvehallerne is a wonderland of food, a place where everyone from home cooks to professional chefs go to source fresh, local foods and groceries. There's also lots of nice Danish craft beer here! .", 'Very nice place with a lot of little places to have a drink or to eat something. One hall is for breakfast and coffee and the other one is more for lunch and dinner', 'Central food/drink/produce Mekka in Copenhagen. Well worth the crowds. Le petit, ma poule, banh mi, hachi Sanchez, coffee collective, Gorms and Smag are really delicious to name a few', 'Really great food options! I went here everyday whilst in Copenhagen - porridge from Groed is delicious, focaccia sandwich from Norcino is super tasty & coffee from Coffee Collective is amazing.', 'Always many people and tourists. You can buy vegetables, fruits, fish and meat, also Unika cheese is here. A lot of food spots.']

name: National Monument
address: Jalan Parlimen, 50480 Kuala Lumpur, Kuala Lumpur
reviews: ['The National Monument commemorates the fallen soldiers during WWII and the Malayan Emergency.The best time to visit is at dawn, where a soldier raises the national flag and lowers it again at dusk.', "A nicely done memorial to those who made the ultimate sacrifice for Malaysia. Reminded us of the Iwo Jima memorial in Washington DC. It's free and there's a small food stand on entry.", 'Such beautiful place to visit but sadly the Jalur Gemilang held by our beloved Tugu Negara was old, and torn due to the weather. Hopefully the caretaker would replace the flag as soon as possible!', "Many years on and still very well preserved. One of must visit places to learn about the country's war histories.", 'Dramatically impressing sculpture of the important battle in history of Malaysia. Very beautiful site around the Monument. Also place of good view.', 'The park was nice and clean. The landscape was full of greenery. Would love to have a picnic here with family.', 'Remembering our nation heroes! Dont forget to bring caps or umbrella! Gotta save your skin too hehe', 'The most underrated spot in KL, which makes this place a plus i.e. crowd is almost non-existent on a Sunday morning when I visited.', 'Dedicated to the fallen heroes of the two World Wars, this National Monument is where you can also find the ASEAN Garden, which has great sculptures by remarkable artists.', 'Relax in the park and take photos around the monuments. Must for tourists.']
